 a huge paradigm shift.", "tokens": [50699, 1779, 11, 309, 311, 257, 2603, 24709, 5513, 13, 50769], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11829090954964622, "compression_ratio": 1.662162162162162, "no_speech_prob": 1.629849358773805e-12}, {"id": 22, "seek": 8732, "start": 95.58, "end": 103.94, "text": " Because if we think about the lambda calculus, which has dominated functional programming for decades, scope is defined syntactically.", "tokens": [50778, 1436, 498, 321, 519, 466, 264, 13607, 33400, 11, 597, 575, 23755, 11745, 9410, 337, 7878, 11, 11923, 307, 7642, 23980, 578, 984, 13, 51196], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11829090954964622, "compression_ratio": 1.662162162162162, "no_speech_prob": 1.629849358773805e-12}, {"id": 23, "seek": 8732, "start": 104.06, "end": 105.52, "text": " Right, you literally type it out.", "tokens": [51202, 1779, 11, 291, 3736, 2010, 309, 484, 13, 51275], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11829090954964622, "compression_ratio": 1.662162162162162, "no_speech_prob": 1.629849358773805e-12}, {"id": 24, "seek": 8732, "start": 105.58, "end": 109.91999999999999, "text": " Yeah, you use parentheses or brackets, you would close a function, and you basically say,", "tokens": [51278, 865, 11, 291, 764, 34153, 420, 26179, 11, 291, 576, 1998, 257, 2445, 11, 293, 291, 1936, 584, 11, 51495], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11829090954964622, "compression_ratio": 1.662162162162162, "no_speech_prob": 1.629849358773805e-12}, {"id": 25, "seek": 8732, "start": 110.19999999999999, "end": 113.96, "text": " everything inside these brackets belongs to this local environment.", "tokens": [51509, 1203, 1854, 613, 26179, 12953, 281, 341, 2654, 2823, 13, 51697], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11829090954964622, "compression_ratio": 1.662162162162162, "no_speech_prob": 1.629849358773805e-12}, {"id": 26, "seek": 8732, "start": 114.0, "end": 115.0, "text": " Yeah, it's very rigid.", "tokens": [51699, 865, 11, 309, 311, 588, 22195, 13, 517