" Yeah, that's the scary part.", "tokens": [51067, 865, 11, 300, 311, 264, 6958, 644, 13, 51130], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.164295494556427, "compression_ratio": 1.4482758620689655, "no_speech_prob": 1.7080378994852041e-12}, {"id": 21, "seek": 5772, "start": 73.12, "end": 73.32, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51135, 1779, 13, 51145], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.164295494556427, "compression_ratio": 1.4482758620689655, "no_speech_prob": 1.7080378994852041e-12}, {"id": 22, "seek": 7332, "start": 73.32, "end": 82.3, "text": " We are looking at a computational landscape today that is completely alien to how we normally think about software, math, and logic.", "tokens": [50365, 492, 366, 1237, 412, 257, 28270, 9661, 965, 300, 307, 2584, 12319, 281, 577, 321, 5646, 519, 466, 4722, 11, 5221, 11, 293, 9952, 13, 50814], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.113471257804644, "compression_ratio": 1.6486486486486487, "no_speech_prob": 1.466482100684341e-12}, {"id": 23, "seek": 7332, "start": 82.75999999999999, "end": 87.38, "text": " So our mission for this deep dive is to ask a question that might just break your brain.", "tokens": [50837, 407, 527, 4447, 337, 341, 2452, 9192, 307, 281, 1029, 257, 1168, 300, 1062, 445, 1821, 428, 3567, 13, 51068], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.113471257804644, "compression_ratio": 1.6486486486486487, "no_speech_prob": 1.466482100684341e-12}, {"id": 24, "seek": 7332, "start": 87.69999999999999, "end": 88.94, "text": " And it really will break it.", "tokens": [51084, 400, 309, 534, 486, 1821, 309, 13, 51146], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.113471257804644, "compression_ratio": 1.6486486486486487, "no_speech_prob": 1.466482100684341e-12}, {"id": 25, "seek": 7332, "start": 89.02, "end": 89.39999999999999, "text": " It will.", "tokens": [51150, 467, 486, 13, 51169], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.113471257804644, "compression_ratio": 1.6486486486486487, "no_speech_prob": 1.466482100684341e-12}, {"id": 26, "seek": 7332, "start": 89.67999999999999, "end": 97.61999999999999, "text": " The question is, what if everything we know about how computers compute and how we write code is fundamentally backward?", "tokens": [51183, 440, 1168, 307, 11, 437, 498, 1203, 321, 458, 466, 577, 10807, 14722, 293, 577, 321, 2464, 3089, 307, 17879, 23897, 30, 51580], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.113471257804644, "compression_ratio": 1.6486486486486487, "no_speech_prob": 1.466482100684341e-12}, {"id": 27, "seek": 7332, "start": 97.91999999999999, "end": 99.75999999999999, "text": " Backward might even be an understatement here.", "tokens": [51595, 5833, 1007, 1062, 754, 312, 364, 833, 19435, 1712, 510, 13, 51687], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.113471257804644, "compression_ratio": 1.6486486486486487, "no_speech_prob": 1.466482100684341e-12}, {"id": 28, "seek": 9976, "start": 99.76, "end": 102.34, "text": " I mean, we are diving into a complete paradigm shift.", "tokens": [50365, 286, 914, 11, 321, 366, 20241, 666, 257, 3566, 24709, 5513, 13, 50494], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14545989486406435, "compression_ratio": 1.5364963503649636, "no_speech_prob": 1.435011289484256e-12}, {"id": 29, "seek": 9976, "start": 102.94000000000001, "end": 111.60000000000001, "text": " It's all outlined in two groundbreaking theoretical papers published by the independent researcher Flixian back in June 2026.", "tokens": [50524, 467, 311, 439, 27412, 294, 732, 42491, 20864, 10577, 6572, 538, 264, 6695, 21751, 3235, 970, 952, 646, 294, 6928, 945, 10880, 13, 50957], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14545989486406435, "compression_ratio": 1.5364963503649636, "no_speech_prob": 1.435011289484256e-12}, {"id": 30, "seek": 9976, "start": 111.72, "end": 111.92, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50963, 1779, 13, 50973], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14545989486406435, "compression_ratio": 1.5364963503649636, "no_speech_prob": 1.435011289484256e-12}, {"id": 31, "seek": 9976, "start": 111.98, "end": 112.60000000000001, "text": " I've got them right here.", "tokens": [50976, 286, 600, 658, 552, 558, 510, 13, 51007], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14545989486406435, "compression_ratio": 1.5364963503649636, "no_speech_prob": 1.435011289484256e-12}, {"id": 32, "seek": 9976, "start": 112.88000000000001, "end": 116.08000000000001, "text": " The first is titled A Historical Foundation for Dependent Type Theory.", "tokens": [51021, 440, 700, 307, 19841, 316, 46124, 10335, 337, 4056, 521, 317, 15576, 29009, 13, 51181], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14545989486406435, "compression_ratio": 1.5364963503649636, "no_speech_prob": 1.435011289484256e-12}, {"id": 33, "seek": 9976, "start": 116.54, "end": 118.98, "text": " The second one is called Types as Refusal Structures.", "tokens": [51204, 440, 1150, 472, 307, 1219, 5569, 5190, 382, 16957, 11765, 745, 44513, 13, 51326], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14545989486406435, "compression_ratio": 1.5364963503649636, "no_speech_prob": 1.435011289484256e-12}, {"id": 34, "seek": 9976, "start": 119.72, "end": 123.78, "text": " And what Flixian is proposing across these two papers is a system called SpherePop.", "tokens": [51363, 400, 437, 3235, 970, 952, 307, 29939, 2108, 613, 732, 10577, 307, 257, 1185, 1219, 318, 6605, 38677, 13, 51566], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14545989486406435, "compression_ratio": 1.5364963503649636, "no_speech_prob": 1.435011289484256e-12}, {"id": 35, "seek": 12378, "start": 123.78, "end": 132.04, "text": " Okay, let's unpack this immediately because SpherePop is a radical new foundation for constructive mathematics and programming.", "tokens": [50365, 1033, 11, 718, 311, 26699, 341, 4258, 570, 318, 6605, 38677, 307, 257, 12001, 777, 7030, 337, 30223, 18666, 293, 9410, 13, 50778], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0846707270695613, "compression_ratio": 1.6162790697674418, "no_speech_prob": 1.3995415069911754e-12}, {"id": 36, "seek": 12378, "start": 132.52, "end": 137.86, "text": " Like, instead of treating computation as a machine that constantly overwrites its current state.", "tokens": [50802, 1743, 11, 2602, 295, 15083, 24903, 382, 257, 3479, 300, 6460, 670, 86, 30931, 1080, 2190, 1785, 13, 51069], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0846707270695613, "compression_ratio": 1.6162790697674418, "no_speech_prob": 1.3995415069911754e-12}, {"id": 37, "seek": 12378, "start": 137.96, "end": 142.16, "text": " Like your laptop wiping its RAM to store new variables every millisecond, yeah.", "tokens": [51074, 1743, 428, 10732, 40611, 1080, 14561, 281, 3531, 777, 9102, 633, 27940, 18882, 11, 1338, 13, 51284], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0846707270695613, "compression_ratio": 1.6162790697674418, "no_speech_prob": 1.3995415069911754e-12}, {"id": 38, "seek": 12378, "start": 142.26, "end": 142.68, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [51289, 7587, 13, 51310], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0846707270695613, "compression_ratio": 1.6162790697674418, "no_speech_prob": 1.3995415069911754e-12}, {"id": 39, "seek": 12378, "start": 143.2, "end": 149.8, "text": " Instead of that, SpherePop treats computation as an irreversible, constantly growing history of events.", "tokens": [51336, 7156, 295, 300, 11, 318, 6605, 38677, 19566, 24903, 382, 364, 16014, 840, 964, 11, 6460, 4194, 2503, 295, 3931, 13, 51666], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0846707270695613, "compression_ratio": 1.6162790697674418, "no_speech_prob": 1.3995415069911754e-12}, {"id": 40, "seek": 14980, "start": 149.8, "end": 160.26000000000002, "text": " To really grasp the magnitude of this, we kind of have to look at how we've built essentially every computing system since, well, since the von Neumann architecture was conceived.", "tokens": [50365, 1407, 534, 21743, 264, 15668, 295, 341, 11, 321, 733, 295, 362, 281, 574, 412, 577, 321, 600, 3094, 4476, 633, 15866, 1185, 1670, 11, 731, 11, 1670, 264, 2957, 1734, 449, 969, 9482, 390, 34898, 13, 50888], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08329114994081128, "compression_ratio": 1.6, "no_speech_prob": 1.6552578535264373e-12}, {"id": 41, "seek": 14980, "start": 160.44, "end": 161.44, "text": " Which is pretty much everything.", "tokens": [50897, 3013, 307, 1238, 709, 1203, 13, 50947], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08329114994081128, "compression_ratio": 1.6, "no_speech_prob": 1.6552578535264373e-12}, {"id": 42, "seek": 14980, "start": 161.58, "end": 161.74, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50954, 1779, 13, 50962], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08329114994081128, "compression_ratio": 1.6, "no_speech_prob": 1.6552578535264373e-12}, {"id": 43, "seek": 14980, "start": 161.82000000000002, "end": 164.64000000000001, "text": " In a standard program, a variable is just a bucket.", "tokens": [50966, 682, 257, 3832, 1461, 11, 257, 7006, 307, 445, 257, 13058, 13, 51107], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08329114994081128, "compression_ratio": 1.6, "no_speech_prob": 1.6552578535264373e-12}, {"id": 44, "seek": 14980, "start": 164.98000000000002, "end": 167.08, "text": " You put the number 5 in a bucket labeled X.", "tokens": [51124, 509, 829, 264, 1230, 1025, 294, 257, 13058, 21335, 1783, 13, 51229], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08329114994081128, "compression_ratio": 1.6, "no_speech_prob": 1.6552578535264373e-12}, {"id": 45, "seek": 14980, "start": 167.60000000000002, "end": 172.22000000000003, "text": " A few microseconds later, the program updates and puts a 6 in that exact same bucket.", "tokens": [51255, 316, 1326, 3123, 37841, 28750, 1780, 11, 264, 1461, 9205, 293, 8137, 257, 1386, 294, 300, 1900, 912, 13058, 13, 51486], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08329114994081128, "compression_ratio": 1.6, "no_speech_prob": 1.6552578535264373e-12}, {"id": 46, "seek": 14980, "start": 172.38000000000002, "end": 173.74, "text": " And the 5 is just gone.", "tokens": [51494, 400, 264, 1025, 307, 445, 2780, 13, 51562], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08329114994081128, "compression_ratio": 1.6, "no_speech_prob": 1.6552578535264373e-12}, {"id": 47, "seek": 14980, "start": 173.86, "end": 175.06, "text": " The 5 is totally gone.", "tokens": [51568, 440, 1025, 307, 3879, 2780, 13, 51628], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08329114994081128, "compression_ratio": 1.6, "no_speech_prob": 1.6552578535264373e-12}, {"id": 48, "seek": 17506, "start": 175.06, "end": 177.04, "text": " The physical state of the machine has changed.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 4001, 1785, 295, 264, 3479, 575, 3105, 13, 50464], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21599583095974392, "compression_ratio": 1.6371681415929205, "no_speech_prob": 3.090687428208838e-12}, {"id": 49, "seek": 17506, "start": 177.58, "end": 180.3, "text": " The history of that 5 is completely erased from the universe.", "tokens": [50491, 440, 2503, 295, 300, 1025, 307, 2584, 38359, 490, 264, 6445, 13, 50627], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21599583095974392, "compression_ratio": 1.6371681415929205, "no_speech_prob": 3.090687428208838e-12}, {"id": 50, "seek": 17506, "start": 180.74, "end": 183.62, "text": " And the machine only knows its present immediate state.", "tokens": [50649, 400, 264, 3479, 787, 3255, 1080, 1974, 11629, 1785, 13, 50793], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21599583095974392, "compression_ratio": 1.6371681415929205, "no_speech_prob": 3.090687428208838e-12}, {"id": 51, "seek": 17506, "start": 183.88, "end": 189.26, "text": " SpherePop argues that this erasure is the root of our most complex computational failures.", "tokens": [50806, 318, 6605, 38677, 38218, 300, 341, 1189, 2508, 307, 264, 5593, 295, 527, 881, 3997, 28270, 20774, 13, 51075], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21599583095974392, "compression_ratio": 1.6371681415929205, "no_speech_prob": 3.090687428208838e-12}, {"id": 52, "seek": 17506, "start": 190.22, "end": 195.06, "text": " In this new system, that kind of state erasure is mathematically impossible.", "tokens": [51123, 682, 341, 777, 1185, 11, 300, 733, 295, 1785, 1189, 2508, 307, 44003, 6243, 13, 51365], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21599583095974392, "compression_ratio": 1.6371681415929205, "no_speech_prob": 3.090687428208838e-12}, {"id": 53, "seek": 17506, "start": 195.96, "end": 196.64000000000001, "text": " Wait, really?", "tokens": [51410, 3802, 11, 534, 30, 51444], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21599583095974392, "compression_ratio": 1.6371681415929205, "no_speech_prob": 3.090687428208838e-12}, {"id": 54, "seek": 17506, "start": 196.98000000000002, "end": 197.54, "text": " Impossible?", "tokens": [51461, 36808, 30, 51489], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21599583095974392, "compression_ratio": 1.6371681415929205, "no_speech_prob": 3.090687428208838e-12}, {"id": 55, "seek": 17506, "start": 197.76, "end": 198.18, "text": " Impossible.", "tokens": [51500, 36808, 13, 51521], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21599583095974392, "compression_ratio": 1.6371681415929205, "no_speech_prob": 3.090687428208838e-12}, {"id": 56, "seek": 19818, "start": 198.18, "end": 205.06, "text": " Every single proof, every variable assignment, every function evaluation has a permanent history attached to it.", "tokens": [50365, 2048, 2167, 8177, 11, 633, 7006, 15187, 11, 633, 2445, 13344, 575, 257, 10996, 2503, 8570, 281, 309, 13, 50709], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10706270391290838, "compression_ratio": 1.6357827476038338, "no_speech_prob": 1.839641069686926e-12}, {"id": 57, "seek": 19818, "start": 205.82, "end": 208.20000000000002, "text": " Computation is no longer about updating a state.", "tokens": [50747, 37804, 399, 307, 572, 2854, 466, 25113, 257, 1785, 13, 50866], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10706270391290838, "compression_ratio": 1.6357827476038338, "no_speech_prob": 1.839641069686926e-12}, {"id": 58, "seek": 19818, "start": 208.4, "end": 211.84, "text": " It is the permanent accumulation of constructive events.", "tokens": [50876, 467, 307, 264, 10996, 35647, 295, 30223, 3931, 13, 51048], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10706270391290838, "compression_ratio": 1.6357827476038338, "no_speech_prob": 1.839641069686926e-12}, {"id": 59, "seek": 19818, "start": 212.54000000000002, "end": 225.70000000000002, "text": " So if you're listening to this right now, whether you write code for a living or you study formal mathematics or you're just someone who uses a smartphone and wonders why apps still crash in the year 2026, this shifts the entire philosophy of problem solving.", "tokens": [51083, 407, 498, 291, 434, 4764, 281, 341, 558, 586, 11, 1968, 291, 2464, 3089, 337, 257, 2647, 420, 291, 2979, 9860, 18666, 420, 291, 434, 445, 1580, 567, 4960, 257, 13307, 293, 27348, 983, 7733, 920, 8252, 294, 264, 1064, 945, 10880, 11, 341, 19201, 264, 2302, 10675, 295, 1154, 12606, 13, 51741], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10706270391290838, "compression_ratio": 1.6357827476038338, "no_speech_prob": 1.839641069686926e-12}, {"id": 60, "seek": 19818, "start": 225.96, "end": 227.12, "text": " It really does move the goalpost.", "tokens": [51754, 467, 534, 775, 1286, 264, 3387, 23744, 13, 51812], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10706270391290838, "compression_ratio": 1.6357827476038338, "no_speech_prob": 1.839641069686926e-12}, {"id": 61, "seek": 22712, "start": 227.12, "end": 229.86, "text": " Yeah, the focus is no longer what is the final answer.", "tokens": [50365, 865, 11, 264, 1879, 307, 572, 2854, 437, 307, 264, 2572, 1867, 13, 50502], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09774835407733917, "compression_ratio": 1.6067796610169491, "no_speech_prob": 1.5856376541639738e-12}, {"id": 62, "seek": 22712, "start": 230.0, "end": 234.34, "text": " The focus becomes what is the exact unerasable path we took to get here.", "tokens": [50509, 440, 1879, 3643, 437, 307, 264, 1900, 517, 6985, 712, 3100, 321, 1890, 281, 483, 510, 13, 50726], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09774835407733917, "compression_ratio": 1.6067796610169491, "no_speech_prob": 1.5856376541639738e-12}, {"id": 63, "seek": 22712, "start": 234.76, "end": 236.28, "text": " And that path is the crucial element.", "tokens": [50747, 400, 300, 3100, 307, 264, 11462, 4478, 13, 50823], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09774835407733917, "compression_ratio": 1.6067796610169491, "no_speech_prob": 1.5856376541639738e-12}, {"id": 64, "seek": 22712, "start": 236.56, "end": 242.96, "text": " It's not just a log file that a tired software engineer reads at like 3.8 AM trying to figure out why a server went down.", "tokens": [50837, 467, 311, 406, 445, 257, 3565, 3991, 300, 257, 5868, 4722, 11403, 15700, 412, 411, 805, 13, 23, 6475, 1382, 281, 2573, 484, 983, 257, 7154, 1437, 760, 13, 51157], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09774835407733917, "compression_ratio": 1.6067796610169491, "no_speech_prob": 1.5856376541639738e-12}, {"id": 65, "seek": 22712, "start": 243.1, "end": 243.62, "text": " Right, right.", "tokens": [51164, 1779, 11, 558, 13, 51190], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09774835407733917, "compression_ratio": 1.6067796610169491, "no_speech_prob": 1.5856376541639738e-12}, {"id": 66, "seek": 22712, "start": 243.82, "end": 245.86, "text": " In SpherePop, the path is the math.", "tokens": [51200, 682, 318, 6605, 38677, 11, 264, 3100, 307, 264, 5221, 13, 51302], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09774835407733917, "compression_ratio": 1.6067796610169491, "no_speech_prob": 1.5856376541639738e-12}, {"id": 67, "seek": 22712, "start": 246.42000000000002, "end": 252.14000000000001, "text": " The provenance of the data where it came from and how it was transformed is elevated to a first class mathematical object.", "tokens": [51330, 440, 12785, 719, 295, 264, 1412, 689, 309, 1361, 490, 293, 577, 309, 390, 16894, 307, 23457, 281, 257, 700, 1508, 18894, 2657, 13, 51616], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09774835407733917, "compression_ratio": 1.6067796610169491, "no_speech_prob": 1.5856376541639738e-12}, {"id": 68, "seek": 22712, "start": 252.3, "end": 253.62, "text": " That is wild.", "tokens": [51624, 663, 307, 4868, 13, 51690], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09774835407733917, "compression_ratio": 1.6067796610169491, "no_speech_prob": 1.5856376541639738e-12}, {"id": 69, "seek": 25362, "start": 253.62, "end": 258.34000000000003, "text": " To understand this, look at traditional type theory, like the calculus of constructions.", "tokens": [50365, 1407, 1223, 341, 11, 574, 412, 5164, 2010, 5261, 11, 411, 264, 33400, 295, 7690, 626, 13, 50601], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13421685767896246, "compression_ratio": 1.6583333333333334, "no_speech_prob": 1.6619905321771378e-12}, {"id": 70, "seek": 25362, "start": 258.96, "end": 263.12, "text": " When mathematicians or programmers set up a problem, they use something called a context.", "tokens": [50632, 1133, 32811, 2567, 420, 41504, 992, 493, 257, 1154, 11, 436, 764, 746, 1219, 257, 4319, 13, 50840], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13421685767896246, "compression_ratio": 1.6583333333333334, "no_speech_prob": 1.6619905321771378e-12}, {"id": 71, "seek": 25362, "start": 263.42, "end": 264.46, "text": " A context, okay.", "tokens": [50855, 316, 4319, 11, 1392, 13, 50907], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13421685767896246, "compression_ratio": 1.6583333333333334, "no_speech_prob": 1.6619905321771378e-12}, {"id": 72, "seek": 25362, "start": 264.52, "end": 267.6, "text": " Yeah, and a context is basically an unordered collection of assumptions.", "tokens": [50910, 865, 11, 293, 257, 4319, 307, 1936, 364, 517, 765, 4073, 5765, 295, 17695, 13, 51064], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13421685767896246, "compression_ratio": 1.6583333333333334, "no_speech_prob": 1.6619905321771378e-12}, {"id": 73, "seek": 25362, "start": 268.24, "end": 274.08, "text": " You assume A is true, you assume B is true, and the system treats them like a bag of loose marbles.", "tokens": [51096, 509, 6552, 316, 307, 2074, 11, 291, 6552, 363, 307, 2074, 11, 293, 264, 1185, 19566, 552, 411, 257, 3411, 295, 9612, 1849, 8806, 13, 51388], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13421685767896246, "compression_ratio": 1.6583333333333334, "no_speech_prob": 1.6619905321771378e-12}, {"id": 74, "seek": 25362, "start": 274.22, "end": 275.7, "text": " Just rolling around in there.", "tokens": [51395, 1449, 9439, 926, 294, 456, 13, 51469], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13421685767896246, "compression_ratio": 1.6583333333333334, "no_speech_prob": 1.6619905321771378e-12}, {"id": 75, "seek": 27570, "start": 275.7, "end": 276.18, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50365, 7587, 13, 50389], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16713034431889373, "compression_ratio": 1.6226415094339623, "no_speech_prob": 1.3406755089775957e-12}, {"id": 76, "seek": 27570, "start": 276.62, "end": 280.76, "text": " It doesn't care if you pulled marble A out first or marble B out first.", "tokens": [50411, 467, 1177, 380, 1127, 498, 291, 7373, 26844, 316, 484, 700, 420, 26844, 363, 484, 700, 13, 50618], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16713034431889373, "compression_ratio": 1.6226415094339623, "no_speech_prob": 1.3406755089775957e-12}, {"id": 77, "seek": 27570, "start": 281.56, "end": 287.26, "text": " SpherePop entirely replaces these unordered contexts with what Fliction calls histories.", "tokens": [50658, 318, 6605, 38677, 7696, 46734, 613, 517, 765, 4073, 30628, 365, 437, 3235, 4105, 5498, 30631, 13, 50943], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16713034431889373, "compression_ratio": 1.6226415094339623, "no_speech_prob": 1.3406755089775957e-12}, {"id": 78, "seek": 27570, "start": 287.8, "end": 292.0, "text": " And a history is very specifically an ordered sequence of admissible events, right?", "tokens": [50970, 400, 257, 2503, 307, 588, 4682, 364, 8866, 8310, 295, 5910, 41073, 3931, 11, 558, 30, 51180], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16713034431889373, "compression_ratio": 1.6226415094339623, "no_speech_prob": 1.3406755089775957e-12}, {"id": 79, "seek": 27570, "start": 292.21999999999997, "end": 293.7, "text": " The sequence intrinsically matters.", "tokens": [51191, 440, 8310, 28621, 984, 7001, 13, 51265], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16713034431889373, "compression_ratio": 1.6226415094339623, "no_speech_prob": 1.3406755089775957e-12}, {"id": 80, "seek": 27570, "start": 293.91999999999996, "end": 295.5, "text": " It governs the entire architecture.", "tokens": [51276, 467, 1980, 82, 264, 2302, 9482, 13, 51355], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16713034431889373, "compression_ratio": 1.6226415094339623, "no_speech_prob": 1.3406755089775957e-12}, {"id": 81, "seek": 27570, "start": 296.06, "end": 299.98, "text": " Fliction introduces this concept called the axiom of historical monotonicity.", "tokens": [51383, 3235, 4105, 31472, 341, 3410, 1219, 264, 6360, 72, 298, 295, 8584, 1108, 310, 11630, 507, 13, 51579], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16713034431889373, "compression_ratio": 1.6226415094339623, "no_speech_prob": 1.3406755089775957e-12}, {"id": 82, "seek": 27570, "start": 300.12, "end": 302.15999999999997, "text": " Okay, that sounds intense.", "tokens": [51586, 1033, 11, 300, 3263, 9447, 13, 51688], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16713034431889373, "compression_ratio": 1.6226415094339623, "no_speech_prob": 1.3406755089775957e-12}, {"id": 83, "seek": 30216, "start": 302.16, "end": 308.78000000000003, "text": " It does, but it just dictates that every time you extend a history, you must preserve the complete provenance of the previous history.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 775, 11, 457, 309, 445, 12569, 1024, 300, 633, 565, 291, 10101, 257, 2503, 11, 291, 1633, 15665, 264, 3566, 12785, 719, 295, 264, 3894, 2503, 13, 50696], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12779926786235735, "compression_ratio": 1.727626459143969, "no_speech_prob": 1.3940813564303212e-12}, {"id": 84, "seek": 30216, "start": 309.24, "end": 311.24, "text": " Let's translate that out of academic speak.", "tokens": [50719, 961, 311, 13799, 300, 484, 295, 7778, 1710, 13, 50819], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12779926786235735, "compression_ratio": 1.727626459143969, "no_speech_prob": 1.3940813564303212e-12}, {"id": 85, "seek": 30216, "start": 311.36, "end": 311.8, "text": " Please do.", "tokens": [50825, 2555, 360, 13, 50847], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12779926786235735, "compression_ratio": 1.727626459143969, "no_speech_prob": 1.3940813564303212e-12}, {"id": 86, "seek": 30216, "start": 312.16, "end": 321.90000000000003, "text": " If event one happens and then event two happens, the mathematical reality of that sequence is completely different from event two happening followed by event one.", "tokens": [50865, 759, 2280, 472, 2314, 293, 550, 2280, 732, 2314, 11, 264, 18894, 4103, 295, 300, 8310, 307, 2584, 819, 490, 2280, 732, 2737, 6263, 538, 2280, 472, 13, 51352], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12779926786235735, "compression_ratio": 1.727626459143969, "no_speech_prob": 1.3940813564303212e-12}, {"id": 87, "seek": 30216, "start": 322.74, "end": 324.88, "text": " Order is not just a side effect of time.", "tokens": [51394, 16321, 307, 406, 445, 257, 1252, 1802, 295, 565, 13, 51501], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12779926786235735, "compression_ratio": 1.727626459143969, "no_speech_prob": 1.3940813564303212e-12}, {"id": 88, "seek": 30216, "start": 325.3, "end": 327.98, "text": " Order is a structural property of the math itself.", "tokens": [51522, 16321, 307, 257, 15067, 4707, 295, 264, 5221, 2564, 13, 51656], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12779926786235735, "compression_ratio": 1.727626459143969, "no_speech_prob": 1.3940813564303212e-12}, {"id": 89, "seek": 32798, "start": 327.98, "end": 328.74, "text": " I see.", "tokens": [50365, 286, 536, 13, 50403], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13328242301940918, "compression_ratio": 1.6366459627329193, "no_speech_prob": 1.853388319553173e-12}, {"id": 90, "seek": 32798, "start": 329.06, "end": 331.40000000000003, "text": " Let me try to visualize this for you, the listener.", "tokens": [50419, 961, 385, 853, 281, 23273, 341, 337, 291, 11, 264, 31569, 13, 50536], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13328242301940918, "compression_ratio": 1.6366459627329193, "no_speech_prob": 1.853388319553173e-12}, {"id": 91, "seek": 32798, "start": 332.06, "end": 339.48, "text": " Compare traditional computing to a giant whiteboard where you walk up, you write down a number, you do some arithmetic.", "tokens": [50569, 48523, 5164, 15866, 281, 257, 7410, 2418, 3787, 689, 291, 1792, 493, 11, 291, 2464, 760, 257, 1230, 11, 291, 360, 512, 42973, 13, 50940], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13328242301940918, "compression_ratio": 1.6366459627329193, "no_speech_prob": 1.853388319553173e-12}, {"id": 92, "seek": 32798, "start": 339.90000000000003, "end": 340.1, "text": " Where?", "tokens": [50961, 2305, 30, 50971], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13328242301940918, "compression_ratio": 1.6366459627329193, "no_speech_prob": 1.853388319553173e-12}, {"id": 93, "seek": 32798, "start": 340.6, "end": 345.36, "text": " And when you run out of space on the board, you grab an eraser, wipe out the old numbers, and write the new ones.", "tokens": [50996, 400, 562, 291, 1190, 484, 295, 1901, 322, 264, 3150, 11, 291, 4444, 364, 46018, 11, 14082, 484, 264, 1331, 3547, 11, 293, 2464, 264, 777, 2306, 13, 51234], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13328242301940918, "compression_ratio": 1.6366459627329193, "no_speech_prob": 1.853388319553173e-12}, {"id": 94, "seek": 32798, "start": 345.42, "end": 346.20000000000005, "text": " Right, exactly.", "tokens": [51237, 1779, 11, 2293, 13, 51276], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13328242301940918, "compression_ratio": 1.6366459627329193, "no_speech_prob": 1.853388319553173e-12}, {"id": 95, "seek": 32798, "start": 346.58000000000004, "end": 348.68, "text": " That is our current mutable state architecture.", "tokens": [51295, 663, 307, 527, 2190, 5839, 712, 1785, 9482, 13, 51400], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13328242301940918, "compression_ratio": 1.6366459627329193, "no_speech_prob": 1.853388319553173e-12}, {"id": 96, "seek": 32798, "start": 349.04, "end": 351.24, "text": " The whiteboard only ever shows the present moment.", "tokens": [51418, 440, 2418, 3787, 787, 1562, 3110, 264, 1974, 1623, 13, 51528], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13328242301940918, "compression_ratio": 1.6366459627329193, "no_speech_prob": 1.853388319553173e-12}, {"id": 97, "seek": 32798, "start": 352.02000000000004, "end": 356.54, "text": " Now, compare spherepop to writing with a permanent fountain pen in a bound leather journal.", "tokens": [51567, 823, 11, 6794, 16687, 13872, 281, 3579, 365, 257, 10996, 29451, 3435, 294, 257, 5472, 12821, 6708, 13, 51793], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13328242301940918, "compression_ratio": 1.6366459627329193, "no_speech_prob": 1.853388319553173e-12}, {"id": 98, "seek": 32798, "start": 356.54, "end": 357.70000000000005, "text": " I love that analogy.", "tokens": [51793, 286, 959, 300, 21663, 13, 51851], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13328242301940918, "compression_ratio": 1.6366459627329193, "no_speech_prob": 1.853388319553173e-12}, {"id": 99, "seek": 35798, "start": 357.98, "end": 371.1, "text": " Yeah, you can cross a line out, you can draw a long arrow linking a thought on page two to a conclusion on page 40, but you can never physically remove the ink, you can never tear a page out of the spine, the journal is monotonic, it only grows.", "tokens": [50365, 865, 11, 291, 393, 3278, 257, 1622, 484, 11, 291, 393, 2642, 257, 938, 11610, 25775, 257, 1194, 322, 3028, 732, 281, 257, 10063, 322, 3028, 3356, 11, 457, 291, 393, 1128, 9762, 4159, 264, 11276, 11, 291, 393, 1128, 12556, 257, 3028, 484, 295, 264, 15395, 11, 264, 6708, 307, 1108, 310, 11630, 11, 309, 787, 13156, 13, 51021], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.062079225977261863, "compression_ratio": 1.6330645161290323, "no_speech_prob": 1.7080411520917216e-12}, {"id": 100, "seek": 35798, "start": 371.38, "end": 378.70000000000005, "text": " While that journal analogy captures the permanence beautifully, what's fascinating here is that it also implies something crucial about identity.", "tokens": [51035, 3987, 300, 6708, 21663, 27986, 264, 8105, 655, 16525, 11, 437, 311, 10343, 510, 307, 300, 309, 611, 18779, 746, 11462, 466, 6575, 13, 51401], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.062079225977261863, "compression_ratio": 1.6330645161290323, "no_speech_prob": 1.7080411520917216e-12}, {"id": 101, "seek": 35798, "start": 379.02000000000004, "end": 380.06, "text": " Okay, how so?", "tokens": [51417, 1033, 11, 577, 370, 30, 51469], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.062079225977261863, "compression_ratio": 1.6330645161290323, "no_speech_prob": 1.7080411520917216e-12}, {"id": 102, "seek": 38006, "start": 380.06, "end": 384.72, "text": " In standard mathematics, identity is usually based on what things look like at the end of the calculation.", "tokens": [50365, 682, 3832, 18666, 11, 6575, 307, 2673, 2361, 322, 437, 721, 574, 411, 412, 264, 917, 295, 264, 17108, 13, 50598], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13366913361982866, "compression_ratio": 1.6944444444444444, "no_speech_prob": 1.5370880566620282e-12}, {"id": 103, "seek": 38006, "start": 385.56, "end": 390.32, "text": " Let's say you have a function that calculates a user's account balance, and it outputs the number 42.", "tokens": [50640, 961, 311, 584, 291, 362, 257, 2445, 300, 4322, 1024, 257, 4195, 311, 2696, 4772, 11, 293, 309, 23930, 264, 1230, 14034, 13, 50878], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13366913361982866, "compression_ratio": 1.6944444444444444, "no_speech_prob": 1.5370880566620282e-12}, {"id": 104, "seek": 38006, "start": 390.56, "end": 391.34, "text": " Okay, 42.", "tokens": [50890, 1033, 11, 14034, 13, 50929], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13366913361982866, "compression_ratio": 1.6944444444444444, "no_speech_prob": 1.5370880566620282e-12}, {"id": 105, "seek": 38006, "start": 391.62, "end": 396.88, "text": " Then, you have a completely different function that calculates the temperature reading, and it also outputs 42.", "tokens": [50943, 1396, 11, 291, 362, 257, 2584, 819, 2445, 300, 4322, 1024, 264, 4292, 3760, 11, 293, 309, 611, 23930, 14034, 13, 51206], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13366913361982866, "compression_ratio": 1.6944444444444444, "no_speech_prob": 1.5370880566620282e-12}, {"id": 106, "seek": 38006, "start": 397.54, "end": 399.84000000000003, "text": " In traditional math, 42 equals 42.", "tokens": [51239, 682, 5164, 5221, 11, 14034, 6915, 14034, 13, 51354], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13366913361982866, "compression_ratio": 1.6944444444444444, "no_speech_prob": 1.5370880566620282e-12}, {"id": 107, "seek": 38006, "start": 400.24, "end": 401.76, "text": " We call this extensional equality.", "tokens": [51374, 492, 818, 341, 1279, 11075, 14949, 13, 51450], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13366913361982866, "compression_ratio": 1.6944444444444444, "no_speech_prob": 1.5370880566620282e-12}, {"id": 108, "seek": 38006, "start": 402.06, "end": 402.62, "text": " Makes sense.", "tokens": [51465, 25245, 2020, 13, 51493], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13366913361982866, "compression_ratio": 1.6944444444444444, "no_speech_prob": 1.5370880566620282e-12}, {"id": 109, "seek": 38006, "start": 402.74, "end": 403.92, "text": " A 42 is a 42.", "tokens": [51499, 316, 14034, 307, 257, 14034, 13, 51558], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13366913361982866, "compression_ratio": 1.6944444444444444, "no_speech_prob": 1.5370880566620282e-12}, {"id": 110, "seek": 40392, "start": 403.92, "end": 409.38, "text": " But in Sphere Pop, identity is a dynamic concept governed by the provenance we just talked about.", "tokens": [50365, 583, 294, 318, 6605, 10215, 11, 6575, 307, 257, 8546, 3410, 35529, 538, 264, 12785, 719, 321, 445, 2825, 466, 13, 50638], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16604224971083345, "compression_ratio": 1.4615384615384615, "no_speech_prob": 1.4322037479586047e-12}, {"id": 111, "seek": 40392, "start": 409.7, "end": 419.32, "text": " If those two 42s have different histories, if they were written on different pages of the journal under different circumstances, they're fundamentally distinct mathematical objects.", "tokens": [50654, 759, 729, 732, 14034, 82, 362, 819, 30631, 11, 498, 436, 645, 3720, 322, 819, 7183, 295, 264, 6708, 833, 819, 9121, 11, 436, 434, 17879, 10644, 18894, 6565, 13, 51135], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16604224971083345, "compression_ratio": 1.4615384615384615, "no_speech_prob": 1.4322037479586047e-12}, {"id": 112, "seek": 40392, "start": 419.58000000000004, "end": 420.04, "text": " Whoa.", "tokens": [51148, 7521, 13, 51171], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16604224971083345, "compression_ratio": 1.4615384615384615, "no_speech_prob": 1.4322037479586047e-12}, {"id": 113, "seek": 42004, "start": 420.04, "end": 424.56, "text": " Yeah, their identity is inextricably tied to their origin story.", "tokens": [50365, 865, 11, 641, 6575, 307, 294, 3828, 1341, 1188, 9601, 281, 641, 4957, 1657, 13, 50591], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1117580114905514, "compression_ratio": 1.6333333333333333, "no_speech_prob": 1.478202651429561e-12}, {"id": 114, "seek": 42004, "start": 424.72, "end": 432.6, "text": " Okay, I have to throw a flag on the play here because my immediate reaction to that is, isn't keeping a record of absolutely everything wildly inefficient.", "tokens": [50599, 1033, 11, 286, 362, 281, 3507, 257, 7166, 322, 264, 862, 510, 570, 452, 11629, 5480, 281, 300, 307, 11, 1943, 380, 5145, 257, 2136, 295, 3122, 1203, 34731, 43495, 13, 50993], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1117580114905514, "compression_ratio": 1.6333333333333333, "no_speech_prob": 1.478202651429561e-12}, {"id": 115, "seek": 42004, "start": 432.90000000000003, "end": 434.28000000000003, "text": " Sounds like a nightmare for memory, right?", "tokens": [51008, 14576, 411, 257, 18724, 337, 4675, 11, 558, 30, 51077], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1117580114905514, "compression_ratio": 1.6333333333333333, "no_speech_prob": 1.478202651429561e-12}, {"id": 116, "seek": 42004, "start": 434.36, "end": 434.8, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [51081, 7587, 13, 51103], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1117580114905514, "compression_ratio": 1.6333333333333333, "no_speech_prob": 1.478202651429561e-12}, {"id": 117, "seek": 42004, "start": 435.20000000000005, "end": 442.76, "text": " If I'm writing an application that just calculates the sales tax on a shopping cart, why in the world do I care about the origin story of the number 42?", "tokens": [51123, 759, 286, 478, 3579, 364, 3861, 300, 445, 4322, 1024, 264, 5763, 3366, 322, 257, 8688, 5467, 11, 983, 294, 264, 1002, 360, 286, 1127, 466, 264, 4957, 1657, 295, 264, 1230, 14034, 30, 51501], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1117580114905514, "compression_ratio": 1.6333333333333333, "no_speech_prob": 1.478202651429561e-12}, {"id": 118, "seek": 42004, "start": 443.26, "end": 445.92, "text": " Why carry around the baggage of every microstep?", "tokens": [51526, 1545, 3985, 926, 264, 41567, 295, 633, 3123, 27494, 595, 30, 51659], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1117580114905514, "compression_ratio": 1.6333333333333333, "no_speech_prob": 1.478202651429561e-12}, {"id": 119, "seek": 42004, "start": 445.96000000000004, "end": 449.0, "text": " It feels like we're hoarding data for the sake of hoarding data.", "tokens": [51661, 467, 3417, 411, 321, 434, 45940, 278, 1412, 337, 264, 9717, 295, 45940, 278, 1412, 13, 51813], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1117580114905514, "compression_ratio": 1.6333333333333333, "no_speech_prob": 1.478202651429561e-12}, {"id": 120, "seek": 44900, "start": 449.0, "end": 451.42, "text": " It does sound incredibly heavy at first glance.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 775, 1626, 6252, 4676, 412, 700, 21094, 13, 50486], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18011672408492477, "compression_ratio": 1.5865384615384615, "no_speech_prob": 1.2893169604871746e-12}, {"id": 121, "seek": 44900, "start": 452.12, "end": 456.62, "text": " But that baggage naturally solves some of the most catastrophic problems in modern engineering.", "tokens": [50521, 583, 300, 41567, 8195, 39890, 512, 295, 264, 881, 34915, 2740, 294, 4363, 7043, 13, 50746], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18011672408492477, "compression_ratio": 1.5865384615384615, "no_speech_prob": 1.2893169604871746e-12}, {"id": 122, "seek": 44900, "start": 457.54, "end": 464.14, "text": " Considered distributed systems, concurrent proof construction, or event sourcing in global databases.", "tokens": [50792, 17416, 292, 12631, 3652, 11, 37702, 8177, 6435, 11, 420, 2280, 11006, 2175, 294, 4338, 22380, 13, 51122], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18011672408492477, "compression_ratio": 1.5865384615384615, "no_speech_prob": 1.2893169604871746e-12}, {"id": 123, "seek": 44900, "start": 464.16, "end": 465.16, "text": " Those are big systems.", "tokens": [51123, 3950, 366, 955, 3652, 13, 51173], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18011672408492477, "compression_ratio": 1.5865384615384615, "no_speech_prob": 1.2893169604871746e-12}, {"id": 124, "seek": 44900, "start": 465.3, "end": 466.14, "text": " Massive systems.", "tokens": [51180, 10482, 488, 3652, 13, 51222], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18011672408492477, "compression_ratio": 1.5865384615384615, "no_speech_prob": 1.2893169604871746e-12}, {"id": 125, "seek": 44900, "start": 466.3, "end": 475.7, "text": " Right now, tech companies spend billions of dollars building massive convoluted infrastructure just to figure out how a system arrived at a certain broken state.", "tokens": [51230, 1779, 586, 11, 7553, 3431, 3496, 17375, 295, 3808, 2390, 5994, 3754, 2308, 292, 6896, 445, 281, 2573, 484, 577, 257, 1185, 6678, 412, 257, 1629, 5463, 1785, 13, 51700], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18011672408492477, "compression_ratio": 1.5865384615384615, "no_speech_prob": 1.2893169604871746e-12}, {"id": 126, "seek": 44900, "start": 475.84, "end": 477.66, "text": " Oh, because the whiteboard got erased.", "tokens": [51707, 876, 11, 570, 264, 2418, 3787, 658, 38359, 13, 51798], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18011672408492477, "compression_ratio": 1.5865384615384615, "no_speech_prob": 1.2893169604871746e-12}, {"id": 127, "seek": 44900, "start": 477.94, "end": 478.5, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [51812, 7587, 13, 51840], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18011672408492477, "compression_ratio": 1.5865384615384615, "no_speech_prob": 1.2893169604871746e-12}, {"id": 128, "seek": 47850, "start": 478.5, "end": 485.34, "text": " When a global financial clearinghouse drops a transaction, it's because the state was overwritten and the context was lost.", "tokens": [50365, 1133, 257, 4338, 4669, 23937, 6410, 11438, 257, 14425, 11, 309, 311, 570, 264, 1785, 390, 670, 26859, 293, 264, 4319, 390, 2731, 13, 50707], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1747870222430363, "compression_ratio": 1.6133828996282529, "no_speech_prob": 1.6106123596273947e-12}, {"id": 129, "seek": 47850, "start": 485.54, "end": 485.6, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [50717, 865, 13, 50720], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1747870222430363, "compression_ratio": 1.6133828996282529, "no_speech_prob": 1.6106123596273947e-12}, {"id": 130, "seek": 47850, "start": 485.72, "end": 488.16, "text": " They have to forensically reconstruct the crime scene.", "tokens": [50726, 814, 362, 281, 32034, 984, 31499, 264, 7206, 4145, 13, 50848], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1747870222430363, "compression_ratio": 1.6133828996282529, "no_speech_prob": 1.6106123596273947e-12}, {"id": 131, "seek": 47850, "start": 488.28, "end": 490.98, "text": " Yeah, like piecing together shredded documents.", "tokens": [50854, 865, 11, 411, 1730, 2175, 1214, 39091, 8512, 13, 50989], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1747870222430363, "compression_ratio": 1.6133828996282529, "no_speech_prob": 1.6106123596273947e-12}, {"id": 132, "seek": 47850, "start": 491.24, "end": 496.56, "text": " In SpherePop, the exact path is preserved at the foundational level of the code.", "tokens": [51002, 682, 318, 6605, 38677, 11, 264, 1900, 3100, 307, 22242, 412, 264, 32195, 1496, 295, 264, 3089, 13, 51268], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1747870222430363, "compression_ratio": 1.6133828996282529, "no_speech_prob": 1.6106123596273947e-12}, {"id": 133, "seek": 47850, "start": 497.0, "end": 500.86, "text": " You don't need to build an external logging system to watch the code run.", "tokens": [51290, 509, 500, 380, 643, 281, 1322, 364, 8320, 27991, 1185, 281, 1159, 264, 3089, 1190, 13, 51483], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1747870222430363, "compression_ratio": 1.6133828996282529, "no_speech_prob": 1.6106123596273947e-12}, {"id": 134, "seek": 47850, "start": 501.2, "end": 503.86, "text": " The code itself is a self-documenting history.", "tokens": [51500, 440, 3089, 2564, 307, 257, 2698, 12, 67, 30439, 278, 2503, 13, 51633], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1747870222430363, "compression_ratio": 1.6133828996282529, "no_speech_prob": 1.6106123596273947e-12}, {"id": 135, "seek": 50386, "start": 503.86, "end": 507.24, "text": " The debugging information isn't an afterthought.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 45592, 1589, 1943, 380, 364, 934, 43135, 13, 50534], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2628593237503715, "compression_ratio": 1.3228346456692914, "no_speech_prob": 2.2364172146127625e-12}, {"id": 136, "seek": 50386, "start": 507.24, "end": 508.52000000000004, "text": " It is the computation.", "tokens": [50534, 467, 307, 264, 24903, 13, 50598], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2628593237503715, "compression_ratio": 1.3228346456692914, "no_speech_prob": 2.2364172146127625e-12}, {"id": 137, "seek": 50386, "start": 508.52000000000004, "end": 509.68, "text": " Okay, that makes sense.", "tokens": [50598, 1033, 11, 300, 1669, 2020, 13, 50656], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2628593237503715, "compression_ratio": 1.3228346456692914, "no_speech_prob": 2.2364172146127625e-12}, {"id": 138, "seek": 50386, "start": 509.68, "end": 513.48, "text": " We're moving from a culture of overwriting to a culture of accumulating.", "tokens": [50656, 492, 434, 2684, 490, 257, 3713, 295, 670, 19868, 281, 257, 3713, 295, 12989, 12162, 13, 50846], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2628593237503715, "compression_ratio": 1.3228346456692914, "no_speech_prob": 2.2364172146127625e-12}, {"id": 139, "seek": 51348, "start": 513.48, "end": 520.02, "text": " So, if this permanent journal is just constantly filling up with ink, what are the actual words we are writing?", "tokens": [50365, 407, 11, 498, 341, 10996, 6708, 307, 445, 6460, 10623, 493, 365, 11276, 11, 437, 366, 264, 3539, 2283, 321, 366, 3579, 30, 50692], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20803506374359132, "compression_ratio": 1.48868778280543, "no_speech_prob": 1.935172942030272e-12}, {"id": 140, "seek": 51348, "start": 520.16, "end": 520.3000000000001, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50699, 1779, 13, 50706], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20803506374359132, "compression_ratio": 1.48868778280543, "no_speech_prob": 1.935172942030272e-12}, {"id": 141, "seek": 51348, "start": 520.34, "end": 521.02, "text": " What's the vocabulary?", "tokens": [50708, 708, 311, 264, 19864, 30, 50742], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20803506374359132, "compression_ratio": 1.48868778280543, "no_speech_prob": 1.935172942030272e-12}, {"id": 142, "seek": 51348, "start": 521.36, "end": 521.54, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [50759, 865, 13, 50768], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20803506374359132, "compression_ratio": 1.48868778280543, "no_speech_prob": 1.935172942030272e-12}, {"id": 143, "seek": 51348, "start": 522.0, "end": 524.08, "text": " Flexion outlines a minimal event algebra.", "tokens": [50791, 29208, 313, 40125, 257, 13206, 2280, 21989, 13, 50895], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20803506374359132, "compression_ratio": 1.48868778280543, "no_speech_prob": 1.935172942030272e-12}, {"id": 144, "seek": 51348, "start": 524.94, "end": 527.88, "text": " There are essentially five primitive historical operations.", "tokens": [50938, 821, 366, 4476, 1732, 28540, 8584, 7705, 13, 51085], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20803506374359132, "compression_ratio": 1.48868778280543, "no_speech_prob": 1.935172942030272e-12}, {"id": 145, "seek": 51348, "start": 528.44, "end": 532.08, "text": " Think of these as the five verbs that build the entire universe of this system.", "tokens": [51113, 6557, 295, 613, 382, 264, 1732, 30051, 300, 1322, 264, 2302, 6445, 295, 341, 1185, 13, 51295], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20803506374359132, "compression_ratio": 1.48868778280543, "no_speech_prob": 1.935172942030272e-12}, {"id": 146, "seek": 53208, "start": 532.08, "end": 535.88, "text": " Pop, Refuse, Bind, Collapse, and Meld.", "tokens": [50365, 10215, 11, 16957, 438, 11, 363, 471, 11, 4586, 11145, 11, 293, 376, 5957, 13, 50555], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16378708808652817, "compression_ratio": 1.6177474402730376, "no_speech_prob": 1.4213533778770215e-12}, {"id": 147, "seek": 53208, "start": 536.12, "end": 539.32, "text": " These five primitive constructors are the alphabet of SpherePop.", "tokens": [50567, 1981, 1732, 28540, 7690, 830, 366, 264, 23339, 295, 318, 6605, 38677, 13, 50727], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16378708808652817, "compression_ratio": 1.6177474402730376, "no_speech_prob": 1.4213533778770215e-12}, {"id": 148, "seek": 53208, "start": 540.0, "end": 546.1800000000001, "text": " Rather than just defining them in abstract terms, let's look at how they actually operate when a system is trying to accomplish a goal.", "tokens": [50761, 16571, 813, 445, 17827, 552, 294, 12649, 2115, 11, 718, 311, 574, 412, 577, 436, 767, 9651, 562, 257, 1185, 307, 1382, 281, 9021, 257, 3387, 13, 51070], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16378708808652817, "compression_ratio": 1.6177474402730376, "no_speech_prob": 1.4213533778770215e-12}, {"id": 149, "seek": 53208, "start": 546.4000000000001, "end": 547.08, "text": " Let's start with Pop.", "tokens": [51081, 961, 311, 722, 365, 10215, 13, 51115], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16378708808652817, "compression_ratio": 1.6177474402730376, "no_speech_prob": 1.4213533778770215e-12}, {"id": 150, "seek": 53208, "start": 547.2, "end": 547.6800000000001, "text": " Okay, Pop.", "tokens": [51121, 1033, 11, 10215, 13, 51145], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16378708808652817, "compression_ratio": 1.6177474402730376, "no_speech_prob": 1.4213533778770215e-12}, {"id": 151, "seek": 53208, "start": 548.08, "end": 551.2800000000001, "text": " During any computation, a system usually faces a branching path.", "tokens": [51165, 6842, 604, 24903, 11, 257, 1185, 2673, 8475, 257, 9819, 278, 3100, 13, 51325], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16378708808652817, "compression_ratio": 1.6177474402730376, "no_speech_prob": 1.4213533778770215e-12}, {"id": 152, "seek": 53208, "start": 551.62, "end": 553.6, "text": " There are several admissible continuations.", "tokens": [51342, 821, 366, 2940, 5910, 41073, 2993, 763, 13, 51441], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16378708808652817, "compression_ratio": 1.6177474402730376, "no_speech_prob": 1.4213533778770215e-12}, {"id": 153, "seek": 53208, "start": 553.88, "end": 557.36, "text": " The Pop operation explicitly records the choice of one of those branches.", "tokens": [51455, 440, 10215, 6916, 20803, 7724, 264, 3922, 295, 472, 295, 729, 14770, 13, 51629], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16378708808652817, "compression_ratio": 1.6177474402730376, "no_speech_prob": 1.4213533778770215e-12}, {"id": 154, "seek": 53208, "start": 557.62, "end": 558.44, "text": " Let's ground this.", "tokens": [51642, 961, 311, 2727, 341, 13, 51683], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16378708808652817, "compression_ratio": 1.6177474402730376, "no_speech_prob": 1.4213533778770215e-12}, {"id": 155, "seek": 55844, "start": 558.44, "end": 561.9200000000001, "text": " Imagine an algorithm routing a delivery drone.", "tokens": [50365, 11739, 364, 9284, 32722, 257, 8982, 13852, 13, 50539], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14895576238632202, "compression_ratio": 1.679054054054054, "no_speech_prob": 1.5984588869547012e-12}, {"id": 156, "seek": 55844, "start": 562.32, "end": 565.6, "text": " The drone comes to an intersection and can turn north or east.", "tokens": [50559, 440, 13852, 1487, 281, 364, 15236, 293, 393, 1261, 6830, 420, 10648, 13, 50723], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14895576238632202, "compression_ratio": 1.679054054054054, "no_speech_prob": 1.5984588869547012e-12}, {"id": 157, "seek": 55844, "start": 566.0200000000001, "end": 573.1400000000001, "text": " In a normal system, the code just evaluates turn north, executes it, and overwrites the drone's coordinate state.", "tokens": [50744, 682, 257, 2710, 1185, 11, 264, 3089, 445, 6133, 1024, 1261, 6830, 11, 4454, 1819, 309, 11, 293, 670, 86, 30931, 264, 13852, 311, 15670, 1785, 13, 51100], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14895576238632202, "compression_ratio": 1.679054054054054, "no_speech_prob": 1.5984588869547012e-12}, {"id": 158, "seek": 55844, "start": 573.5600000000001, "end": 575.5, "text": " And the fact that east was an option is forgotten.", "tokens": [51121, 400, 264, 1186, 300, 10648, 390, 364, 3614, 307, 11832, 13, 51218], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14895576238632202, "compression_ratio": 1.679054054054054, "no_speech_prob": 1.5984588869547012e-12}, {"id": 159, "seek": 55844, "start": 575.86, "end": 576.1800000000001, "text": " Completely.", "tokens": [51236, 39978, 13, 51252], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14895576238632202, "compression_ratio": 1.679054054054054, "no_speech_prob": 1.5984588869547012e-12}, {"id": 160, "seek": 55844, "start": 576.6, "end": 576.82, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51273, 1779, 13, 51284], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14895576238632202, "compression_ratio": 1.679054054054054, "no_speech_prob": 1.5984588869547012e-12}, {"id": 161, "seek": 55844, "start": 577.1600000000001, "end": 580.0200000000001, "text": " But in SpherePop, the system executes a Pop event.", "tokens": [51301, 583, 294, 318, 6605, 38677, 11, 264, 1185, 4454, 1819, 257, 10215, 2280, 13, 51444], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14895576238632202, "compression_ratio": 1.679054054054054, "no_speech_prob": 1.5984588869547012e-12}, {"id": 162, "seek": 55844, "start": 580.4200000000001, "end": 582.0600000000001, "text": " It doesn't just silently move the drone.", "tokens": [51464, 467, 1177, 380, 445, 40087, 1286, 264, 13852, 13, 51546], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14895576238632202, "compression_ratio": 1.679054054054054, "no_speech_prob": 1.5984588869547012e-12}, {"id": 163, "seek": 55844, "start": 582.34, "end": 586.72, "text": " It permanently logs the commitment to the northern branch into the math itself.", "tokens": [51560, 467, 24042, 20820, 264, 8371, 281, 264, 14197, 9819, 666, 264, 5221, 2564, 13, 51779], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14895576238632202, "compression_ratio": 1.679054054054054, "no_speech_prob": 1.5984588869547012e-12}, {"id": 164, "seek": 55844, "start": 586.72, "end": 588.2, "text": " Like writing it in the journal.", "tokens": [51779, 1743, 3579, 309, 294, 264, 6708, 13, 51853], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14895576238632202, "compression_ratio": 1.679054054054054, "no_speech_prob": 1.5984588869547012e-12}, {"id": 165, "seek": 58844, "start": 588.44, "end": 588.72, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [50365, 1079, 13, 50379], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12771056680118337, "compression_ratio": 1.5739130434782609, "no_speech_prob": 1.340802577472211e-12}, {"id": 166, "seek": 58844, "start": 589.3000000000001, "end": 598.34, "text": " The identity of all future actions that drone takes, every package it delivers, will mathematically depend on the fact that it chose north instead of east at that specific moment.", "tokens": [50408, 440, 6575, 295, 439, 2027, 5909, 300, 13852, 2516, 11, 633, 7372, 309, 24860, 11, 486, 44003, 5672, 322, 264, 1186, 300, 309, 5111, 6830, 2602, 295, 10648, 412, 300, 2685, 1623, 13, 50860], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12771056680118337, "compression_ratio": 1.5739130434782609, "no_speech_prob": 1.340802577472211e-12}, {"id": 167, "seek": 58844, "start": 598.48, "end": 599.48, "text": " That is so cool.", "tokens": [50867, 663, 307, 370, 1627, 13, 50917], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12771056680118337, "compression_ratio": 1.5739130434782609, "no_speech_prob": 1.340802577472211e-12}, {"id": 168, "seek": 58844, "start": 599.86, "end": 600.6400000000001, "text": " Then there is refuse.", "tokens": [50936, 1396, 456, 307, 16791, 13, 50975], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12771056680118337, "compression_ratio": 1.5739130434782609, "no_speech_prob": 1.340802577472211e-12}, {"id": 169, "seek": 58844, "start": 600.9200000000001, "end": 602.7800000000001, "text": " And this is where the theory starts to bend my mind a bit.", "tokens": [50989, 400, 341, 307, 689, 264, 5261, 3719, 281, 11229, 452, 1575, 257, 857, 13, 51082], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12771056680118337, "compression_ratio": 1.5739130434782609, "no_speech_prob": 1.340802577472211e-12}, {"id": 170, "seek": 58844, "start": 602.94, "end": 607.24, "text": " Refuse permanently records that an alternative has been intentionally rejected.", "tokens": [51090, 16957, 438, 24042, 7724, 300, 364, 8535, 575, 668, 22062, 15749, 13, 51305], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12771056680118337, "compression_ratio": 1.5739130434782609, "no_speech_prob": 1.340802577472211e-12}, {"id": 171, "seek": 60724, "start": 607.24, "end": 608.72, "text": " It's a very powerful concept.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 311, 257, 588, 4005, 3410, 13, 50439], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14254478910076085, "compression_ratio": 1.439153439153439, "no_speech_prob": 1.340477642081117e-12}, {"id": 172, "seek": 60724, "start": 608.72, "end": 619.82, "text": " Now, in traditional programming, if our drone encounters an error, say, the north path is blocked by a storm, the program might throw an exception or crash or just skip a block of code.", "tokens": [50439, 823, 11, 294, 5164, 9410, 11, 498, 527, 13852, 26310, 364, 6713, 11, 584, 11, 264, 6830, 3100, 307, 15470, 538, 257, 7679, 11, 264, 1461, 1062, 3507, 364, 11183, 420, 8252, 420, 445, 10023, 257, 3461, 295, 3089, 13, 50994], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14254478910076085, "compression_ratio": 1.439153439153439, "no_speech_prob": 1.340477642081117e-12}, {"id": 173, "seek": 60724, "start": 620.14, "end": 623.04, "text": " Are you saying a crash is now considered a refuse event?", "tokens": [51010, 2014, 291, 1566, 257, 8252, 307, 586, 4888, 257, 16791, 2280, 30, 51155], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14254478910076085, "compression_ratio": 1.439153439153439, "no_speech_prob": 1.340477642081117e-12}, {"id": 174, "seek": 62304, "start": 623.04, "end": 625.24, "text": " I wouldn't call it a crash at all, actually.", "tokens": [50365, 286, 2759, 380, 818, 309, 257, 8252, 412, 439, 11, 767, 13, 50475], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16713109697614398, "compression_ratio": 1.4189944134078212, "no_speech_prob": 1.668234994589568e-12}, {"id": 175, "seek": 62304, "start": 625.4399999999999, "end": 626.56, "text": " That's a legacy way of thinking.", "tokens": [50485, 663, 311, 257, 11711, 636, 295, 1953, 13, 50541], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16713109697614398, "compression_ratio": 1.4189944134078212, "no_speech_prob": 1.668234994589568e-12}, {"id": 176, "seek": 62304, "start": 627.1999999999999, "end": 634.28, "text": " A crash implies that this system encountered a state it didn't know how to handle and the runtime environment had to halt.", "tokens": [50573, 316, 8252, 18779, 300, 341, 1185, 20381, 257, 1785, 309, 994, 380, 458, 577, 281, 4813, 293, 264, 34474, 2823, 632, 281, 12479, 13, 50927], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16713109697614398, "compression_ratio": 1.4189944134078212, "no_speech_prob": 1.668234994589568e-12}, {"id": 177, "seek": 62304, "start": 634.48, "end": 635.1999999999999, "text": " Like a failure.", "tokens": [50937, 1743, 257, 7763, 13, 50973], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16713109697614398, "compression_ratio": 1.4189944134078212, "no_speech_prob": 1.668234994589568e-12}, {"id": 178, "seek": 62304, "start": 635.4399999999999, "end": 635.5999999999999, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50985, 1779, 13, 50993], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16713109697614398, "compression_ratio": 1.4189944134078212, "no_speech_prob": 1.668234994589568e-12}, {"id": 179, "seek": 62304, "start": 636.04, "end": 637.3399999999999, "text": " Refusal is entirely different.", "tokens": [51015, 16957, 11765, 307, 7696, 819, 13, 51080], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16713109697614398, "compression_ratio": 1.4189944134078212, "no_speech_prob": 1.668234994589568e-12}, {"id": 180, "seek": 63734, "start": 637.34, "end": 655.72, "text": " So when Thomas Edison said he didn't fail 10,000 times to invent the light bulb, he just successfully found 10,000 ways that won't work.", "tokens": [50365, 407, 562, 8500, 47497, 848, 415, 994, 380, 3061, 1266, 11, 1360, 1413, 281, 7962, 264, 1442, 21122, 11, 415, 445, 10727, 1352, 1266, 11, 1360, 2098, 300, 1582, 380, 589, 13, 51284], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12961096233791775, "compression_ratio": 1.182608695652174, "no_speech_prob": 1.5922283023300787e-12}, {"id": 181, "seek": 65572, "start": 655.72, "end": 661.7, "text": " SpherePOP is essentially writing those 10,000 ways into the foundational math of the universe.", "tokens": [50365, 318, 6605, 47, 12059, 307, 4476, 3579, 729, 1266, 11, 1360, 2098, 666, 264, 32195, 5221, 295, 264, 6445, 13, 50664], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17933270055004674, "compression_ratio": 1.5227272727272727, "no_speech_prob": 1.3672832397532142e-12}, {"id": 182, "seek": 65572, "start": 661.9, "end": 663.38, "text": " That's a perfect way to look at it.", "tokens": [50674, 663, 311, 257, 2176, 636, 281, 574, 412, 309, 13, 50748], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17933270055004674, "compression_ratio": 1.5227272727272727, "no_speech_prob": 1.3672832397532142e-12}, {"id": 183, "seek": 65572, "start": 663.84, "end": 667.6800000000001, "text": " And this is vital for complex tasks like automated proof search or pathfinding.", "tokens": [50771, 400, 341, 307, 11707, 337, 3997, 9608, 411, 18473, 8177, 3164, 420, 3100, 69, 9245, 13, 50963], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17933270055004674, "compression_ratio": 1.5227272727272727, "no_speech_prob": 1.3672832397532142e-12}, {"id": 184, "seek": 65572, "start": 668.1800000000001, "end": 675.84, "text": " When an optimization algorithm realizes a path is bad, it shouldn't just forget that path and blindly try again from scratch.", "tokens": [50988, 1133, 364, 19618, 9284, 29316, 257, 3100, 307, 1578, 11, 309, 4659, 380, 445, 2870, 300, 3100, 293, 47744, 853, 797, 490, 8459, 13, 51371], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17933270055004674, "compression_ratio": 1.5227272727272727, "no_speech_prob": 1.3672832397532142e-12}, {"id": 185, "seek": 65572, "start": 675.98, "end": 676.22, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51378, 1779, 13, 51390], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17933270055004674, "compression_ratio": 1.5227272727272727, "no_speech_prob": 1.3672832397532142e-12}, {"id": 186, "seek": 65572, "start": 676.3000000000001, "end": 678.0, "text": " Because then it might just hit the same wall again.", "tokens": [51394, 1436, 550, 309, 1062, 445, 2045, 264, 912, 2929, 797, 13, 51479], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17933270055004674, "compression_ratio": 1.5227272727272727, "no_speech_prob": 1.3672832397532142e-12}, {"id": 187, "seek": 65572, "start": 678.1, "end": 678.5400000000001, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [51484, 7587, 13, 51506], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17933270055004674, "compression_ratio": 1.5227272727272727, "no_speech_prob": 1.3672832397532142e-12}, {"id": 188, "seek": 65572, "start": 678.82, "end": 679.82, "text": " It logs the refusal.", "tokens": [51520, 467, 20820, 264, 48948, 13, 51570], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17933270055004674, "compression_ratio": 1.5227272727272727, "no_speech_prob": 1.3672832397532142e-12}, {"id": 189, "seek": 65572, "start": 680.26, "end": 682.44, "text": " Future algorithms can inspect that history.", "tokens": [51592, 20805, 14642, 393, 15018, 300, 2503, 13, 51701], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17933270055004674, "compression_ratio": 1.5227272727272727, "no_speech_prob": 1.3672832397532142e-12}, {"id": 190, "seek": 68244, "start": 682.44, "end": 689.7, "text": " They can look at the journal and say, not only do I see what path was chosen, but I see the structural proof of what was deliberately abandoned.", "tokens": [50365, 814, 393, 574, 412, 264, 6708, 293, 584, 11, 406, 787, 360, 286, 536, 437, 3100, 390, 8614, 11, 457, 286, 536, 264, 15067, 8177, 295, 437, 390, 23506, 13732, 13, 50728], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14667082214355467, "compression_ratio": 1.5578231292517006, "no_speech_prob": 1.7013920654285197e-12}, {"id": 191, "seek": 68244, "start": 690.12, "end": 691.22, "text": " And I won't make that mistake.", "tokens": [50749, 400, 286, 1582, 380, 652, 300, 6146, 13, 50804], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14667082214355467, "compression_ratio": 1.5578231292517006, "no_speech_prob": 1.7013920654285197e-12}, {"id": 192, "seek": 68244, "start": 691.6, "end": 691.8000000000001, "text": " Okay.", "tokens": [50823, 1033, 13, 50833], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14667082214355467, "compression_ratio": 1.5578231292517006, "no_speech_prob": 1.7013920654285197e-12}, {"id": 193, "seek": 68244, "start": 692.1800000000001, "end": 693.7600000000001, "text": " Verb number three is bind.", "tokens": [50852, 27034, 1230, 1045, 307, 14786, 13, 50931], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14667082214355467, "compression_ratio": 1.5578231292517006, "no_speech_prob": 1.7013920654285197e-12}, {"id": 194, "seek": 68244, "start": 694.2600000000001, "end": 696.74, "text": " Bind establishes a formal dependency.", "tokens": [50956, 363, 471, 8327, 279, 257, 9860, 33621, 13, 51080], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14667082214355467, "compression_ratio": 1.5578231292517006, "no_speech_prob": 1.7013920654285197e-12}, {"id": 195, "seek": 68244, "start": 697.44, "end": 705.08, "text": " If you have a function, let's call it f, that operates on a variable x, traditional systems just do a symbolic substitution.", "tokens": [51115, 759, 291, 362, 257, 2445, 11, 718, 311, 818, 309, 283, 11, 300, 22577, 322, 257, 7006, 2031, 11, 5164, 3652, 445, 360, 257, 25755, 35827, 13, 51497], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14667082214355467, "compression_ratio": 1.5578231292517006, "no_speech_prob": 1.7013920654285197e-12}, {"id": 196, "seek": 68244, "start": 705.2600000000001, "end": 706.12, "text": " Just swap it out.", "tokens": [51506, 1449, 18135, 309, 484, 13, 51549], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14667082214355467, "compression_ratio": 1.5578231292517006, "no_speech_prob": 1.7013920654285197e-12}, {"id": 197, "seek": 68244, "start": 706.1800000000001, "end": 706.32, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [51552, 865, 13, 51559], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14667082214355467, "compression_ratio": 1.5578231292517006, "no_speech_prob": 1.7013920654285197e-12}, {"id": 198, "seek": 68244, "start": 706.4200000000001, "end": 709.3000000000001, "text": " They swap the x for a number, compute the result, and move on.", "tokens": [51564, 814, 18135, 264, 2031, 337, 257, 1230, 11, 14722, 264, 1874, 11, 293, 1286, 322, 13, 51708], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14667082214355467, "compression_ratio": 1.5578231292517006, "no_speech_prob": 1.7013920654285197e-12}, {"id": 199, "seek": 70930, "start": 709.3, "end": 717.9399999999999, "text": " Spherpop uses the bind verb to record that every subsequent construction of that function historically depends upon that specific x.", "tokens": [50365, 1738, 511, 13872, 4960, 264, 14786, 9595, 281, 2136, 300, 633, 19962, 6435, 295, 300, 2445, 16180, 5946, 3564, 300, 2685, 2031, 13, 50797], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14808517032199436, "compression_ratio": 1.6437246963562753, "no_speech_prob": 1.965617772714534e-12}, {"id": 200, "seek": 70930, "start": 718.0799999999999, "end": 718.76, "text": " Oh, I see.", "tokens": [50804, 876, 11, 286, 536, 13, 50838], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14808517032199436, "compression_ratio": 1.6437246963562753, "no_speech_prob": 1.965617772714534e-12}, {"id": 201, "seek": 70930, "start": 719.02, "end": 722.12, "text": " The dependency graph isn't just a mental model for the programmer.", "tokens": [50851, 440, 33621, 4295, 1943, 380, 445, 257, 4973, 2316, 337, 264, 32116, 13, 51006], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14808517032199436, "compression_ratio": 1.6437246963562753, "no_speech_prob": 1.965617772714534e-12}, {"id": 202, "seek": 70930, "start": 722.42, "end": 724.8599999999999, "text": " It becomes a physical part of the provenance.", "tokens": [51021, 467, 3643, 257, 4001, 644, 295, 264, 12785, 719, 13, 51143], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14808517032199436, "compression_ratio": 1.6437246963562753, "no_speech_prob": 1.965617772714534e-12}, {"id": 203, "seek": 70930, "start": 725.24, "end": 734.3399999999999, "text": " If the drone's speed depends on its battery level, bind explicitly links every future speed calculation to the exact history of that battery reading.", "tokens": [51162, 759, 264, 13852, 311, 3073, 5946, 322, 1080, 5809, 1496, 11, 14786, 20803, 6123, 633, 2027, 3073, 17108, 281, 264, 1900, 2503, 295, 300, 5809, 3760, 13, 51617], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14808517032199436, "compression_ratio": 1.6437246963562753, "no_speech_prob": 1.965617772714534e-12}, {"id": 204, "seek": 73434, "start": 734.34, "end": 740.5600000000001, "text": " Which brings us to collapse. Earlier, we talked about how two 42s with different histories are completely distinct objects.", "tokens": [50365, 3013, 5607, 505, 281, 15584, 13, 24552, 11, 321, 2825, 466, 577, 732, 14034, 82, 365, 819, 30631, 366, 2584, 10644, 6565, 13, 50676], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08872055539897844, "compression_ratio": 1.6607142857142858, "no_speech_prob": 1.8393526719090447e-12}, {"id": 205, "seek": 73434, "start": 740.98, "end": 745.5, "text": " Collapse is how we deal with the reality that sometimes we really do need them to act the same.", "tokens": [50697, 4586, 11145, 307, 577, 321, 2028, 365, 264, 4103, 300, 2171, 321, 534, 360, 643, 552, 281, 605, 264, 912, 13, 50923], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08872055539897844, "compression_ratio": 1.6607142857142858, "no_speech_prob": 1.8393526719090447e-12}, {"id": 206, "seek": 73434, "start": 745.86, "end": 748.5, "text": " Right. We can't always treat them as totally alien to each other.", "tokens": [50941, 1779, 13, 492, 393, 380, 1009, 2387, 552, 382, 3879, 12319, 281, 1184, 661, 13, 51073], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08872055539897844, "compression_ratio": 1.6607142857142858, "no_speech_prob": 1.8393526719090447e-12}, {"id": 207, "seek": 73434, "start": 748.6, "end": 753.14, "text": " Yeah. Collapse states that two independently constructed histories are now considered equivalent.", "tokens": [51078, 865, 13, 4586, 11145, 4368, 300, 732, 21761, 17083, 30631, 366, 586, 4888, 10344, 13, 51305], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08872055539897844, "compression_ratio": 1.6607142857142858, "no_speech_prob": 1.8393526719090447e-12}, {"id": 208, "seek": 73434, "start": 753.74, "end": 757.96, "text": " But the genius here is that it does this without erasing either original history.", "tokens": [51335, 583, 264, 14017, 510, 307, 300, 309, 775, 341, 1553, 1189, 3349, 2139, 3380, 2503, 13, 51546], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08872055539897844, "compression_ratio": 1.6607142857142858, "no_speech_prob": 1.8393526719090447e-12}, {"id": 209, "seek": 75796, "start": 757.96, "end": 762.1800000000001, "text": " It completely upends how standard math handles equivalence.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 2584, 493, 2581, 577, 3832, 5221, 18722, 9052, 655, 13, 50576], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1412254821422488, "compression_ratio": 1.6056338028169015, "no_speech_prob": 1.796759030621431e-12}, {"id": 210, "seek": 75796, "start": 763.1600000000001, "end": 768.6800000000001, "text": " Usually, when mathematicians want to say two distinct things are equivalent, they use a tool called a quotient.", "tokens": [50625, 11419, 11, 562, 32811, 2567, 528, 281, 584, 732, 10644, 721, 366, 10344, 11, 436, 764, 257, 2290, 1219, 257, 9641, 1196, 13, 50901], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1412254821422488, "compression_ratio": 1.6056338028169015, "no_speech_prob": 1.796759030621431e-12}, {"id": 211, "seek": 75796, "start": 768.96, "end": 769.74, "text": " A quotient.", "tokens": [50915, 316, 9641, 1196, 13, 50954], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1412254821422488, "compression_ratio": 1.6056338028169015, "no_speech_prob": 1.796759030621431e-12}, {"id": 212, "seek": 75796, "start": 769.86, "end": 772.88, "text": " A quotient basically forces the two things to be equal.", "tokens": [50960, 316, 9641, 1196, 1936, 5874, 264, 732, 721, 281, 312, 2681, 13, 51111], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1412254821422488, "compression_ratio": 1.6056338028169015, "no_speech_prob": 1.796759030621431e-12}, {"id": 213, "seek": 75796, "start": 773.0600000000001, "end": 776.62, "text": " And in doing so, it essentially demands that you forget their differences.", "tokens": [51120, 400, 294, 884, 370, 11, 309, 4476, 15107, 300, 291, 2870, 641, 7300, 13, 51298], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1412254821422488, "compression_ratio": 1.6056338028169015, "no_speech_prob": 1.796759030621431e-12}, {"id": 214, "seek": 75796, "start": 776.72, "end": 778.24, "text": " It just smooths it all out.", "tokens": [51303, 467, 445, 5508, 82, 309, 439, 484, 13, 51379], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1412254821422488, "compression_ratio": 1.6056338028169015, "no_speech_prob": 1.796759030621431e-12}, {"id": 215, "seek": 77824, "start": 778.24, "end": 781.1, "text": " Yeah. But Sphere Pop refuses to forget.", "tokens": [50365, 865, 13, 583, 318, 6605, 10215, 33222, 281, 2870, 13, 50508], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16778989938589242, "compression_ratio": 1.6360424028268552, "no_speech_prob": 1.7758239540324738e-12}, {"id": 216, "seek": 77824, "start": 782.2, "end": 790.58, "text": " Collapse is an explicit event that records the identification of the two histories, preserving both of their original distinct paths forever.", "tokens": [50563, 4586, 11145, 307, 364, 13691, 2280, 300, 7724, 264, 22065, 295, 264, 732, 30631, 11, 33173, 1293, 295, 641, 3380, 10644, 14518, 5680, 13, 50982], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16778989938589242, "compression_ratio": 1.6360424028268552, "no_speech_prob": 1.7758239540324738e-12}, {"id": 217, "seek": 77824, "start": 790.82, "end": 793.54, "text": " It's like taking two different hiking trails up a mountain, right?", "tokens": [50994, 467, 311, 411, 1940, 732, 819, 23784, 23024, 493, 257, 6937, 11, 558, 30, 51130], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16778989938589242, "compression_ratio": 1.6360424028268552, "no_speech_prob": 1.7758239540324738e-12}, {"id": 218, "seek": 77824, "start": 794.14, "end": 795.76, "text": " Trail A is steep and rocky.", "tokens": [51160, 30080, 316, 307, 16841, 293, 33301, 13, 51241], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16778989938589242, "compression_ratio": 1.6360424028268552, "no_speech_prob": 1.7758239540324738e-12}, {"id": 219, "seek": 77824, "start": 796.02, "end": 797.6800000000001, "text": " Trail B is long and winding.", "tokens": [51254, 30080, 363, 307, 938, 293, 29775, 13, 51337], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16778989938589242, "compression_ratio": 1.6360424028268552, "no_speech_prob": 1.7758239540324738e-12}, {"id": 220, "seek": 77824, "start": 798.1, "end": 800.24, "text": " The summit is the exact same location.", "tokens": [51358, 440, 21564, 307, 264, 1900, 912, 4914, 13, 51465], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16778989938589242, "compression_ratio": 1.6360424028268552, "no_speech_prob": 1.7758239540324738e-12}, {"id": 221, "seek": 77824, "start": 800.66, "end": 802.76, "text": " Traditional math says you are at the summit.", "tokens": [51486, 46738, 5221, 1619, 291, 366, 412, 264, 21564, 13, 51591], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16778989938589242, "compression_ratio": 1.6360424028268552, "no_speech_prob": 1.7758239540324738e-12}, {"id": 222, "seek": 77824, "start": 802.94, "end": 805.2, "text": " Therefore, Trail A and Trail B are identical.", "tokens": [51600, 7504, 11, 30080, 316, 293, 30080, 363, 366, 14800, 13, 51713], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16778989938589242, "compression_ratio": 1.6360424028268552, "no_speech_prob": 1.7758239540324738e-12}, {"id": 223, "seek": 77824, "start": 805.54, "end": 806.76, "text": " Yep. It erases the journey.", "tokens": [51730, 7010, 13, 467, 1189, 1957, 264, 4671, 13, 51791], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16778989938589242, "compression_ratio": 1.6360424028268552, "no_speech_prob": 1.7758239540324738e-12}, {"id": 224, "seek": 80676, "start": 806.76, "end": 815.98, "text": " But Sphere Pop says you are at the summit, and I am formally collapsing these two endpoints to recognize they arrived at the same place, but I am keeping the full GPS track of both trails.", "tokens": [50365, 583, 318, 6605, 10215, 1619, 291, 366, 412, 264, 21564, 11, 293, 286, 669, 25983, 45339, 613, 732, 917, 20552, 281, 5521, 436, 6678, 412, 264, 912, 1081, 11, 457, 286, 669, 5145, 264, 1577, 19462, 2837, 295, 1293, 23024, 13, 50826], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.148384110266421, "compression_ratio": 1.662295081967213, "no_speech_prob": 1.8461545226583498e-12}, {"id": 225, "seek": 80676, "start": 816.56, "end": 822.98, "text": " You staple the receipts together, you have both histories, but the system now formally acknowledges they represent the same transaction.", "tokens": [50855, 509, 32361, 264, 2268, 48908, 1214, 11, 291, 362, 1293, 30631, 11, 457, 264, 1185, 586, 25983, 15195, 2880, 436, 2906, 264, 912, 14425, 13, 51176], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.148384110266421, "compression_ratio": 1.662295081967213, "no_speech_prob": 1.8461545226583498e-12}, {"id": 226, "seek": 80676, "start": 823.5, "end": 825.5, "text": " Stapling the receipts is a great visualization.", "tokens": [51202, 16959, 11970, 264, 2268, 48908, 307, 257, 869, 25801, 13, 51302], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.148384110266421, "compression_ratio": 1.662295081967213, "no_speech_prob": 1.8461545226583498e-12}, {"id": 227, "seek": 80676, "start": 826.3199999999999, "end": 829.14, "text": " And that leads us with the fifth verb, which is MELD.", "tokens": [51343, 400, 300, 6689, 505, 365, 264, 9266, 9595, 11, 597, 307, 38005, 35, 13, 51484], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.148384110266421, "compression_ratio": 1.662295081967213, "no_speech_prob": 1.8461545226583498e-12}, {"id": 228, "seek": 80676, "start": 829.76, "end": 832.42, "text": " MELD merges compatible, independent histories.", "tokens": [51515, 38005, 35, 3551, 2880, 18218, 11, 6695, 30631, 13, 51648], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.148384110266421, "compression_ratio": 1.662295081967213, "no_speech_prob": 1.8461545226583498e-12}, {"id": 229, "seek": 80676, "start": 832.64, "end": 833.88, "text": " What does that mean practically?", "tokens": [51659, 708, 775, 300, 914, 15667, 30, 51721], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.148384110266421, "compression_ratio": 1.662295081967213, "no_speech_prob": 1.8461545226583498e-12}, {"id": 230, "seek": 83388, "start": 833.88, "end": 838.58, "text": " Well, in modern computing, we rarely have one processor doing one thing.", "tokens": [50365, 1042, 11, 294, 4363, 15866, 11, 321, 13752, 362, 472, 15321, 884, 472, 551, 13, 50600], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1142277717590332, "compression_ratio": 1.6503496503496504, "no_speech_prob": 1.8980305608456982e-12}, {"id": 231, "seek": 83388, "start": 839.36, "end": 841.4, "text": " We have thousands of concurrent threads.", "tokens": [50639, 492, 362, 5383, 295, 37702, 19314, 13, 50741], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1142277717590332, "compression_ratio": 1.6503496503496504, "no_speech_prob": 1.8980305608456982e-12}, {"id": 232, "seek": 83388, "start": 842.4399999999999, "end": 849.54, "text": " If two computers are calculating different parts of a complex problem at the exact same time, their histories are independent.", "tokens": [50793, 759, 732, 10807, 366, 28258, 819, 3166, 295, 257, 3997, 1154, 412, 264, 1900, 912, 565, 11, 641, 30631, 366, 6695, 13, 51148], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1142277717590332, "compression_ratio": 1.6503496503496504, "no_speech_prob": 1.8980305608456982e-12}, {"id": 233, "seek": 83388, "start": 849.88, "end": 851.38, "text": " Right. They have their own separate journals.", "tokens": [51165, 1779, 13, 814, 362, 641, 1065, 4994, 29621, 13, 51240], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1142277717590332, "compression_ratio": 1.6503496503496504, "no_speech_prob": 1.8980305608456982e-12}, {"id": 234, "seek": 83388, "start": 851.92, "end": 852.56, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [51267, 7587, 13, 51299], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1142277717590332, "compression_ratio": 1.6503496503496504, "no_speech_prob": 1.8980305608456982e-12}, {"id": 235, "seek": 83388, "start": 853.42, "end": 862.48, "text": " MELD is the operation that combines their respective journals into a single, unified history without violating any of the dependency constraints established by the bind events.", "tokens": [51342, 38005, 35, 307, 264, 6916, 300, 29520, 641, 23649, 29621, 666, 257, 2167, 11, 26787, 2503, 1553, 42201, 604, 295, 264, 33621, 18491, 7545, 538, 264, 14786, 3931, 13, 51795], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1142277717590332, "compression_ratio": 1.6503496503496504, "no_speech_prob": 1.8980305608456982e-12}, {"id": 236, "seek": 86248, "start": 862.48, "end": 866.16, "text": " It is the formal foundation for concurrent computation.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 307, 264, 9860, 7030, 337, 37702, 24903, 13, 50549], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17913740985798385, "compression_ratio": 1.4535714285714285, "no_speech_prob": 1.5546327246374059e-12}, {"id": 237, "seek": 86248, "start": 866.5600000000001, "end": 877.22, "text": " So, out of just those five verbs, POP, REFUSE, BIND, COLLAPSE, and MELDFLICTION builds up an entire dependent type calculus, which acts as the perfect bridge to the second paper.", "tokens": [50569, 407, 11, 484, 295, 445, 729, 1732, 30051, 11, 430, 12059, 11, 10869, 37, 44626, 11, 363, 18323, 11, 3002, 24010, 4715, 5879, 11, 293, 38005, 35, 37, 43, 2532, 7413, 15182, 493, 364, 2302, 12334, 2010, 33400, 11, 597, 10672, 382, 264, 2176, 7283, 281, 264, 1150, 3035, 13, 51102], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17913740985798385, "compression_ratio": 1.4535714285714285, "no_speech_prob": 1.5546327246374059e-12}, {"id": 238, "seek": 86248, "start": 877.72, "end": 878.98, "text": " Types is refusal structures.", "tokens": [51127, 5569, 5190, 307, 48948, 9227, 13, 51190], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17913740985798385, "compression_ratio": 1.4535714285714285, "no_speech_prob": 1.5546327246374059e-12}, {"id": 239, "seek": 86248, "start": 879.26, "end": 880.4200000000001, "text": " Yes, look at it into the types.", "tokens": [51204, 1079, 11, 574, 412, 309, 666, 264, 3467, 13, 51262], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17913740985798385, "compression_ratio": 1.4535714285714285, "no_speech_prob": 1.5546327246374059e-12}, {"id": 240, "seek": 86248, "start": 880.54, "end": 885.1, "text": " Let's dive into this, because the word type in programming usually means something incredibly rigid and boring.", "tokens": [51268, 961, 311, 9192, 666, 341, 11, 570, 264, 1349, 2010, 294, 9410, 2673, 1355, 746, 6252, 22195, 293, 9989, 13, 51496], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17913740985798385, "compression_ratio": 1.4535714285714285, "no_speech_prob": 1.5546327246374059e-12}, {"id": 241, "seek": 88510, "start": 885.1, "end": 889.58, "text": " If you've ever coded in Python or Java, a type is just a static label.", "tokens": [50365, 759, 291, 600, 1562, 34874, 294, 15329, 420, 10745, 11, 257, 2010, 307, 445, 257, 13437, 7645, 13, 50589], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.164621900803972, "compression_ratio": 1.5758928571428572, "no_speech_prob": 1.6108577145790282e-12}, {"id": 242, "seek": 88510, "start": 889.6800000000001, "end": 890.64, "text": " A sticky note, basically.", "tokens": [50594, 316, 14470, 3637, 11, 1936, 13, 50642], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.164621900803972, "compression_ratio": 1.5758928571428572, "no_speech_prob": 1.6108577145790282e-12}, {"id": 243, "seek": 88510, "start": 890.94, "end": 891.16, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [50657, 865, 13, 50668], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.164621900803972, "compression_ratio": 1.5758928571428572, "no_speech_prob": 1.6108577145790282e-12}, {"id": 244, "seek": 88510, "start": 891.7, "end": 895.88, "text": " It's a sticky note that says, this is an integer, or this is a string of text.", "tokens": [50695, 467, 311, 257, 14470, 3637, 300, 1619, 11, 341, 307, 364, 24922, 11, 420, 341, 307, 257, 6798, 295, 2487, 13, 50904], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.164621900803972, "compression_ratio": 1.5758928571428572, "no_speech_prob": 1.6108577145790282e-12}, {"id": 245, "seek": 88510, "start": 896.12, "end": 898.24, "text": " It is essentially just a collection of values.", "tokens": [50916, 467, 307, 4476, 445, 257, 5765, 295, 4190, 13, 51022], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.164621900803972, "compression_ratio": 1.5758928571428572, "no_speech_prob": 1.6108577145790282e-12}, {"id": 246, "seek": 88510, "start": 898.8000000000001, "end": 900.88, "text": " But SpherePop rejects that entirely.", "tokens": [51050, 583, 318, 6605, 38677, 8248, 82, 300, 7696, 13, 51154], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.164621900803972, "compression_ratio": 1.5758928571428572, "no_speech_prob": 1.6108577145790282e-12}, {"id": 247, "seek": 88510, "start": 901.44, "end": 905.2, "text": " SpherePop says a type is a disciplined refusal structure.", "tokens": [51182, 318, 6605, 38677, 1619, 257, 2010, 307, 257, 40061, 48948, 3877, 13, 51370], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.164621900803972, "compression_ratio": 1.5758928571428572, "no_speech_prob": 1.6108577145790282e-12}, {"id": 248, "seek": 88510, "start": 905.6800000000001, "end": 906.9, "text": " What does that actually mean?", "tokens": [51394, 708, 775, 300, 767, 914, 30, 51455], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.164621900803972, "compression_ratio": 1.5758928571428572, "no_speech_prob": 1.6108577145790282e-12}, {"id": 249, "seek": 90690, "start": 906.9, "end": 913.0799999999999, "text": " It means we have to stop thinking of types as passive buckets, and start thinking of them as active gatekeepers.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 1355, 321, 362, 281, 1590, 1953, 295, 3467, 382, 14975, 32191, 11, 293, 722, 1953, 295, 552, 382, 4967, 8539, 43153, 13, 50674], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11094997275588858, "compression_ratio": 1.6666666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.460980642020715e-12}, {"id": 250, "seek": 90690, "start": 913.64, "end": 924.4399999999999, "text": " Instead of a type being a static collection of values that something either belongs to or doesn't, a SpherePop type assigns one of three statuses to any candidate continuation in the program.", "tokens": [50702, 7156, 295, 257, 2010, 885, 257, 13437, 5765, 295, 4190, 300, 746, 2139, 12953, 281, 420, 1177, 380, 11, 257, 318, 6605, 38677, 2010, 6269, 82, 472, 295, 1045, 6558, 279, 281, 604, 11532, 29357, 294, 264, 1461, 13, 51242], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11094997275588858, "compression_ratio": 1.6666666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.460980642020715e-12}, {"id": 251, "seek": 90690, "start": 924.52, "end": 925.52, "text": " And those statuses are?", "tokens": [51246, 400, 729, 6558, 279, 366, 30, 51296], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11094997275588858, "compression_ratio": 1.6666666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.460980642020715e-12}, {"id": 252, "seek": 90690, "start": 925.68, "end": 927.78, "text": " Admit, refuse, or defer.", "tokens": [51304, 1999, 3508, 11, 16791, 11, 420, 25704, 13, 51409], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11094997275588858, "compression_ratio": 1.6666666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.460980642020715e-12}, {"id": 253, "seek": 90690, "start": 928.04, "end": 930.54, "text": " I want to break down how this contrasts with the old way.", "tokens": [51422, 286, 528, 281, 1821, 760, 577, 341, 8712, 82, 365, 264, 1331, 636, 13, 51547], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11094997275588858, "compression_ratio": 1.6666666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.460980642020715e-12}, {"id": 254, "seek": 90690, "start": 930.98, "end": 934.38, "text": " In traditional type theory, there is a very famous mathematical judgment.", "tokens": [51569, 682, 5164, 2010, 5261, 11, 456, 307, 257, 588, 4618, 18894, 12216, 13, 51739], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11094997275588858, "compression_ratio": 1.6666666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.460980642020715e-12}, {"id": 255, "seek": 93438, "start": 934.38, "end": 941.26, "text": " It's written as the Greek letter gamma, a turnstile symbol, a lowercase t, a colon, and a capital A.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 311, 3720, 382, 264, 10281, 5063, 15546, 11, 257, 1261, 372, 794, 5986, 11, 257, 3126, 9765, 256, 11, 257, 8255, 11, 293, 257, 4238, 316, 13, 50709], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1056155572857773, "compression_ratio": 1.613899613899614, "no_speech_prob": 1.5732936871695746e-12}, {"id": 256, "seek": 93438, "start": 941.4399999999999, "end": 943.0, "text": " Right, the classic typing judgment.", "tokens": [50718, 1779, 11, 264, 7230, 18444, 12216, 13, 50796], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1056155572857773, "compression_ratio": 1.613899613899614, "no_speech_prob": 1.5732936871695746e-12}, {"id": 257, "seek": 93438, "start": 943.28, "end": 949.22, "text": " When you read a textbook, this usually means under a specific set of assumptions, this term et belongs to this type A.", "tokens": [50810, 1133, 291, 1401, 257, 25591, 11, 341, 2673, 1355, 833, 257, 2685, 992, 295, 17695, 11, 341, 1433, 1030, 12953, 281, 341, 2010, 316, 13, 51107], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1056155572857773, "compression_ratio": 1.613899613899614, "no_speech_prob": 1.5732936871695746e-12}, {"id": 258, "seek": 93438, "start": 949.34, "end": 950.02, "text": " It's static.", "tokens": [51113, 467, 311, 13437, 13, 51147], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1056155572857773, "compression_ratio": 1.613899613899614, "no_speech_prob": 1.5732936871695746e-12}, {"id": 259, "seek": 93438, "start": 950.22, "end": 951.22, "text": " It's a statement of fact.", "tokens": [51157, 467, 311, 257, 5629, 295, 1186, 13, 51207], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1056155572857773, "compression_ratio": 1.613899613899614, "no_speech_prob": 1.5732936871695746e-12}, {"id": 260, "seek": 93438, "start": 951.5, "end": 956.0, "text": " But in SpherePop, that exact same judgment is interpreted dynamically.", "tokens": [51221, 583, 294, 318, 6605, 38677, 11, 300, 1900, 912, 12216, 307, 26749, 43492, 13, 51446], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1056155572857773, "compression_ratio": 1.613899613899614, "no_speech_prob": 1.5732936871695746e-12}, {"id": 261, "seek": 93438, "start": 956.7, "end": 959.8, "text": " It doesn't mean the term passively belongs to a set.", "tokens": [51481, 467, 1177, 380, 914, 264, 1433, 1320, 3413, 12953, 281, 257, 992, 13, 51636], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1056155572857773, "compression_ratio": 1.613899613899614, "no_speech_prob": 1.5732936871695746e-12}, {"id": 262, "seek": 95980, "start": 959.8, "end": 969.28, "text": " It means, under the accumulated history we have so far, the event is allowed to continue without violating the refusal conditions of type A.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 1355, 11, 833, 264, 31346, 2503, 321, 362, 370, 1400, 11, 264, 2280, 307, 4350, 281, 2354, 1553, 42201, 264, 48948, 4487, 295, 2010, 316, 13, 50839], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12200941733264048, "compression_ratio": 1.6538461538461537, "no_speech_prob": 1.2494643991320387e-12}, {"id": 263, "seek": 95980, "start": 969.4799999999999, "end": 970.8599999999999, "text": " Wow, that's a huge shift.", "tokens": [50849, 3153, 11, 300, 311, 257, 2603, 5513, 13, 50918], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12200941733264048, "compression_ratio": 1.6538461538461537, "no_speech_prob": 1.2494643991320387e-12}, {"id": 264, "seek": 95980, "start": 971.18, "end": 976.02, "text": " It shifts the emphasis entirely from static membership to controlled continuation.", "tokens": [50934, 467, 19201, 264, 16271, 7696, 490, 13437, 16560, 281, 10164, 29357, 13, 51176], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12200941733264048, "compression_ratio": 1.6538461538461537, "no_speech_prob": 1.2494643991320387e-12}, {"id": 265, "seek": 95980, "start": 976.54, "end": 979.9599999999999, "text": " Think of a type like a bouncer at a very exclusive nightclub.", "tokens": [51202, 6557, 295, 257, 2010, 411, 257, 272, 14296, 412, 257, 588, 13005, 1818, 40607, 13, 51373], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12200941733264048, "compression_ratio": 1.6538461538461537, "no_speech_prob": 1.2494643991320387e-12}, {"id": 266, "seek": 95980, "start": 980.4799999999999, "end": 983.8199999999999, "text": " Traditional type theory treats a type like the physical club itself.", "tokens": [51399, 46738, 2010, 5261, 19566, 257, 2010, 411, 264, 4001, 6482, 2564, 13, 51566], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12200941733264048, "compression_ratio": 1.6538461538461537, "no_speech_prob": 1.2494643991320387e-12}, {"id": 267, "seek": 95980, "start": 984.3, "end": 987.62, "text": " You are either inside the integer club or you are outside of it.", "tokens": [51590, 509, 366, 2139, 1854, 264, 24922, 6482, 420, 291, 366, 2380, 295, 309, 13, 51756], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12200941733264048, "compression_ratio": 1.6538461538461537, "no_speech_prob": 1.2494643991320387e-12}, {"id": 268, "seek": 95980, "start": 987.6999999999999, "end": 989.02, "text": " Right, geographic location.", "tokens": [51760, 1779, 11, 32318, 4914, 13, 51826], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12200941733264048, "compression_ratio": 1.6538461538461537, "no_speech_prob": 1.2494643991320387e-12}, {"id": 269, "seek": 98902, "start": 989.02, "end": 992.62, "text": " But SpherePop treats the type as the bouncer standing at the door.", "tokens": [50365, 583, 318, 6605, 38677, 19566, 264, 2010, 382, 264, 272, 14296, 4877, 412, 264, 2853, 13, 50545], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12407578786214192, "compression_ratio": 1.7864077669902914, "no_speech_prob": 1.7080538372571397e-12}, {"id": 270, "seek": 98902, "start": 993.06, "end": 995.3199999999999, "text": " You walk up, and the bouncer doesn't just look at your ID.", "tokens": [50567, 509, 1792, 493, 11, 293, 264, 272, 14296, 1177, 380, 445, 574, 412, 428, 7348, 13, 50680], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12407578786214192, "compression_ratio": 1.7864077669902914, "no_speech_prob": 1.7080538372571397e-12}, {"id": 271, "seek": 98902, "start": 995.88, "end": 1000.3, "text": " The bouncer looks at your entire history, every club you've been to, every drink you've ordered.", "tokens": [50708, 440, 272, 14296, 1542, 412, 428, 2302, 2503, 11, 633, 6482, 291, 600, 668, 281, 11, 633, 2822, 291, 600, 8866, 13, 50929], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12407578786214192, "compression_ratio": 1.7864077669902914, "no_speech_prob": 1.7080538372571397e-12}, {"id": 272, "seek": 98902, "start": 1000.52, "end": 1001.38, "text": " They're checking your journal.", "tokens": [50940, 814, 434, 8568, 428, 6708, 13, 50983], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12407578786214192, "compression_ratio": 1.7864077669902914, "no_speech_prob": 1.7080538372571397e-12}, {"id": 273, "seek": 98902, "start": 1001.78, "end": 1002.22, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [51003, 7587, 13, 51025], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12407578786214192, "compression_ratio": 1.7864077669902914, "no_speech_prob": 1.7080538372571397e-12}, {"id": 274, "seek": 98902, "start": 1002.48, "end": 1003.66, "text": " The type is a set of rules.", "tokens": [51038, 440, 2010, 307, 257, 992, 295, 4474, 13, 51097], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12407578786214192, "compression_ratio": 1.7864077669902914, "no_speech_prob": 1.7080538372571397e-12}, {"id": 275, "seek": 98902, "start": 1004.34, "end": 1008.0799999999999, "text": " If your history meets the criteria, the bouncer executes an admit event.", "tokens": [51131, 759, 428, 2503, 13961, 264, 11101, 11, 264, 272, 14296, 4454, 1819, 364, 9796, 2280, 13, 51318], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12407578786214192, "compression_ratio": 1.7864077669902914, "no_speech_prob": 1.7080538372571397e-12}, {"id": 276, "seek": 98902, "start": 1008.3199999999999, "end": 1009.42, "text": " You can continue your night.", "tokens": [51330, 509, 393, 2354, 428, 1818, 13, 51385], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12407578786214192, "compression_ratio": 1.7864077669902914, "no_speech_prob": 1.7080538372571397e-12}, {"id": 277, "seek": 98902, "start": 1009.78, "end": 1014.54, "text": " If your history violates the rules, you are refused entry before you can even step inside and make a mess.", "tokens": [51403, 759, 428, 2503, 3448, 1024, 264, 4474, 11, 291, 366, 14654, 8729, 949, 291, 393, 754, 1823, 1854, 293, 652, 257, 2082, 13, 51641], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12407578786214192, "compression_ratio": 1.7864077669902914, "no_speech_prob": 1.7080538372571397e-12}, {"id": 278, "seek": 98902, "start": 1014.74, "end": 1017.22, "text": " That captures the active nature of it perfectly.", "tokens": [51651, 663, 27986, 264, 4967, 3687, 295, 309, 6239, 13, 51775], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12407578786214192, "compression_ratio": 1.7864077669902914, "no_speech_prob": 1.7080538372571397e-12}, {"id": 279, "seek": 98902, "start": 1017.48, "end": 1017.76, "text": " Ah.", "tokens": [51788, 2438, 13, 51802], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12407578786214192, "compression_ratio": 1.7864077669902914, "no_speech_prob": 1.7080538372571397e-12}, {"id": 280, "seek": 101776, "start": 1017.76, "end": 1020.86, "text": " And we should explore that third status, too, which is defer.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 321, 820, 6839, 300, 2636, 6558, 11, 886, 11, 597, 307, 25704, 13, 50520], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1361964450163, "compression_ratio": 1.5510204081632653, "no_speech_prob": 1.9168347464848523e-12}, {"id": 281, "seek": 101776, "start": 1021.46, "end": 1022.08, "text": " Oh, right.", "tokens": [50550, 876, 11, 558, 13, 50581], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1361964450163, "compression_ratio": 1.5510204081632653, "no_speech_prob": 1.9168347464848523e-12}, {"id": 282, "seek": 101776, "start": 1022.22, "end": 1022.62, "text": " Defer.", "tokens": [50588, 1346, 612, 13, 50608], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1361964450163, "compression_ratio": 1.5510204081632653, "no_speech_prob": 1.9168347464848523e-12}, {"id": 283, "seek": 101776, "start": 1022.76, "end": 1024.46, "text": " That's like being put on the wait list, isn't it?", "tokens": [50615, 663, 311, 411, 885, 829, 322, 264, 1699, 1329, 11, 1943, 380, 309, 30, 50700], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1361964450163, "compression_ratio": 1.5510204081632653, "no_speech_prob": 1.9168347464848523e-12}, {"id": 284, "seek": 101776, "start": 1024.56, "end": 1031.72, "text": " The bouncer looks at your history and says, I don't have enough information to let you in yet, but you haven't explicitly broken a rule either.", "tokens": [50705, 440, 272, 14296, 1542, 412, 428, 2503, 293, 1619, 11, 286, 500, 380, 362, 1547, 1589, 281, 718, 291, 294, 1939, 11, 457, 291, 2378, 380, 20803, 5463, 257, 4978, 2139, 13, 51063], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1361964450163, "compression_ratio": 1.5510204081632653, "no_speech_prob": 1.9168347464848523e-12}, {"id": 285, "seek": 101776, "start": 1032.36, "end": 1037.12, "text": " Stand over there by the velvet rope until more of your party arrives or more of your history is generated.", "tokens": [51095, 9133, 670, 456, 538, 264, 41905, 13540, 1826, 544, 295, 428, 3595, 20116, 420, 544, 295, 428, 2503, 307, 10833, 13, 51333], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1361964450163, "compression_ratio": 1.5510204081632653, "no_speech_prob": 1.9168347464848523e-12}, {"id": 286, "seek": 103712, "start": 1037.12, "end": 1042.04, "text": " It is an incredibly robust way to handle partial information in a system.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 307, 364, 6252, 13956, 636, 281, 4813, 14641, 1589, 294, 257, 1185, 13, 50611], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21875233120388454, "compression_ratio": 1.0138888888888888, "no_speech_prob": 1.5191782293949574e-12}, {"id": 287, "seek": 104204, "start": 1042.04, "end": 1049.62, "text": " And if we connect this to the broader landscape of software engineering, this completely reframes what a type error actually is.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 498, 321, 1745, 341, 281, 264, 13227, 9661, 295, 4722, 7043, 11, 341, 2584, 13334, 1632, 437, 257, 2010, 6713, 767, 307, 13, 50744], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12355110380384657, "compression_ratio": 1.4352331606217616, "no_speech_prob": 1.56129590592885e-12}, {"id": 288, "seek": 104204, "start": 1049.74, "end": 1050.3799999999999, "text": " Oh, man.", "tokens": [50750, 876, 11, 587, 13, 50782], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12355110380384657, "compression_ratio": 1.4352331606217616, "no_speech_prob": 1.56129590592885e-12}, {"id": 289, "seek": 104204, "start": 1050.6, "end": 1054.26, "text": " A type error in a language like C++ is a catastrophic failure.", "tokens": [50793, 316, 2010, 6713, 294, 257, 2856, 411, 383, 25472, 307, 257, 34915, 7763, 13, 50976], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12355110380384657, "compression_ratio": 1.4352331606217616, "no_speech_prob": 1.56129590592885e-12}, {"id": 290, "seek": 104204, "start": 1054.3999999999999, "end": 1054.62, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50983, 1779, 13, 50994], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12355110380384657, "compression_ratio": 1.4352331606217616, "no_speech_prob": 1.56129590592885e-12}, {"id": 291, "seek": 104204, "start": 1054.94, "end": 1058.04, "text": " The compiler throws its hands up, breaks the build, and yells at you.", "tokens": [51010, 440, 31958, 19251, 1080, 2377, 493, 11, 9857, 264, 1322, 11, 293, 48543, 412, 291, 13, 51165], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12355110380384657, "compression_ratio": 1.4352331606217616, "no_speech_prob": 1.56129590592885e-12}, {"id": 292, "seek": 105804, "start": 1058.04, "end": 1059.8, "text": " Just a wall of red text.", "tokens": [50365, 1449, 257, 2929, 295, 2182, 2487, 13, 50453], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.4029435475667318, "compression_ratio": 0.8048780487804879, "no_speech_prob": 1.304040100728876e-12}, {"id": 293, "seek": 105804, "start": 1060.0, "end": 1060.42, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50463, 7587, 13, 50484], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.4029435475667318, "compression_ratio": 0.8048780487804879, "no_speech_prob": 1.304040100728876e-12}, {"id": 294, "seek": 106042, "start": 1060.42, "end": 1064.66, "text": " In sphere pop, a type error is simply an early refusal event.", "tokens": [50365, 682, 16687, 1665, 11, 257, 2010, 6713, 307, 2935, 364, 2440, 48948, 2280, 13, 50577], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.26500654220581055, "compression_ratio": 0.953125, "no_speech_prob": 1.5189513058802562e-12}, {"id": 295, "seek": 106466, "start": 1064.66, "end": 1067.5600000000002, "text": " It is the bouncer successfully doing their job.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 307, 264, 272, 14296, 10727, 884, 641, 1691, 13, 50510], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17511526313987938, "compression_ratio": 1.5376344086021505, "no_speech_prob": 1.579450979727337e-12}, {"id": 296, "seek": 106466, "start": 1067.96, "end": 1074.0, "text": " It prevents an incoherent, mathematically unsound history from ever becoming a committed collapse.", "tokens": [50530, 467, 22367, 364, 834, 78, 511, 317, 11, 44003, 2693, 554, 2503, 490, 1562, 5617, 257, 7784, 15584, 13, 50832], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17511526313987938, "compression_ratio": 1.5376344086021505, "no_speech_prob": 1.579450979727337e-12}, {"id": 297, "seek": 106466, "start": 1074.22, "end": 1075.3600000000001, "text": " So it's not a bug.", "tokens": [50843, 407, 309, 311, 406, 257, 7426, 13, 50900], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17511526313987938, "compression_ratio": 1.5376344086021505, "no_speech_prob": 1.579450979727337e-12}, {"id": 298, "seek": 106466, "start": 1075.5800000000002, "end": 1075.92, "text": " No.", "tokens": [50911, 883, 13, 50928], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17511526313987938, "compression_ratio": 1.5376344086021505, "no_speech_prob": 1.579450979727337e-12}, {"id": 299, "seek": 106466, "start": 1076.26, "end": 1077.8400000000001, "text": " The error isn't a failure of the system.", "tokens": [50945, 440, 6713, 1943, 380, 257, 7763, 295, 264, 1185, 13, 51024], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17511526313987938, "compression_ratio": 1.5376344086021505, "no_speech_prob": 1.579450979727337e-12}, {"id": 300, "seek": 106466, "start": 1078.0600000000002, "end": 1081.8200000000002, "text": " It's a boundary condition successfully preventing bad history from forming.", "tokens": [51035, 467, 311, 257, 12866, 4188, 10727, 19965, 1578, 2503, 490, 15745, 13, 51223], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17511526313987938, "compression_ratio": 1.5376344086021505, "no_speech_prob": 1.579450979727337e-12}, {"id": 301, "seek": 108182, "start": 1081.82, "end": 1088.6799999999998, "text": " In fliction goes extremely deep into how this bouncer logic applies to complex, higher-order types,", "tokens": [50365, 682, 932, 4105, 1709, 4664, 2452, 666, 577, 341, 272, 14296, 9952, 13165, 281, 3997, 11, 2946, 12, 4687, 3467, 11, 50708], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13925671186603483, "compression_ratio": 1.6666666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.2594528284864959e-12}, {"id": 302, "seek": 108182, "start": 1089.2, "end": 1094.4399999999998, "text": " specifically pi types and sigma types, which are the heavy hitters in advanced dependent type theory.", "tokens": [50734, 4682, 3895, 3467, 293, 12771, 3467, 11, 597, 366, 264, 4676, 2045, 1559, 294, 7339, 12334, 2010, 5261, 13, 50996], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13925671186603483, "compression_ratio": 1.6666666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.2594528284864959e-12}, {"id": 303, "seek": 108182, "start": 1094.58, "end": 1095.82, "text": " They really are the foundation.", "tokens": [51003, 814, 534, 366, 264, 7030, 13, 51065], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13925671186603483, "compression_ratio": 1.6666666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.2594528284864959e-12}, {"id": 304, "seek": 108182, "start": 1095.8999999999999, "end": 1099.1599999999999, "text": " I always struggle with explaining these intuitively, so let's walk through them carefully.", "tokens": [51069, 286, 1009, 7799, 365, 13468, 613, 46506, 11, 370, 718, 311, 1792, 807, 552, 7500, 13, 51232], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13925671186603483, "compression_ratio": 1.6666666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.2594528284864959e-12}, {"id": 305, "seek": 108182, "start": 1099.28, "end": 1102.46, "text": " Let's start with the pi type, also known as the dependent product type.", "tokens": [51238, 961, 311, 722, 365, 264, 3895, 2010, 11, 611, 2570, 382, 264, 12334, 1674, 2010, 13, 51397], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13925671186603483, "compression_ratio": 1.6666666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.2594528284864959e-12}, {"id": 306, "seek": 108182, "start": 1103.06, "end": 1108.12, "text": " In flitching's framework, a pi type is described as a universal repair operator.", "tokens": [51427, 682, 932, 1549, 278, 311, 8388, 11, 257, 3895, 2010, 307, 7619, 382, 257, 11455, 10535, 12973, 13, 51680], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13925671186603483, "compression_ratio": 1.6666666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.2594528284864959e-12}, {"id": 307, "seek": 108182, "start": 1108.34, "end": 1111.34, "text": " In standard programming, this is akin to a function.", "tokens": [51691, 682, 3832, 9410, 11, 341, 307, 47540, 281, 257, 2445, 13, 51841], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13925671186603483, "compression_ratio": 1.6666666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.2594528284864959e-12}, {"id": 308, "seek": 111182, "start": 1111.82, "end": 1114.24, "text": " But in sphere pop, it acts as a guarantee.", "tokens": [50365, 583, 294, 16687, 1665, 11, 309, 10672, 382, 257, 10815, 13, 50486], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10877593897156797, "compression_ratio": 1.6993006993006994, "no_speech_prob": 1.9659354439510723e-12}, {"id": 309, "seek": 111182, "start": 1114.56, "end": 1115.3799999999999, "text": " A guarantee of what?", "tokens": [50502, 316, 10815, 295, 437, 30, 50543], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10877593897156797, "compression_ratio": 1.6993006993006994, "no_speech_prob": 1.9659354439510723e-12}, {"id": 310, "seek": 111182, "start": 1115.8999999999999, "end": 1121.98, "text": " A pi type takes any admissible history and guarantees that it can be transformed into another admissible history.", "tokens": [50569, 316, 3895, 2010, 2516, 604, 5910, 41073, 2503, 293, 32567, 300, 309, 393, 312, 16894, 666, 1071, 5910, 41073, 2503, 13, 50873], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10877593897156797, "compression_ratio": 1.6993006993006994, "no_speech_prob": 1.9659354439510723e-12}, {"id": 311, "seek": 111182, "start": 1122.36, "end": 1125.54, "text": " It is a promise that no matter what valid input you give it,", "tokens": [50892, 467, 307, 257, 6228, 300, 572, 1871, 437, 7363, 4846, 291, 976, 309, 11, 51051], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10877593897156797, "compression_ratio": 1.6993006993006994, "no_speech_prob": 1.9659354439510723e-12}, {"id": 312, "seek": 111182, "start": 1125.54, "end": 1129.56, "text": " it already knows how to safely continue the computation without hitting a refusal.", "tokens": [51051, 309, 1217, 3255, 577, 281, 11750, 2354, 264, 24903, 1553, 8850, 257, 48948, 13, 51252], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10877593897156797, "compression_ratio": 1.6993006993006994, "no_speech_prob": 1.9659354439510723e-12}, {"id": 313, "seek": 111182, "start": 1130.24, "end": 1135.96, "text": " So, if pi is the universal bouncer who knows exactly how to handle any VIP who walks in the door", "tokens": [51286, 407, 11, 498, 3895, 307, 264, 11455, 272, 14296, 567, 3255, 2293, 577, 281, 4813, 604, 29732, 567, 12896, 294, 264, 2853, 51572], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10877593897156797, "compression_ratio": 1.6993006993006994, "no_speech_prob": 1.9659354439510723e-12}, {"id": 314, "seek": 111182, "start": 1135.96, "end": 1139.26, "text": " and seamlessly route them to the right table, what is a sigma type?", "tokens": [51572, 293, 38083, 7955, 552, 281, 264, 558, 3199, 11, 437, 307, 257, 12771, 2010, 30, 51737], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10877593897156797, "compression_ratio": 1.6993006993006994, "no_speech_prob": 1.9659354439510723e-12}, {"id": 315, "seek": 113926, "start": 1139.26, "end": 1143.4, "text": " A sigma type, or dependent sum type, is a witness for pair.", "tokens": [50365, 316, 12771, 2010, 11, 420, 12334, 2408, 2010, 11, 307, 257, 7286, 337, 6119, 13, 50572], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11532760801769439, "compression_ratio": 1.628787878787879, "no_speech_prob": 1.7013935833115612e-12}, {"id": 316, "seek": 113926, "start": 1144.26, "end": 1151.92, "text": " It represents a pair of things, where the validity of the second thing depends entirely on the specific history of the first thing you admitted.", "tokens": [50615, 467, 8855, 257, 6119, 295, 721, 11, 689, 264, 40943, 295, 264, 1150, 551, 5946, 7696, 322, 264, 2685, 2503, 295, 264, 700, 551, 291, 14920, 13, 50998], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11532760801769439, "compression_ratio": 1.628787878787879, "no_speech_prob": 1.7013935833115612e-12}, {"id": 317, "seek": 113926, "start": 1152.1, "end": 1153.96, "text": " Okay, let's use a real-world example here.", "tokens": [51007, 1033, 11, 718, 311, 764, 257, 957, 12, 13217, 1365, 510, 13, 51100], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11532760801769439, "compression_ratio": 1.628787878787879, "no_speech_prob": 1.7013935833115612e-12}, {"id": 318, "seek": 113926, "start": 1154.3799999999999, "end": 1158.12, "text": " Let's say you are writing software for a bank to execute a wire transfer.", "tokens": [51121, 961, 311, 584, 291, 366, 3579, 4722, 337, 257, 3765, 281, 14483, 257, 6234, 5003, 13, 51308], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11532760801769439, "compression_ratio": 1.628787878787879, "no_speech_prob": 1.7013935833115612e-12}, {"id": 319, "seek": 113926, "start": 1158.54, "end": 1164.08, "text": " A traditional program might just take two inputs, an account number, and a transfer amount.", "tokens": [51329, 316, 5164, 1461, 1062, 445, 747, 732, 15743, 11, 364, 2696, 1230, 11, 293, 257, 5003, 2372, 13, 51606], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11532760801769439, "compression_ratio": 1.628787878787879, "no_speech_prob": 1.7013935833115612e-12}, {"id": 320, "seek": 113926, "start": 1164.24, "end": 1164.78, "text": " Pretty standard.", "tokens": [51614, 10693, 3832, 13, 51641], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11532760801769439, "compression_ratio": 1.628787878787879, "no_speech_prob": 1.7013935833115612e-12}, {"id": 321, "seek": 116478, "start": 1164.78, "end": 1170.6, "text": " But what if the account doesn't have enough money, the program has to run, check the balance, realize there's an error,", "tokens": [50365, 583, 437, 498, 264, 2696, 1177, 380, 362, 1547, 1460, 11, 264, 1461, 575, 281, 1190, 11, 1520, 264, 4772, 11, 4325, 456, 311, 364, 6713, 11, 50656], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13770826721191406, "compression_ratio": 1.6742671009771988, "no_speech_prob": 1.6426212603656842e-12}, {"id": 322, "seek": 116478, "start": 1170.86, "end": 1173.68, "text": " and try to stop the transaction before the money is gone?", "tokens": [50669, 293, 853, 281, 1590, 264, 14425, 949, 264, 1460, 307, 2780, 30, 50810], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13770826721191406, "compression_ratio": 1.6742671009771988, "no_speech_prob": 1.6426212603656842e-12}, {"id": 323, "seek": 116478, "start": 1173.82, "end": 1174.26, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50817, 7587, 13, 50839], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13770826721191406, "compression_ratio": 1.6742671009771988, "no_speech_prob": 1.6426212603656842e-12}, {"id": 324, "seek": 116478, "start": 1174.58, "end": 1179.6399999999999, "text": " Which requires writing a bunch of manual error checking code that is so thrown to human oversight.", "tokens": [50855, 3013, 7029, 3579, 257, 3840, 295, 9688, 6713, 8568, 3089, 300, 307, 370, 11732, 281, 1952, 29146, 13, 51108], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13770826721191406, "compression_ratio": 1.6742671009771988, "no_speech_prob": 1.6426212603656842e-12}, {"id": 325, "seek": 116478, "start": 1180.7, "end": 1182.82, "text": " A sigma type solves this structurally.", "tokens": [51161, 316, 12771, 2010, 39890, 341, 6594, 6512, 13, 51267], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13770826721191406, "compression_ratio": 1.6742671009771988, "no_speech_prob": 1.6426212603656842e-12}, {"id": 326, "seek": 116478, "start": 1182.96, "end": 1183.54, "text": " How so?", "tokens": [51274, 1012, 370, 30, 51303], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13770826721191406, "compression_ratio": 1.6742671009771988, "no_speech_prob": 1.6426212603656842e-12}, {"id": 327, "seek": 116478, "start": 1183.78, "end": 1186.74, "text": " In our bank example, a sigma type would require a pair.", "tokens": [51315, 682, 527, 3765, 1365, 11, 257, 12771, 2010, 576, 3651, 257, 6119, 13, 51463], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13770826721191406, "compression_ratio": 1.6742671009771988, "no_speech_prob": 1.6426212603656842e-12}, {"id": 328, "seek": 116478, "start": 1187.3, "end": 1193.08, "text": " The first part is the transfer request, and the second part is a cryptographic proof that the account holds sufficient funds.", "tokens": [51491, 440, 700, 644, 307, 264, 5003, 5308, 11, 293, 264, 1150, 644, 307, 257, 9844, 12295, 8177, 300, 264, 2696, 9190, 11563, 8271, 13, 51780], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13770826721191406, "compression_ratio": 1.6742671009771988, "no_speech_prob": 1.6426212603656842e-12}, {"id": 329, "seek": 119308, "start": 1193.08, "end": 1197.1399999999999, "text": " The bouncer will not even look at the second part of the pair until the first part is validated.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 272, 14296, 486, 406, 754, 574, 412, 264, 1150, 644, 295, 264, 6119, 1826, 264, 700, 644, 307, 40693, 13, 50568], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14406288794751437, "compression_ratio": 1.6539923954372624, "no_speech_prob": 1.3250609377096767e-12}, {"id": 330, "seek": 119308, "start": 1197.58, "end": 1198.54, "text": " It's the bouncer saying,", "tokens": [50590, 467, 311, 264, 272, 14296, 1566, 11, 50638], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14406288794751437, "compression_ratio": 1.6539923954372624, "no_speech_prob": 1.3250609377096767e-12}, {"id": 331, "seek": 119308, "start": 1198.76, "end": 1202.26, "text": " You can only bring your plus one into the club if I verify your ID first,", "tokens": [50649, 509, 393, 787, 1565, 428, 1804, 472, 666, 264, 6482, 498, 286, 16888, 428, 7348, 700, 11, 50824], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14406288794751437, "compression_ratio": 1.6539923954372624, "no_speech_prob": 1.3250609377096767e-12}, {"id": 332, "seek": 119308, "start": 1202.46, "end": 1205.96, "text": " and your plus one's entry is strictly dependent on you being cleared.", "tokens": [50834, 293, 428, 1804, 472, 311, 8729, 307, 20792, 12334, 322, 291, 885, 19725, 13, 51009], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14406288794751437, "compression_ratio": 1.6539923954372624, "no_speech_prob": 1.3250609377096767e-12}, {"id": 333, "seek": 119308, "start": 1206.12, "end": 1206.4399999999998, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [51017, 1079, 13, 51033], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14406288794751437, "compression_ratio": 1.6539923954372624, "no_speech_prob": 1.3250609377096767e-12}, {"id": 334, "seek": 119308, "start": 1206.8799999999999, "end": 1212.96, "text": " The program cannot physically be written or executed without providing the proof of funds up front.", "tokens": [51055, 440, 1461, 2644, 9762, 312, 3720, 420, 17577, 1553, 6530, 264, 8177, 295, 8271, 493, 1868, 13, 51359], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14406288794751437, "compression_ratio": 1.6539923954372624, "no_speech_prob": 1.3250609377096767e-12}, {"id": 335, "seek": 119308, "start": 1213.36, "end": 1216.76, "text": " The structure on the type prevents the error from ever existing.", "tokens": [51379, 440, 3877, 322, 264, 2010, 22367, 264, 6713, 490, 1562, 6741, 13, 51549], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14406288794751437, "compression_ratio": 1.6539923954372624, "no_speech_prob": 1.3250609377096767e-12}, {"id": 336, "seek": 121676, "start": 1216.76, "end": 1217.6, "text": " Precisely.", "tokens": [50365, 48746, 736, 13, 50407], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20348349133053342, "compression_ratio": 1.4903846153846154, "no_speech_prob": 1.5858753112801827e-12}, {"id": 337, "seek": 121676, "start": 1218.14, "end": 1224.78, "text": " The refusal structure forces the programmer to construct a valid history of proof before the computation can proceed.", "tokens": [50434, 440, 48948, 3877, 5874, 264, 32116, 281, 7690, 257, 7363, 2503, 295, 8177, 949, 264, 24903, 393, 8991, 13, 50766], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20348349133053342, "compression_ratio": 1.4903846153846154, "no_speech_prob": 1.5858753112801827e-12}, {"id": 338, "seek": 121676, "start": 1225.3, "end": 1230.44, "text": " And this leads us directly into one of the most profound realizations in modern computer science,", "tokens": [50792, 400, 341, 6689, 505, 3838, 666, 472, 295, 264, 881, 14382, 957, 14455, 294, 4363, 3820, 3497, 11, 51049], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20348349133053342, "compression_ratio": 1.4903846153846154, "no_speech_prob": 1.5858753112801827e-12}, {"id": 339, "seek": 121676, "start": 1230.62, "end": 1233.26, "text": " which SpherePop completely reinterprets.", "tokens": [51058, 597, 318, 6605, 38677, 2584, 319, 5106, 3712, 1373, 13, 51190], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20348349133053342, "compression_ratio": 1.4903846153846154, "no_speech_prob": 1.5858753112801827e-12}, {"id": 340, "seek": 121676, "start": 1233.42, "end": 1234.0, "text": " Which is?", "tokens": [51198, 3013, 307, 30, 51227], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20348349133053342, "compression_ratio": 1.4903846153846154, "no_speech_prob": 1.5858753112801827e-12}, {"id": 341, "seek": 121676, "start": 1234.1, "end": 1235.4, "text": " The Curry-Howard correspondence.", "tokens": [51232, 440, 34789, 12, 6462, 515, 38135, 13, 51297], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20348349133053342, "compression_ratio": 1.4903846153846154, "no_speech_prob": 1.5858753112801827e-12}, {"id": 342, "seek": 123540, "start": 1235.4, "end": 1237.1000000000001, "text": " Oh, the Curry-Howard correspondence.", "tokens": [50365, 876, 11, 264, 34789, 12, 6462, 515, 38135, 13, 50450], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15172835640285326, "compression_ratio": 1.6630434782608696, "no_speech_prob": 3.1663634388057194e-12}, {"id": 343, "seek": 123540, "start": 1237.2800000000002, "end": 1242.52, "text": " For anyone who hasn't encountered this, it is arguably one of the most beautiful, elegant concepts in all of mathematics.", "tokens": [50459, 1171, 2878, 567, 6132, 380, 20381, 341, 11, 309, 307, 26771, 472, 295, 264, 881, 2238, 11, 21117, 10392, 294, 439, 295, 18666, 13, 50721], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15172835640285326, "compression_ratio": 1.6630434782608696, "no_speech_prob": 3.1663634388057194e-12}, {"id": 344, "seek": 123540, "start": 1242.7800000000002, "end": 1243.24, "text": " It really is.", "tokens": [50734, 467, 534, 307, 13, 50757], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15172835640285326, "compression_ratio": 1.6630434782608696, "no_speech_prob": 3.1663634388057194e-12}, {"id": 345, "seek": 123540, "start": 1243.42, "end": 1249.8400000000001, "text": " It is the realization, discovered decades ago, that computer programs and mathematical proofs are not just similar.", "tokens": [50766, 467, 307, 264, 25138, 11, 6941, 7878, 2057, 11, 300, 3820, 4268, 293, 18894, 8177, 82, 366, 406, 445, 2531, 13, 51087], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15172835640285326, "compression_ratio": 1.6630434782608696, "no_speech_prob": 3.1663634388057194e-12}, {"id": 346, "seek": 123540, "start": 1249.96, "end": 1251.3400000000001, "text": " They are the exact same thing.", "tokens": [51093, 814, 366, 264, 1900, 912, 551, 13, 51162], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15172835640285326, "compression_ratio": 1.6630434782608696, "no_speech_prob": 3.1663634388057194e-12}, {"id": 347, "seek": 123540, "start": 1251.98, "end": 1253.2, "text": " Propositions as types.", "tokens": [51194, 21944, 329, 2451, 382, 3467, 13, 51255], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15172835640285326, "compression_ratio": 1.6630434782608696, "no_speech_prob": 3.1663634388057194e-12}, {"id": 348, "seek": 123540, "start": 1253.68, "end": 1255.8200000000002, "text": " It is a stunning equivalence.", "tokens": [51279, 467, 307, 257, 18550, 9052, 655, 13, 51386], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15172835640285326, "compression_ratio": 1.6630434782608696, "no_speech_prob": 3.1663634388057194e-12}, {"id": 349, "seek": 123540, "start": 1256.0, "end": 1260.3000000000002, "text": " Under Curry-Howard, a mathematical proposition, a statement you want to prove is true,", "tokens": [51395, 6974, 34789, 12, 6462, 515, 11, 257, 18894, 24830, 11, 257, 5629, 291, 528, 281, 7081, 307, 2074, 11, 51610], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15172835640285326, "compression_ratio": 1.6630434782608696, "no_speech_prob": 3.1663634388057194e-12}, {"id": 350, "seek": 126030, "start": 1260.3, "end": 1263.36, "text": " is directly equivalent to a type in programming.", "tokens": [50365, 307, 3838, 10344, 281, 257, 2010, 294, 9410, 13, 50518], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16021047071977096, "compression_ratio": 1.75, "no_speech_prob": 1.7015509010467889e-12}, {"id": 351, "seek": 126030, "start": 1263.96, "end": 1270.12, "text": " And the formal proof of that proposition is directly equivalent to a program that successfully outputs that type.", "tokens": [50548, 400, 264, 9860, 8177, 295, 300, 24830, 307, 3838, 10344, 281, 257, 1461, 300, 10727, 23930, 300, 2010, 13, 50856], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16021047071977096, "compression_ratio": 1.75, "no_speech_prob": 1.7015509010467889e-12}, {"id": 352, "seek": 126030, "start": 1270.24, "end": 1272.2, "text": " Right. If you can code it, you can prove it.", "tokens": [50862, 1779, 13, 759, 291, 393, 3089, 309, 11, 291, 393, 7081, 309, 13, 50960], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16021047071977096, "compression_ratio": 1.75, "no_speech_prob": 1.7015509010467889e-12}, {"id": 353, "seek": 126030, "start": 1272.3, "end": 1272.74, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50965, 7587, 13, 50987], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16021047071977096, "compression_ratio": 1.75, "no_speech_prob": 1.7015509010467889e-12}, {"id": 354, "seek": 126030, "start": 1273.44, "end": 1275.8799999999999, "text": " If you can write a program that compiles to a certain type,", "tokens": [51022, 759, 291, 393, 2464, 257, 1461, 300, 715, 4680, 281, 257, 1629, 2010, 11, 51144], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16021047071977096, "compression_ratio": 1.75, "no_speech_prob": 1.7015509010467889e-12}, {"id": 355, "seek": 126030, "start": 1276.18, "end": 1278.6, "text": " you have mathematically proven the corresponding proposition.", "tokens": [51159, 291, 362, 44003, 12785, 264, 11760, 24830, 13, 51280], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16021047071977096, "compression_ratio": 1.75, "no_speech_prob": 1.7015509010467889e-12}, {"id": 356, "seek": 126030, "start": 1279.56, "end": 1284.12, "text": " SpherePop takes this elegant concept and views it entirely through the lens of history.", "tokens": [51328, 318, 6605, 38677, 2516, 341, 21117, 3410, 293, 6809, 309, 7696, 807, 264, 6765, 295, 2503, 13, 51556], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16021047071977096, "compression_ratio": 1.75, "no_speech_prob": 1.7015509010467889e-12}, {"id": 357, "seek": 126030, "start": 1284.54, "end": 1286.8799999999999, "text": " So how does the bouncer analogy work here?", "tokens": [51577, 407, 577, 775, 264, 272, 14296, 21663, 589, 510, 30, 51694], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16021047071977096, "compression_ratio": 1.75, "no_speech_prob": 1.7015509010467889e-12}, {"id": 358, "seek": 128688, "start": 1286.88, "end": 1293.38, "text": " To prove a proposition in SpherePop is to construct a history that the proposition's bouncer cannot refuse.", "tokens": [50365, 1407, 7081, 257, 24830, 294, 318, 6605, 38677, 307, 281, 7690, 257, 2503, 300, 264, 24830, 311, 272, 14296, 2644, 16791, 13, 50690], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16845689879523384, "compression_ratio": 1.8013468013468013, "no_speech_prob": 1.854066162751411e-12}, {"id": 359, "seek": 128688, "start": 1293.66, "end": 1295.0, "text": " That is the exact mechanism.", "tokens": [50704, 663, 307, 264, 1900, 7513, 13, 50771], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16845689879523384, "compression_ratio": 1.8013468013468013, "no_speech_prob": 1.854066162751411e-12}, {"id": 360, "seek": 128688, "start": 1295.5400000000002, "end": 1297.18, "text": " You are tasked with proving a theorem.", "tokens": [50798, 509, 366, 38621, 365, 27221, 257, 20904, 13, 50880], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16845689879523384, "compression_ratio": 1.8013468013468013, "no_speech_prob": 1.854066162751411e-12}, {"id": 361, "seek": 128688, "start": 1297.68, "end": 1298.7800000000002, "text": " You start combining events.", "tokens": [50905, 509, 722, 21928, 3931, 13, 50960], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16845689879523384, "compression_ratio": 1.8013468013468013, "no_speech_prob": 1.854066162751411e-12}, {"id": 362, "seek": 128688, "start": 1298.9, "end": 1299.3000000000002, "text": " You pop.", "tokens": [50966, 509, 1665, 13, 50986], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16845689879523384, "compression_ratio": 1.8013468013468013, "no_speech_prob": 1.854066162751411e-12}, {"id": 363, "seek": 128688, "start": 1299.44, "end": 1299.98, "text": " You bind.", "tokens": [50993, 509, 14786, 13, 51020], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16845689879523384, "compression_ratio": 1.8013468013468013, "no_speech_prob": 1.854066162751411e-12}, {"id": 364, "seek": 128688, "start": 1300.1200000000001, "end": 1300.5800000000002, "text": " You meld.", "tokens": [51027, 509, 4795, 67, 13, 51050], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16845689879523384, "compression_ratio": 1.8013468013468013, "no_speech_prob": 1.854066162751411e-12}, {"id": 365, "seek": 128688, "start": 1300.8000000000002, "end": 1303.22, "text": " You are building up a sequence of actions in the journal.", "tokens": [51061, 509, 366, 2390, 493, 257, 8310, 295, 5909, 294, 264, 6708, 13, 51182], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16845689879523384, "compression_ratio": 1.8013468013468013, "no_speech_prob": 1.854066162751411e-12}, {"id": 366, "seek": 128688, "start": 1303.38, "end": 1304.14, "text": " Page by page.", "tokens": [51190, 21217, 538, 3028, 13, 51228], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16845689879523384, "compression_ratio": 1.8013468013468013, "no_speech_prob": 1.854066162751411e-12}, {"id": 367, "seek": 128688, "start": 1304.24, "end": 1304.96, "text": " Page by page.", "tokens": [51233, 21217, 538, 3028, 13, 51269], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16845689879523384, "compression_ratio": 1.8013468013468013, "no_speech_prob": 1.854066162751411e-12}, {"id": 368, "seek": 128688, "start": 1305.0400000000002, "end": 1305.2, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51273, 1779, 13, 51281], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16845689879523384, "compression_ratio": 1.8013468013468013, "no_speech_prob": 1.854066162751411e-12}, {"id": 369, "seek": 128688, "start": 1305.38, "end": 1308.7, "text": " You keep building this history until you present it to the type representing your theorem,", "tokens": [51290, 509, 1066, 2390, 341, 2503, 1826, 291, 1974, 309, 281, 264, 2010, 13460, 428, 20904, 11, 51456], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16845689879523384, "compression_ratio": 1.8013468013468013, "no_speech_prob": 1.854066162751411e-12}, {"id": 370, "seek": 128688, "start": 1308.98, "end": 1312.44, "text": " and the bouncer has absolutely no logical choice but to admit you.", "tokens": [51470, 293, 264, 272, 14296, 575, 3122, 572, 14978, 3922, 457, 281, 9796, 291, 13, 51643], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16845689879523384, "compression_ratio": 1.8013468013468013, "no_speech_prob": 1.854066162751411e-12}, {"id": 371, "seek": 128688, "start": 1313.18, "end": 1315.88, "text": " You have provided a completely unrefusable history.", "tokens": [51680, 509, 362, 5649, 257, 2584, 20584, 69, 301, 712, 2503, 13, 51815], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16845689879523384, "compression_ratio": 1.8013468013468013, "no_speech_prob": 1.854066162751411e-12}, {"id": 372, "seek": 131588, "start": 1315.88, "end": 1317.64, "text": " That history is the proof.", "tokens": [50365, 663, 2503, 307, 264, 8177, 13, 50453], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16564500098134957, "compression_ratio": 1.6144067796610169, "no_speech_prob": 1.4782080724404234e-12}, {"id": 373, "seek": 131588, "start": 1318.14, "end": 1318.44, "text": " Wow.", "tokens": [50478, 3153, 13, 50493], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16564500098134957, "compression_ratio": 1.6144067796610169, "no_speech_prob": 1.4782080724404234e-12}, {"id": 374, "seek": 131588, "start": 1318.66, "end": 1320.0, "text": " Okay, but what about the opposite?", "tokens": [50504, 1033, 11, 457, 437, 466, 264, 6182, 30, 50571], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16564500098134957, "compression_ratio": 1.6144067796610169, "no_speech_prob": 1.4782080724404234e-12}, {"id": 375, "seek": 131588, "start": 1320.66, "end": 1321.5800000000002, "text": " What is a contradiction?", "tokens": [50604, 708, 307, 257, 34937, 30, 50650], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16564500098134957, "compression_ratio": 1.6144067796610169, "no_speech_prob": 1.4782080724404234e-12}, {"id": 376, "seek": 131588, "start": 1322.1200000000001, "end": 1325.5600000000002, "text": " If I want to prove that something is false, how does that work in the journal?", "tokens": [50677, 759, 286, 528, 281, 7081, 300, 746, 307, 7908, 11, 577, 775, 300, 589, 294, 264, 6708, 30, 50849], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16564500098134957, "compression_ratio": 1.6144067796610169, "no_speech_prob": 1.4782080724404234e-12}, {"id": 377, "seek": 131588, "start": 1326.14, "end": 1328.92, "text": " In traditional logic, contradiction is pretty straightforward.", "tokens": [50878, 682, 5164, 9952, 11, 34937, 307, 1238, 15325, 13, 51017], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16564500098134957, "compression_ratio": 1.6144067796610169, "no_speech_prob": 1.4782080724404234e-12}, {"id": 378, "seek": 131588, "start": 1329.42, "end": 1333.9, "text": " It's the rule that A and not A cannot both be true at the same time.", "tokens": [51042, 467, 311, 264, 4978, 300, 316, 293, 406, 316, 2644, 1293, 312, 2074, 412, 264, 912, 565, 13, 51266], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16564500098134957, "compression_ratio": 1.6144067796610169, "no_speech_prob": 1.4782080724404234e-12}, {"id": 379, "seek": 131588, "start": 1334.0, "end": 1338.0200000000002, "text": " In a state-based system, a contradiction just evaluates false and you move on.", "tokens": [51271, 682, 257, 1785, 12, 6032, 1185, 11, 257, 34937, 445, 6133, 1024, 7908, 293, 291, 1286, 322, 13, 51472], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16564500098134957, "compression_ratio": 1.6144067796610169, "no_speech_prob": 1.4782080724404234e-12}, {"id": 380, "seek": 133802, "start": 1338.02, "end": 1344.56, "text": " But in sphere pop, negation or proving a contradiction is a much more rigorous historical event.", "tokens": [50365, 583, 294, 16687, 1665, 11, 2485, 399, 420, 27221, 257, 34937, 307, 257, 709, 544, 29882, 8584, 2280, 13, 50692], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12953861704412498, "compression_ratio": 1.6580645161290322, "no_speech_prob": 1.6488038148340656e-12}, {"id": 381, "seek": 133802, "start": 1344.8799999999999, "end": 1353.72, "text": " A contradiction occurs when you have a history that admits a continuation but also admits a structural rule proving that very same continuation is inadmissible.", "tokens": [50708, 316, 34937, 11843, 562, 291, 362, 257, 2503, 300, 46682, 257, 29357, 457, 611, 46682, 257, 15067, 4978, 27221, 300, 588, 912, 29357, 307, 42148, 76, 41073, 13, 51150], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12953861704412498, "compression_ratio": 1.6580645161290322, "no_speech_prob": 1.6488038148340656e-12}, {"id": 382, "seek": 135372, "start": 1353.72, "end": 1356.4, "text": " It's a paradox written in pen in the journal.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 311, 257, 26221, 3720, 294, 3435, 294, 264, 6708, 13, 50499], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14131679349732632, "compression_ratio": 1.6730769230769231, "no_speech_prob": 1.9276305811971595e-12}, {"id": 383, "seek": 135372, "start": 1356.74, "end": 1362.76, "text": " You have a page that says, I must tune left, and the exact same page has a bound rule that says turning left is mathematically impossible.", "tokens": [50516, 509, 362, 257, 3028, 300, 1619, 11, 286, 1633, 10864, 1411, 11, 293, 264, 1900, 912, 3028, 575, 257, 5472, 4978, 300, 1619, 6246, 1411, 307, 44003, 6243, 13, 50817], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14131679349732632, "compression_ratio": 1.6730769230769231, "no_speech_prob": 1.9276305811971595e-12}, {"id": 384, "seek": 135372, "start": 1363.14, "end": 1368.78, "text": " And because the history is monotonic and cannot be erased, the system cannot just shrug and ignore the paradox.", "tokens": [50836, 400, 570, 264, 2503, 307, 1108, 310, 11630, 293, 2644, 312, 38359, 11, 264, 1185, 2644, 445, 9884, 697, 293, 11200, 264, 26221, 13, 51118], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14131679349732632, "compression_ratio": 1.6730769230769231, "no_speech_prob": 1.9276305811971595e-12}, {"id": 385, "seek": 135372, "start": 1369.02, "end": 1371.3600000000001, "text": " It forces a collapse into impossibility.", "tokens": [51130, 467, 5874, 257, 15584, 666, 38802, 2841, 13, 51247], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14131679349732632, "compression_ratio": 1.6730769230769231, "no_speech_prob": 1.9276305811971595e-12}, {"id": 386, "seek": 135372, "start": 1371.48, "end": 1373.28, "text": " It just folds in on itself.", "tokens": [51253, 467, 445, 31341, 294, 322, 2564, 13, 51343], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14131679349732632, "compression_ratio": 1.6730769230769231, "no_speech_prob": 1.9276305811971595e-12}, {"id": 387, "seek": 135372, "start": 1373.38, "end": 1376.28, "text": " The refusal structure completely consumes that branch of computation.", "tokens": [51348, 440, 48948, 3877, 2584, 48823, 300, 9819, 295, 24903, 13, 51493], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14131679349732632, "compression_ratio": 1.6730769230769231, "no_speech_prob": 1.9276305811971595e-12}, {"id": 388, "seek": 137628, "start": 1376.28, "end": 1383.02, "text": " It is a much stronger, more structurally sound form of negation than just flipping a Boolean bit from true to false.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 307, 257, 709, 7249, 11, 544, 6594, 6512, 1626, 1254, 295, 2485, 399, 813, 445, 26886, 257, 23351, 28499, 857, 490, 2074, 281, 7908, 13, 50702], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13341782156345064, "compression_ratio": 1.6118881118881119, "no_speech_prob": 1.6881494032533473e-12}, {"id": 389, "seek": 137628, "start": 1383.54, "end": 1385.06, "text": " So what does this all mean?", "tokens": [50728, 407, 437, 775, 341, 439, 914, 30, 50804], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13341782156345064, "compression_ratio": 1.6118881118881119, "no_speech_prob": 1.6881494032533473e-12}, {"id": 390, "seek": 137628, "start": 1385.18, "end": 1387.02, "text": " Let's bring this back down to earth for you, the listener.", "tokens": [50810, 961, 311, 1565, 341, 646, 760, 281, 4120, 337, 291, 11, 264, 31569, 13, 50902], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13341782156345064, "compression_ratio": 1.6118881118881119, "no_speech_prob": 1.6881494032533473e-12}, {"id": 391, "seek": 137628, "start": 1387.56, "end": 1388.6, "text": " What does this all mean for you?", "tokens": [50929, 708, 775, 341, 439, 914, 337, 291, 30, 50981], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13341782156345064, "compression_ratio": 1.6118881118881119, "no_speech_prob": 1.6881494032533473e-12}, {"id": 392, "seek": 137628, "start": 1389.08, "end": 1395.66, "text": " Why should you care about the philosophical difference between historical equivalence and traditional definitional equality?", "tokens": [51005, 1545, 820, 291, 1127, 466, 264, 25066, 2649, 1296, 8584, 9052, 655, 293, 5164, 1561, 2628, 14949, 30, 51334], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13341782156345064, "compression_ratio": 1.6118881118881119, "no_speech_prob": 1.6881494032533473e-12}, {"id": 393, "seek": 137628, "start": 1396.0, "end": 1397.66, "text": " It sounds super abstract, I know.", "tokens": [51351, 467, 3263, 1687, 12649, 11, 286, 458, 13, 51434], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13341782156345064, "compression_ratio": 1.6118881118881119, "no_speech_prob": 1.6881494032533473e-12}, {"id": 394, "seek": 137628, "start": 1397.7, "end": 1397.94, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51436, 1779, 13, 51448], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13341782156345064, "compression_ratio": 1.6118881118881119, "no_speech_prob": 1.6881494032533473e-12}, {"id": 395, "seek": 137628, "start": 1398.1399999999999, "end": 1401.04, "text": " But let's say you were building a massive software system.", "tokens": [51458, 583, 718, 311, 584, 291, 645, 2390, 257, 5994, 4722, 1185, 13, 51603], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13341782156345064, "compression_ratio": 1.6118881118881119, "no_speech_prob": 1.6881494032533473e-12}, {"id": 396, "seek": 140104, "start": 1401.04, "end": 1405.5, "text": " Maybe it's a back end for a health care database tracking patient medications.", "tokens": [50365, 2704, 309, 311, 257, 646, 917, 337, 257, 1585, 1127, 8149, 11603, 4537, 17504, 13, 50588], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12832095406272195, "compression_ratio": 1.6651982378854626, "no_speech_prob": 1.5251228014864782e-12}, {"id": 397, "seek": 140104, "start": 1405.84, "end": 1410.76, "text": " Or maybe you are formulating a complex legal argument for a high stakes trial.", "tokens": [50605, 1610, 1310, 291, 366, 1254, 12162, 257, 3997, 5089, 6770, 337, 257, 1090, 28429, 7308, 13, 50851], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12832095406272195, "compression_ratio": 1.6651982378854626, "no_speech_prob": 1.5251228014864782e-12}, {"id": 398, "seek": 140104, "start": 1411.2, "end": 1415.12, "text": " You don't just want to know that conclusion X equals conclusion Y.", "tokens": [50873, 509, 500, 380, 445, 528, 281, 458, 300, 10063, 1783, 6915, 10063, 398, 13, 51069], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12832095406272195, "compression_ratio": 1.6651982378854626, "no_speech_prob": 1.5251228014864782e-12}, {"id": 399, "seek": 140104, "start": 1415.22, "end": 1416.1599999999999, "text": " No, you need the Y.", "tokens": [51074, 883, 11, 291, 643, 264, 398, 13, 51121], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12832095406272195, "compression_ratio": 1.6651982378854626, "no_speech_prob": 1.5251228014864782e-12}, {"id": 400, "seek": 140104, "start": 1416.24, "end": 1416.68, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [51125, 7587, 13, 51147], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12832095406272195, "compression_ratio": 1.6651982378854626, "no_speech_prob": 1.5251228014864782e-12}, {"id": 401, "seek": 140104, "start": 1416.86, "end": 1422.28, "text": " If a patient is given a substitute drug, you don't just want the computer to say drug X equals drug Y.", "tokens": [51156, 759, 257, 4537, 307, 2212, 257, 15802, 4110, 11, 291, 500, 380, 445, 528, 264, 3820, 281, 584, 4110, 1783, 6915, 4110, 398, 13, 51427], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12832095406272195, "compression_ratio": 1.6651982378854626, "no_speech_prob": 1.5251228014864782e-12}, {"id": 402, "seek": 140104, "start": 1422.3799999999999, "end": 1423.3799999999999, "text": " You want the receipt.", "tokens": [51432, 509, 528, 264, 33882, 13, 51482], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12832095406272195, "compression_ratio": 1.6651982378854626, "no_speech_prob": 1.5251228014864782e-12}, {"id": 403, "seek": 142338, "start": 1423.38, "end": 1431.42, "text": " You want the exact, unforgeable, historical proof replay of why X is legally and chemically allowed to replace Y.", "tokens": [50365, 509, 528, 264, 1900, 11, 31411, 432, 712, 11, 8584, 8177, 23836, 295, 983, 1783, 307, 21106, 293, 4771, 984, 4350, 281, 7406, 398, 13, 50767], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11978314057835993, "compression_ratio": 1.6072727272727272, "no_speech_prob": 1.9813577861738096e-12}, {"id": 404, "seek": 142338, "start": 1431.6200000000001, "end": 1435.98, "text": " And providing that exact receipt is the purpose of the replay operator in SpherePop.", "tokens": [50777, 400, 6530, 300, 1900, 33882, 307, 264, 4334, 295, 264, 23836, 12973, 294, 318, 6605, 38677, 13, 50995], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11978314057835993, "compression_ratio": 1.6072727272727272, "no_speech_prob": 1.9813577861738096e-12}, {"id": 405, "seek": 142338, "start": 1436.6000000000001, "end": 1445.64, "text": " In our daily lives, observable equality, like the simple fact that a generic drug has the same active ingredient as a name brand drug, is just a projection.", "tokens": [51026, 682, 527, 5212, 2909, 11, 9951, 712, 14949, 11, 411, 264, 2199, 1186, 300, 257, 19577, 4110, 575, 264, 912, 4967, 14751, 382, 257, 1315, 3360, 4110, 11, 307, 445, 257, 22743, 13, 51478], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11978314057835993, "compression_ratio": 1.6072727272727272, "no_speech_prob": 1.9813577861738096e-12}, {"id": 406, "seek": 142338, "start": 1445.8200000000002, "end": 1446.3000000000002, "text": " A shadow.", "tokens": [51487, 316, 8576, 13, 51511], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11978314057835993, "compression_ratio": 1.6072727272727272, "no_speech_prob": 1.9813577861738096e-12}, {"id": 407, "seek": 142338, "start": 1446.64, "end": 1451.5600000000002, "text": " It's a surface level shadow of a much deeper, richer historical equivalence.", "tokens": [51528, 467, 311, 257, 3753, 1496, 8576, 295, 257, 709, 7731, 11, 29021, 8584, 9052, 655, 13, 51774], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11978314057835993, "compression_ratio": 1.6072727272727272, "no_speech_prob": 1.9813577861738096e-12}, {"id": 408, "seek": 145156, "start": 1451.56, "end": 1458.96, "text": " When we use the replay operator, we reconstruct the observable computation strictly determined by the history.", "tokens": [50365, 1133, 321, 764, 264, 23836, 12973, 11, 321, 31499, 264, 9951, 712, 24903, 20792, 9540, 538, 264, 2503, 13, 50735], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09613796760295999, "compression_ratio": 1.657258064516129, "no_speech_prob": 1.796740273923847e-12}, {"id": 409, "seek": 145156, "start": 1459.54, "end": 1463.04, "text": " We rewind the journal and watch the ink dry all over again.", "tokens": [50764, 492, 41458, 264, 6708, 293, 1159, 264, 11276, 4016, 439, 670, 797, 13, 50939], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09613796760295999, "compression_ratio": 1.657258064516129, "no_speech_prob": 1.796740273923847e-12}, {"id": 410, "seek": 145156, "start": 1463.1399999999999, "end": 1463.56, "text": " Oh, that's beautiful.", "tokens": [50944, 876, 11, 300, 311, 2238, 13, 50965], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09613796760295999, "compression_ratio": 1.657258064516129, "no_speech_prob": 1.796740273923847e-12}, {"id": 411, "seek": 145156, "start": 1464.3799999999999, "end": 1477.86, "text": " If two distinct histories, say the research and development of the name brand drug and the reverse engineering of the generic drug replay to the exact same observable chemical result, they are deemed replay equivalent.", "tokens": [51006, 759, 732, 10644, 30631, 11, 584, 264, 2132, 293, 3250, 295, 264, 1315, 3360, 4110, 293, 264, 9943, 7043, 295, 264, 19577, 4110, 23836, 281, 264, 1900, 912, 9951, 712, 7313, 1874, 11, 436, 366, 27637, 23836, 10344, 13, 51680], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09613796760295999, "compression_ratio": 1.657258064516129, "no_speech_prob": 1.796740273923847e-12}, {"id": 412, "seek": 147786, "start": 1477.86, "end": 1483.4599999999998, "text": " And once they are a replay equivalent, we can explicitly record a collapse event to formally identify them.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 1564, 436, 366, 257, 23836, 10344, 11, 321, 393, 20803, 2136, 257, 15584, 2280, 281, 25983, 5876, 552, 13, 50645], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12072743778735136, "compression_ratio": 1.6360655737704919, "no_speech_prob": 1.5251243193695196e-12}, {"id": 413, "seek": 147786, "start": 1483.74, "end": 1485.26, "text": " We staple the receipts together.", "tokens": [50659, 492, 32361, 264, 2268, 48908, 1214, 13, 50735], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12072743778735136, "compression_ratio": 1.6360655737704919, "no_speech_prob": 1.5251243193695196e-12}, {"id": 414, "seek": 147786, "start": 1485.4799999999998, "end": 1492.34, "text": " We preserve both independent histories forever, the billions spent on R&D, and the separate manufacturing process of the generic.", "tokens": [50746, 492, 15665, 1293, 6695, 30631, 5680, 11, 264, 17375, 4418, 322, 497, 5, 35, 11, 293, 264, 4994, 11096, 1399, 295, 264, 19577, 13, 51089], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12072743778735136, "compression_ratio": 1.6360655737704919, "no_speech_prob": 1.5251243193695196e-12}, {"id": 415, "seek": 147786, "start": 1492.6799999999998, "end": 1497.12, "text": " But the system now formally knows they safely end up at the exact same place.", "tokens": [51106, 583, 264, 1185, 586, 25983, 3255, 436, 11750, 917, 493, 412, 264, 1900, 912, 1081, 13, 51328], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12072743778735136, "compression_ratio": 1.6360655737704919, "no_speech_prob": 1.5251243193695196e-12}, {"id": 416, "seek": 147786, "start": 1497.3799999999999, "end": 1502.4199999999998, "text": " This focus on irreversible history completely changes the structural rules of logic itself.", "tokens": [51341, 639, 1879, 322, 16014, 840, 964, 2503, 2584, 2962, 264, 15067, 4474, 295, 9952, 2564, 13, 51593], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12072743778735136, "compression_ratio": 1.6360655737704919, "no_speech_prob": 1.5251243193695196e-12}, {"id": 417, "seek": 147786, "start": 1502.7199999999998, "end": 1504.02, "text": " Let's look at something called weakening.", "tokens": [51608, 961, 311, 574, 412, 746, 1219, 5336, 4559, 13, 51673], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12072743778735136, "compression_ratio": 1.6360655737704919, "no_speech_prob": 1.5251243193695196e-12}, {"id": 418, "seek": 147786, "start": 1504.1799999999998, "end": 1504.7199999999998, "text": " Okay, weakening.", "tokens": [51681, 1033, 11, 5336, 4559, 13, 51708], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12072743778735136, "compression_ratio": 1.6360655737704919, "no_speech_prob": 1.5251243193695196e-12}, {"id": 419, "seek": 150472, "start": 1504.72, "end": 1518.54, "text": " In traditional logic, the rule of weakening states that if you can prove a conclusion using a specific set of assumptions, you can still prove that same conclusion, even if you throw in a bunch of extra irrelevant assumptions later.", "tokens": [50365, 682, 5164, 9952, 11, 264, 4978, 295, 5336, 4559, 4368, 300, 498, 291, 393, 7081, 257, 10063, 1228, 257, 2685, 992, 295, 17695, 11, 291, 393, 920, 7081, 300, 912, 10063, 11, 754, 498, 291, 3507, 294, 257, 3840, 295, 2857, 28682, 17695, 1780, 13, 51056], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09922933124360583, "compression_ratio": 1.8478260869565217, "no_speech_prob": 2.1088070525920877e-12}, {"id": 420, "seek": 150472, "start": 1518.7, "end": 1521.44, "text": " Let's say, if it is raining, the grass is wet.", "tokens": [51064, 961, 311, 584, 11, 498, 309, 307, 18441, 11, 264, 8054, 307, 6630, 13, 51201], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09922933124360583, "compression_ratio": 1.8478260869565217, "no_speech_prob": 2.1088070525920877e-12}, {"id": 421, "seek": 150472, "start": 1521.88, "end": 1527.14, "text": " And weakening means I can also say, if it is raining and my car is blue, the grass is wet.", "tokens": [51223, 400, 5336, 4559, 1355, 286, 393, 611, 584, 11, 498, 309, 307, 18441, 293, 452, 1032, 307, 3344, 11, 264, 8054, 307, 6630, 13, 51486], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09922933124360583, "compression_ratio": 1.8478260869565217, "no_speech_prob": 2.1088070525920877e-12}, {"id": 422, "seek": 150472, "start": 1527.66, "end": 1530.68, "text": " The blue car is irrelevant, but the logic still holds.", "tokens": [51512, 440, 3344, 1032, 307, 28682, 11, 457, 264, 9952, 920, 9190, 13, 51663], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09922933124360583, "compression_ratio": 1.8478260869565217, "no_speech_prob": 2.1088070525920877e-12}, {"id": 423, "seek": 153068, "start": 1530.68, "end": 1531.2, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50365, 7587, 13, 50391], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15157188287302226, "compression_ratio": 1.6245847176079735, "no_speech_prob": 1.5365288251814602e-12}, {"id": 424, "seek": 153068, "start": 1531.94, "end": 1535.14, "text": " But in sphere pop, weakening isn't just a logical trick.", "tokens": [50428, 583, 294, 16687, 1665, 11, 5336, 4559, 1943, 380, 445, 257, 14978, 4282, 13, 50588], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15157188287302226, "compression_ratio": 1.6245847176079735, "no_speech_prob": 1.5365288251814602e-12}, {"id": 425, "seek": 153068, "start": 1535.42, "end": 1537.28, "text": " It is simply historical extension.", "tokens": [50602, 467, 307, 2935, 8584, 10320, 13, 50695], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15157188287302226, "compression_ratio": 1.6245847176079735, "no_speech_prob": 1.5365288251814602e-12}, {"id": 426, "seek": 153068, "start": 1538.1200000000001, "end": 1549.16, "text": " Because histories are monotonic, adding a new, event-like observing a blue car to the end of the journal physically cannot invalidate the ink that already dried on the previous pages proving the grass is wet.", "tokens": [50737, 1436, 30631, 366, 1108, 310, 11630, 11, 5127, 257, 777, 11, 2280, 12, 4092, 22107, 257, 3344, 1032, 281, 264, 917, 295, 264, 6708, 9762, 2644, 34702, 473, 264, 11276, 300, 1217, 13538, 322, 264, 3894, 7183, 27221, 264, 8054, 307, 6630, 13, 51289], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15157188287302226, "compression_ratio": 1.6245847176079735, "no_speech_prob": 1.5365288251814602e-12}, {"id": 427, "seek": 153068, "start": 1549.24, "end": 1552.5800000000002, "text": " The proof remains structurally sound because the history can only grow.", "tokens": [51293, 440, 8177, 7023, 6594, 6512, 1626, 570, 264, 2503, 393, 787, 1852, 13, 51460], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15157188287302226, "compression_ratio": 1.6245847176079735, "no_speech_prob": 1.5365288251814602e-12}, {"id": 428, "seek": 153068, "start": 1552.74, "end": 1553.02, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51468, 1779, 13, 51482], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15157188287302226, "compression_ratio": 1.6245847176079735, "no_speech_prob": 1.5365288251814602e-12}, {"id": 429, "seek": 153068, "start": 1553.42, "end": 1554.8600000000001, "text": " What about the rule of exchange?", "tokens": [51502, 708, 466, 264, 4978, 295, 7742, 30, 51574], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15157188287302226, "compression_ratio": 1.6245847176079735, "no_speech_prob": 1.5365288251814602e-12}, {"id": 430, "seek": 153068, "start": 1555.2, "end": 1558.02, "text": " This is the rule that says the order of assumptions doesn't matter.", "tokens": [51591, 639, 307, 264, 4978, 300, 1619, 264, 1668, 295, 17695, 1177, 380, 1871, 13, 51732], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15157188287302226, "compression_ratio": 1.6245847176079735, "no_speech_prob": 1.5365288251814602e-12}, {"id": 431, "seek": 155802, "start": 1558.02, "end": 1562.0, "text": " If I assume A and B, it's logically the same as assuming B and A.", "tokens": [50365, 759, 286, 6552, 316, 293, 363, 11, 309, 311, 38887, 264, 912, 382, 11926, 363, 293, 316, 13, 50564], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14580758412679037, "compression_ratio": 1.6324786324786325, "no_speech_prob": 1.6684725432855596e-12}, {"id": 432, "seek": 155802, "start": 1562.3799999999999, "end": 1565.44, "text": " This is where sphere pop aggressively departs from traditional logic.", "tokens": [50583, 639, 307, 689, 16687, 1665, 32024, 9110, 82, 490, 5164, 9952, 13, 50736], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14580758412679037, "compression_ratio": 1.6324786324786325, "no_speech_prob": 1.6684725432855596e-12}, {"id": 433, "seek": 155802, "start": 1566.3799999999999, "end": 1568.86, "text": " In sphere pop, exchange is strictly conditional.", "tokens": [50783, 682, 16687, 1665, 11, 7742, 307, 20792, 27708, 13, 50907], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14580758412679037, "compression_ratio": 1.6324786324786325, "no_speech_prob": 1.6684725432855596e-12}, {"id": 434, "seek": 155802, "start": 1569.46, "end": 1573.0, "text": " You can only swap the order of two events if they are historically independent.", "tokens": [50937, 509, 393, 787, 18135, 264, 1668, 295, 732, 3931, 498, 436, 366, 16180, 6695, 13, 51114], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14580758412679037, "compression_ratio": 1.6324786324786325, "no_speech_prob": 1.6684725432855596e-12}, {"id": 435, "seek": 155802, "start": 1573.78, "end": 1577.22, "text": " Meaning, neither event used the bind verb to depend on the other.", "tokens": [51153, 19948, 11, 9662, 2280, 1143, 264, 14786, 9595, 281, 5672, 322, 264, 661, 13, 51325], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14580758412679037, "compression_ratio": 1.6324786324786325, "no_speech_prob": 1.6684725432855596e-12}, {"id": 436, "seek": 155802, "start": 1577.26, "end": 1579.48, "text": " Oh, so if they are connected, you can't touch them.", "tokens": [51327, 876, 11, 370, 498, 436, 366, 4582, 11, 291, 393, 380, 2557, 552, 13, 51438], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14580758412679037, "compression_ratio": 1.6324786324786325, "no_speech_prob": 1.6684725432855596e-12}, {"id": 437, "seek": 157948, "start": 1579.48, "end": 1587.74, "text": " If event B depends on the outcome of event A, swapping their order destroys the dependency graph, the bouncer will refuse it.", "tokens": [50365, 759, 2280, 363, 5946, 322, 264, 9700, 295, 2280, 316, 11, 1693, 10534, 641, 1668, 36714, 264, 33621, 4295, 11, 264, 272, 14296, 486, 16791, 309, 13, 50778], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1352763898444898, "compression_ratio": 1.6174242424242424, "no_speech_prob": 1.7144710130756469e-12}, {"id": 438, "seek": 157948, "start": 1588.18, "end": 1590.8, "text": " Time and order are mathematically real properties here.", "tokens": [50800, 6161, 293, 1668, 366, 44003, 957, 7221, 510, 13, 50931], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1352763898444898, "compression_ratio": 1.6174242424242424, "no_speech_prob": 1.7144710130756469e-12}, {"id": 439, "seek": 157948, "start": 1591.02, "end": 1596.2, "text": " You cannot put your shoes on before your socks, and the math finally reflects that physical reality.", "tokens": [50942, 509, 2644, 829, 428, 6654, 322, 949, 428, 17564, 11, 293, 264, 5221, 2721, 18926, 300, 4001, 4103, 13, 51201], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1352763898444898, "compression_ratio": 1.6174242424242424, "no_speech_prob": 1.7144710130756469e-12}, {"id": 440, "seek": 157948, "start": 1596.56, "end": 1598.54, "text": " Okay, here's where it gets really interesting.", "tokens": [51219, 1033, 11, 510, 311, 689, 309, 2170, 534, 1880, 13, 51318], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1352763898444898, "compression_ratio": 1.6174242424242424, "no_speech_prob": 1.7144710130756469e-12}, {"id": 441, "seek": 157948, "start": 1599.18, "end": 1604.2, "text": " In section 5 of the second paper, Fliction makes a claim that kind of flips the whole table over.", "tokens": [51350, 682, 3541, 1025, 295, 264, 1150, 3035, 11, 3235, 4105, 1669, 257, 3932, 300, 733, 295, 40249, 264, 1379, 3199, 670, 13, 51601], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1352763898444898, "compression_ratio": 1.6174242424242424, "no_speech_prob": 1.7144710130756469e-12}, {"id": 442, "seek": 160420, "start": 1604.2, "end": 1607.98, "text": " The quote is, composition is ontologically prior to typing.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 6513, 307, 11, 12686, 307, 6592, 17157, 4059, 281, 18444, 13, 50554], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10803085460997465, "compression_ratio": 1.7119205298013245, "no_speech_prob": 1.399537820703789e-12}, {"id": 443, "seek": 160420, "start": 1608.48, "end": 1611.44, "text": " It is a profound philosophical and architectural shift.", "tokens": [50579, 467, 307, 257, 14382, 25066, 293, 26621, 5513, 13, 50727], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10803085460997465, "compression_ratio": 1.7119205298013245, "no_speech_prob": 1.399537820703789e-12}, {"id": 444, "seek": 160420, "start": 1612.0, "end": 1622.14, "text": " What Fliction is arguing is that the graph topology, the literal structural web of who depends on whom and how the nodes connect to each other, is fundamentally separate from the semantics.", "tokens": [50755, 708, 3235, 4105, 307, 19697, 307, 300, 264, 4295, 1192, 1793, 11, 264, 20411, 15067, 3670, 295, 567, 5946, 322, 7101, 293, 577, 264, 13891, 1745, 281, 1184, 661, 11, 307, 17879, 4994, 490, 264, 4361, 45298, 13, 51262], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10803085460997465, "compression_ratio": 1.7119205298013245, "no_speech_prob": 1.399537820703789e-12}, {"id": 445, "seek": 160420, "start": 1622.38, "end": 1623.74, "text": " The semantics being what, exactly?", "tokens": [51274, 440, 4361, 45298, 885, 437, 11, 2293, 30, 51342], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10803085460997465, "compression_ratio": 1.7119205298013245, "no_speech_prob": 1.399537820703789e-12}, {"id": 446, "seek": 160420, "start": 1623.82, "end": 1628.1000000000001, "text": " The semantics being the actual mathematical transformation happening at each node.", "tokens": [51346, 440, 4361, 45298, 885, 264, 3539, 18894, 9887, 2737, 412, 1184, 9984, 13, 51560], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10803085460997465, "compression_ratio": 1.7119205298013245, "no_speech_prob": 1.399537820703789e-12}, {"id": 447, "seek": 160420, "start": 1628.38, "end": 1632.66, "text": " Okay, think of it like the motherboard of a retro gaming console, like an old Super Nintendo.", "tokens": [51574, 1033, 11, 519, 295, 309, 411, 264, 32916, 295, 257, 18820, 9703, 11076, 11, 411, 364, 1331, 4548, 11578, 13, 51788], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10803085460997465, "compression_ratio": 1.7119205298013245, "no_speech_prob": 1.399537820703789e-12}, {"id": 448, "seek": 163266, "start": 1632.66, "end": 1641.3200000000002, "text": " The composition graph that Fliction is talking about is the bare motherboard itself, with all the copper traces and wires connecting the different components.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 12686, 4295, 300, 3235, 4105, 307, 1417, 466, 307, 264, 6949, 32916, 2564, 11, 365, 439, 264, 15007, 26076, 293, 15537, 11015, 264, 819, 6677, 13, 50798], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13888754964876576, "compression_ratio": 1.7195945945945945, "no_speech_prob": 1.6487895033653888e-12}, {"id": 449, "seek": 163266, "start": 1641.46, "end": 1642.6200000000001, "text": " That's a great way to picture it.", "tokens": [50805, 663, 311, 257, 869, 636, 281, 3036, 309, 13, 50863], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13888754964876576, "compression_ratio": 1.7195945945945945, "no_speech_prob": 1.6487895033653888e-12}, {"id": 450, "seek": 163266, "start": 1642.72, "end": 1642.92, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50868, 1779, 13, 50878], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13888754964876576, "compression_ratio": 1.7195945945945945, "no_speech_prob": 1.6487895033653888e-12}, {"id": 451, "seek": 163266, "start": 1643.3000000000002, "end": 1645.6000000000001, "text": " That motherboard dictates the flow of electricity.", "tokens": [50897, 663, 32916, 12569, 1024, 264, 3095, 295, 10356, 13, 51012], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13888754964876576, "compression_ratio": 1.7195945945945945, "no_speech_prob": 1.6487895033653888e-12}, {"id": 452, "seek": 163266, "start": 1646.22, "end": 1649.1000000000001, "text": " It dictates that node A connects to node B.", "tokens": [51043, 467, 12569, 1024, 300, 9984, 316, 16967, 281, 9984, 363, 13, 51187], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13888754964876576, "compression_ratio": 1.7195945945945945, "no_speech_prob": 1.6487895033653888e-12}, {"id": 453, "seek": 163266, "start": 1649.78, "end": 1654.94, "text": " But the motherboard itself doesn't actually know what game you are playing until you plug in a cartridge.", "tokens": [51221, 583, 264, 32916, 2564, 1177, 380, 767, 458, 437, 1216, 291, 366, 2433, 1826, 291, 5452, 294, 257, 27753, 13, 51479], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13888754964876576, "compression_ratio": 1.7195945945945945, "no_speech_prob": 1.6487895033653888e-12}, {"id": 454, "seek": 163266, "start": 1655.7, "end": 1659.24, "text": " The operator libraries in SpherePop are the game partridges.", "tokens": [51517, 440, 12973, 15148, 294, 318, 6605, 38677, 366, 264, 1216, 644, 43292, 13, 51694], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13888754964876576, "compression_ratio": 1.7195945945945945, "no_speech_prob": 1.6487895033653888e-12}, {"id": 455, "seek": 163266, "start": 1659.24, "end": 1662.2, "text": " That is a highly effective way to visualize it.", "tokens": [51694, 663, 307, 257, 5405, 4942, 636, 281, 23273, 309, 13, 51842], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13888754964876576, "compression_ratio": 1.7195945945945945, "no_speech_prob": 1.6487895033653888e-12}, {"id": 456, "seek": 166220, "start": 1662.2, "end": 1669.52, "text": " You take your Boolean logic cartridge, you plug it into the graph, and suddenly that exact same motherboard runs standard digital logic.", "tokens": [50365, 509, 747, 428, 23351, 28499, 9952, 27753, 11, 291, 5452, 309, 666, 264, 4295, 11, 293, 5800, 300, 1900, 912, 32916, 6676, 3832, 4562, 9952, 13, 50731], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12452315349204868, "compression_ratio": 1.6293436293436294, "no_speech_prob": 1.455070005457193e-12}, {"id": 457, "seek": 166220, "start": 1669.92, "end": 1673.42, "text": " It evaluates A and D, ORR, and not gates.", "tokens": [50751, 467, 6133, 1024, 316, 293, 413, 11, 19654, 49, 11, 293, 406, 19792, 13, 50926], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12452315349204868, "compression_ratio": 1.6293436293436294, "no_speech_prob": 1.455070005457193e-12}, {"id": 458, "seek": 166220, "start": 1673.76, "end": 1675.06, "text": " Just standard computer stuff.", "tokens": [50943, 1449, 3832, 3820, 1507, 13, 51008], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12452315349204868, "compression_ratio": 1.6293436293436294, "no_speech_prob": 1.455070005457193e-12}, {"id": 459, "seek": 166220, "start": 1675.1000000000001, "end": 1675.24, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51010, 1779, 13, 51017], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12452315349204868, "compression_ratio": 1.6293436293436294, "no_speech_prob": 1.455070005457193e-12}, {"id": 460, "seek": 166220, "start": 1675.46, "end": 1683.94, "text": " But if you pull that cartridge out and swap it for a fuzzy logic cartridge or neural network cartridge, the underlying copper traces haven't changed.", "tokens": [51028, 583, 498, 291, 2235, 300, 27753, 484, 293, 18135, 309, 337, 257, 34710, 9952, 27753, 420, 18161, 3209, 27753, 11, 264, 14217, 15007, 26076, 2378, 380, 3105, 13, 51452], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12452315349204868, "compression_ratio": 1.6293436293436294, "no_speech_prob": 1.455070005457193e-12}, {"id": 461, "seek": 166220, "start": 1684.3, "end": 1685.82, "text": " The dependency graph is identical.", "tokens": [51470, 440, 33621, 4295, 307, 14800, 13, 51546], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12452315349204868, "compression_ratio": 1.6293436293436294, "no_speech_prob": 1.455070005457193e-12}, {"id": 462, "seek": 166220, "start": 1686.04, "end": 1687.0, "text": " But the game changed.", "tokens": [51557, 583, 264, 1216, 3105, 13, 51605], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12452315349204868, "compression_ratio": 1.6293436293436294, "no_speech_prob": 1.455070005457193e-12}, {"id": 463, "seek": 168700, "start": 1687.0, "end": 1687.44, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50365, 7587, 13, 50387], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1594345768292745, "compression_ratio": 1.148936170212766, "no_speech_prob": 1.513262171820573e-12}, {"id": 464, "seek": 168700, "start": 1687.74, "end": 1693.32, "text": " Now, the exact same system is running continuous gradients or evaluating probability distributions.", "tokens": [50402, 823, 11, 264, 1900, 912, 1185, 307, 2614, 10957, 2771, 2448, 420, 27479, 8482, 37870, 13, 50681], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1594345768292745, "compression_ratio": 1.148936170212766, "no_speech_prob": 1.513262171820573e-12}, {"id": 465, "seek": 169332, "start": 1693.32, "end": 1705.34, "text": " This means that logical systems, classical Boolean logic that runs our computers, or probabilistic logic that runs AI aren't actually inherent absolute computational realities.", "tokens": [50365, 639, 1355, 300, 14978, 3652, 11, 13735, 23351, 28499, 9952, 300, 6676, 527, 10807, 11, 420, 31959, 3142, 9952, 300, 6676, 7318, 3212, 380, 767, 26387, 8236, 28270, 27785, 13, 50966], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08580689877271652, "compression_ratio": 1.6059113300492611, "no_speech_prob": 1.6362183960158538e-12}, {"id": 466, "seek": 169332, "start": 1705.6799999999998, "end": 1707.3799999999999, "text": " They are just human interpretations.", "tokens": [50983, 814, 366, 445, 1952, 37547, 13, 51068], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08580689877271652, "compression_ratio": 1.6059113300492611, "no_speech_prob": 1.6362183960158538e-12}, {"id": 467, "seek": 169332, "start": 1707.74, "end": 1713.56, "text": " There are specific operator algebras that we choose to overlay onto the exact same underlying composition graph.", "tokens": [51086, 821, 366, 2685, 12973, 419, 432, 38182, 300, 321, 2826, 281, 31741, 3911, 264, 1900, 912, 14217, 12686, 4295, 13, 51377], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08580689877271652, "compression_ratio": 1.6059113300492611, "no_speech_prob": 1.6362183960158538e-12}, {"id": 468, "seek": 171356, "start": 1713.56, "end": 1716.06, "text": " And that completely shatters how we categorize software.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 300, 2584, 402, 37690, 577, 321, 19250, 1125, 4722, 13, 50490], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1917660959650961, "compression_ratio": 1.471311475409836, "no_speech_prob": 2.059525076522628e-12}, {"id": 469, "seek": 171356, "start": 1716.82, "end": 1720.8, "text": " The runtime engine processing the SpherePop graph doesn't know it is doing logic.", "tokens": [50528, 440, 34474, 2848, 9007, 264, 318, 6605, 38677, 4295, 1177, 380, 458, 309, 307, 884, 9952, 13, 50727], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1917660959650961, "compression_ratio": 1.471311475409836, "no_speech_prob": 2.059525076522628e-12}, {"id": 470, "seek": 171356, "start": 1720.94, "end": 1721.04, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [50734, 865, 13, 50739], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1917660959650961, "compression_ratio": 1.471311475409836, "no_speech_prob": 2.059525076522628e-12}, {"id": 471, "seek": 171356, "start": 1721.1399999999999, "end": 1722.78, "text": " It has no concept of philosophy.", "tokens": [50744, 467, 575, 572, 3410, 295, 10675, 13, 50826], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1917660959650961, "compression_ratio": 1.471311475409836, "no_speech_prob": 2.059525076522628e-12}, {"id": 472, "seek": 171356, "start": 1723.1, "end": 1723.26, "text": " Ah.", "tokens": [50842, 2438, 13, 50850], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1917660959650961, "compression_ratio": 1.471311475409836, "no_speech_prob": 2.059525076522628e-12}, {"id": 473, "seek": 171356, "start": 1723.28, "end": 1728.94, "text": " It's just moving data through the topology and composing histories according to whatever cartridge is currently loaded.", "tokens": [50851, 467, 311, 445, 2684, 1412, 807, 264, 1192, 1793, 293, 715, 6110, 30631, 4650, 281, 2035, 27753, 307, 4362, 13210, 13, 51134], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1917660959650961, "compression_ratio": 1.471311475409836, "no_speech_prob": 2.059525076522628e-12}, {"id": 474, "seek": 171356, "start": 1729.1399999999999, "end": 1731.6, "text": " Let's talk about truth values, because this blew my mind.", "tokens": [51144, 961, 311, 751, 466, 3494, 4190, 11, 570, 341, 19075, 452, 1575, 13, 51267], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1917660959650961, "compression_ratio": 1.471311475409836, "no_speech_prob": 2.059525076522628e-12}, {"id": 475, "seek": 173160, "start": 1731.6, "end": 1735.02, "text": " In Boolean logic, truth is an ontological absolute.", "tokens": [50365, 682, 23351, 28499, 9952, 11, 3494, 307, 364, 6592, 4383, 8236, 13, 50536], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16274736022949218, "compression_ratio": 1.6080586080586081, "no_speech_prob": 1.875921076463505e-12}, {"id": 476, "seek": 173160, "start": 1735.26, "end": 1736.74, "text": " It is the bedrock of the universe.", "tokens": [50548, 467, 307, 264, 2901, 17799, 295, 264, 6445, 13, 50622], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16274736022949218, "compression_ratio": 1.6080586080586081, "no_speech_prob": 1.875921076463505e-12}, {"id": 477, "seek": 173160, "start": 1737.1599999999999, "end": 1737.9399999999998, "text": " True or false.", "tokens": [50643, 13587, 420, 7908, 13, 50682], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16274736022949218, "compression_ratio": 1.6080586080586081, "no_speech_prob": 1.875921076463505e-12}, {"id": 478, "seek": 173160, "start": 1738.1799999999998, "end": 1738.74, "text": " One or zero.", "tokens": [50694, 1485, 420, 4018, 13, 50722], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16274736022949218, "compression_ratio": 1.6080586080586081, "no_speech_prob": 1.875921076463505e-12}, {"id": 479, "seek": 173160, "start": 1739.28, "end": 1741.8999999999999, "text": " But in SpherePop, a truth value is just.", "tokens": [50749, 583, 294, 318, 6605, 38677, 11, 257, 3494, 2158, 307, 445, 13, 50880], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16274736022949218, "compression_ratio": 1.6080586080586081, "no_speech_prob": 1.875921076463505e-12}, {"id": 480, "seek": 173160, "start": 1742.2199999999998, "end": 1745.4399999999998, "text": " Another arbitrary piece of data flowing down a copper trace.", "tokens": [50896, 3996, 23211, 2522, 295, 1412, 13974, 760, 257, 15007, 13508, 13, 51057], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16274736022949218, "compression_ratio": 1.6080586080586081, "no_speech_prob": 1.875921076463505e-12}, {"id": 481, "seek": 173160, "start": 1745.52, "end": 1745.76, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [51061, 1079, 13, 51073], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16274736022949218, "compression_ratio": 1.6080586080586081, "no_speech_prob": 1.875921076463505e-12}, {"id": 482, "seek": 173160, "start": 1746.1799999999998, "end": 1747.84, "text": " Truth is stripped of its absolute status.", "tokens": [51094, 20522, 307, 33221, 295, 1080, 8236, 6558, 13, 51177], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16274736022949218, "compression_ratio": 1.6080586080586081, "no_speech_prob": 1.875921076463505e-12}, {"id": 483, "seek": 173160, "start": 1747.9399999999998, "end": 1748.82, "text": " It could be a Boolean one.", "tokens": [51182, 467, 727, 312, 257, 23351, 28499, 472, 13, 51226], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16274736022949218, "compression_ratio": 1.6080586080586081, "no_speech_prob": 1.875921076463505e-12}, {"id": 484, "seek": 173160, "start": 1749.1999999999998, "end": 1754.54, "text": " But if you swap the cartridge, that exact same node might output a fuzzy logic value of 0.43.", "tokens": [51245, 583, 498, 291, 18135, 264, 27753, 11, 300, 1900, 912, 9984, 1062, 5598, 257, 34710, 9952, 2158, 295, 1958, 13, 17201, 13, 51512], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16274736022949218, "compression_ratio": 1.6080586080586081, "no_speech_prob": 1.875921076463505e-12}, {"id": 485, "seek": 173160, "start": 1755.08, "end": 1758.06, "text": " Or it might output a complex probability distribution.", "tokens": [51539, 1610, 309, 1062, 5598, 257, 3997, 8482, 7316, 13, 51688], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16274736022949218, "compression_ratio": 1.6080586080586081, "no_speech_prob": 1.875921076463505e-12}, {"id": 486, "seek": 175806, "start": 1758.06, "end": 1762.5, "text": " The machine evaluates the node based on the rules of the loaded operator library.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 3479, 6133, 1024, 264, 9984, 2361, 322, 264, 4474, 295, 264, 13210, 12973, 6405, 13, 50587], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13694574521935504, "compression_ratio": 1.599250936329588, "no_speech_prob": 1.8324569292516024e-12}, {"id": 487, "seek": 175806, "start": 1763.2, "end": 1766.3799999999999, "text": " But the history of how that node was reached remains constant.", "tokens": [50622, 583, 264, 2503, 295, 577, 300, 9984, 390, 6488, 7023, 5754, 13, 50781], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13694574521935504, "compression_ratio": 1.599250936329588, "no_speech_prob": 1.8324569292516024e-12}, {"id": 488, "seek": 175806, "start": 1767.04, "end": 1769.6399999999999, "text": " The practical implication of this is staggering.", "tokens": [50814, 440, 8496, 37814, 295, 341, 307, 42974, 13, 50944], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13694574521935504, "compression_ratio": 1.599250936329588, "no_speech_prob": 1.8324569292516024e-12}, {"id": 489, "seek": 175806, "start": 1770.32, "end": 1779.8999999999999, "text": " It means you could architect a single, massive software program where one module is executing strict, rigid Boolean logic for a banking ledger.", "tokens": [50978, 467, 1355, 291, 727, 6331, 257, 2167, 11, 5994, 4722, 1461, 689, 472, 10088, 307, 32368, 10910, 11, 22195, 23351, 28499, 9952, 337, 257, 18261, 4684, 1321, 13, 51457], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13694574521935504, "compression_ratio": 1.599250936329588, "no_speech_prob": 1.8324569292516024e-12}, {"id": 490, "seek": 175806, "start": 1780.44, "end": 1786.1399999999999, "text": " And the data flows seamlessly into another module that uses fuzzy logic to evaluate risk.", "tokens": [51484, 400, 264, 1412, 12867, 38083, 666, 1071, 10088, 300, 4960, 34710, 9952, 281, 13059, 3148, 13, 51769], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13694574521935504, "compression_ratio": 1.599250936329588, "no_speech_prob": 1.8324569292516024e-12}, {"id": 491, "seek": 178614, "start": 1786.14, "end": 1790.18, "text": " And that flows seamlessly into a neural network to predict market trends.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 300, 12867, 38083, 666, 257, 18161, 3209, 281, 6069, 2142, 13892, 13, 50567], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12523596627371653, "compression_ratio": 1.591549295774648, "no_speech_prob": 2.389555133625043e-12}, {"id": 492, "seek": 178614, "start": 1790.6200000000001, "end": 1791.8200000000002, "text": " Because it's all just one graph.", "tokens": [50589, 1436, 309, 311, 439, 445, 472, 4295, 13, 50649], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12523596627371653, "compression_ratio": 1.591549295774648, "no_speech_prob": 2.389555133625043e-12}, {"id": 493, "seek": 178614, "start": 1792.38, "end": 1792.76, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50677, 7587, 13, 50696], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12523596627371653, "compression_ratio": 1.591549295774648, "no_speech_prob": 2.389555133625043e-12}, {"id": 494, "seek": 178614, "start": 1792.92, "end": 1798.3600000000001, "text": " Because to the underlying SpherePop runtime, it's all just nodes passing data and recording history.", "tokens": [50704, 1436, 281, 264, 14217, 318, 6605, 38677, 34474, 11, 309, 311, 439, 445, 13891, 8437, 1412, 293, 6613, 2503, 13, 50976], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12523596627371653, "compression_ratio": 1.591549295774648, "no_speech_prob": 2.389555133625043e-12}, {"id": 495, "seek": 178614, "start": 1798.8000000000002, "end": 1804.18, "text": " The boundary between a traditional logic circuit and a modern machine learning model completely evaporates.", "tokens": [50998, 440, 12866, 1296, 257, 5164, 9952, 9048, 293, 257, 4363, 3479, 2539, 2316, 2584, 26315, 1024, 13, 51267], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12523596627371653, "compression_ratio": 1.591549295774648, "no_speech_prob": 2.389555133625043e-12}, {"id": 496, "seek": 178614, "start": 1804.2800000000002, "end": 1805.38, "text": " It doesn't just evaporate.", "tokens": [51272, 467, 1177, 380, 445, 26315, 473, 13, 51327], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12523596627371653, "compression_ratio": 1.591549295774648, "no_speech_prob": 2.389555133625043e-12}, {"id": 497, "seek": 178614, "start": 1805.48, "end": 1808.3200000000002, "text": " It is revealed to be an artificial boundary we created.", "tokens": [51332, 467, 307, 9599, 281, 312, 364, 11677, 12866, 321, 2942, 13, 51474], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12523596627371653, "compression_ratio": 1.591549295774648, "no_speech_prob": 2.389555133625043e-12}, {"id": 498, "seek": 178614, "start": 1809.0200000000002, "end": 1810.7800000000002, "text": " Fliction points out a brilliant equivalence.", "tokens": [51509, 3235, 4105, 2793, 484, 257, 10248, 9052, 655, 13, 51597], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12523596627371653, "compression_ratio": 1.591549295774648, "no_speech_prob": 2.389555133625043e-12}, {"id": 499, "seek": 181078, "start": 1810.78, "end": 1819.78, "text": " An AND gate in Boolean logic is fundamentally no different from an arithmetic addition operator, or a function that concatenates two strings of text together.", "tokens": [50365, 1107, 8093, 8539, 294, 23351, 28499, 9952, 307, 17879, 572, 819, 490, 364, 42973, 4500, 12973, 11, 420, 257, 2445, 300, 1588, 7186, 1024, 732, 13985, 295, 2487, 1214, 13, 50815], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1891677299242341, "compression_ratio": 1.5950413223140496, "no_speech_prob": 1.4779785468405082e-12}, {"id": 500, "seek": 181078, "start": 1819.96, "end": 1821.76, "text": " Because they just take inputs and give an output.", "tokens": [50824, 1436, 436, 445, 747, 15743, 293, 976, 364, 5598, 13, 50914], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1891677299242341, "compression_ratio": 1.5950413223140496, "no_speech_prob": 1.4779785468405082e-12}, {"id": 501, "seek": 181078, "start": 1822.28, "end": 1825.06, "text": " They're all just functions with a specified arity.", "tokens": [50940, 814, 434, 439, 445, 6828, 365, 257, 22206, 594, 507, 13, 51079], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1891677299242341, "compression_ratio": 1.5950413223140496, "no_speech_prob": 1.4779785468405082e-12}, {"id": 502, "seek": 181078, "start": 1825.42, "end": 1828.3999999999999, "text": " Meaning, they take a certain number of inputs and produce an output.", "tokens": [51097, 19948, 11, 436, 747, 257, 1629, 1230, 295, 15743, 293, 5258, 364, 5598, 13, 51246], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1891677299242341, "compression_ratio": 1.5950413223140496, "no_speech_prob": 1.4779785468405082e-12}, {"id": 503, "seek": 181078, "start": 1829.06, "end": 1832.68, "text": " A truth table is literally just a finite lookup function.", "tokens": [51279, 316, 3494, 3199, 307, 3736, 445, 257, 19362, 574, 1010, 2445, 13, 51460], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1891677299242341, "compression_ratio": 1.5950413223140496, "no_speech_prob": 1.4779785468405082e-12}, {"id": 504, "seek": 183268, "start": 1832.68, "end": 1842.7, "text": " If you replace a rigid binary Boolean AND gate with a differentiable mathematical function, suddenly your rigid logic circuit becomes fluid.", "tokens": [50365, 759, 291, 7406, 257, 22195, 17434, 23351, 28499, 8093, 8539, 365, 257, 819, 9364, 18894, 2445, 11, 5800, 428, 22195, 9952, 9048, 3643, 9113, 13, 50866], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15609535170190128, "compression_ratio": 1.471111111111111, "no_speech_prob": 1.7414723092398776e-12}, {"id": 505, "seek": 183268, "start": 1843.04, "end": 1844.5600000000002, "text": " You can run backpropagation through it.", "tokens": [50883, 509, 393, 1190, 646, 79, 1513, 559, 399, 807, 309, 13, 50959], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15609535170190128, "compression_ratio": 1.471111111111111, "no_speech_prob": 1.7414723092398776e-12}, {"id": 506, "seek": 183268, "start": 1844.68, "end": 1844.92, "text": " Wait.", "tokens": [50965, 3802, 13, 50977], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15609535170190128, "compression_ratio": 1.471111111111111, "no_speech_prob": 1.7414723092398776e-12}, {"id": 507, "seek": 183268, "start": 1845.8, "end": 1846.44, "text": " Backpropagation.", "tokens": [51021, 5833, 79, 1513, 559, 399, 13, 51053], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15609535170190128, "compression_ratio": 1.471111111111111, "no_speech_prob": 1.7414723092398776e-12}, {"id": 508, "seek": 183268, "start": 1846.64, "end": 1849.8200000000002, "text": " That is the core mechanism of how artificial intelligence learns.", "tokens": [51063, 663, 307, 264, 4965, 7513, 295, 577, 11677, 7599, 27152, 13, 51222], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15609535170190128, "compression_ratio": 1.471111111111111, "no_speech_prob": 1.7414723092398776e-12}, {"id": 509, "seek": 183268, "start": 1850.3400000000001, "end": 1853.52, "text": " It's how neural networks adjust their weights to get smarter.", "tokens": [51248, 467, 311, 577, 18161, 9590, 4369, 641, 17443, 281, 483, 20294, 13, 51407], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15609535170190128, "compression_ratio": 1.471111111111111, "no_speech_prob": 1.7414723092398776e-12}, {"id": 510, "seek": 185352, "start": 1853.52, "end": 1863.78, "text": " You're saying that because the SpherePOP graph separates the topology from the operators, training in AI is just running the historical journal backward with a calculus cartridge plugged in.", "tokens": [50365, 509, 434, 1566, 300, 570, 264, 318, 6605, 47, 12059, 4295, 34149, 264, 1192, 1793, 490, 264, 19077, 11, 3097, 294, 7318, 307, 445, 2614, 264, 8584, 6708, 23897, 365, 257, 33400, 27753, 25679, 294, 13, 50878], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13256387861948166, "compression_ratio": 1.7272727272727273, "no_speech_prob": 2.0206820158102934e-12}, {"id": 511, "seek": 185352, "start": 1863.94, "end": 1865.5, "text": " That is precisely what it is.", "tokens": [50886, 663, 307, 13402, 437, 309, 307, 13, 50964], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13256387861948166, "compression_ratio": 1.7272727272727273, "no_speech_prob": 2.0206820158102934e-12}, {"id": 512, "seek": 185352, "start": 1865.82, "end": 1869.52, "text": " In AI training, the forward pass computes the values and makes a prediction.", "tokens": [50980, 682, 7318, 3097, 11, 264, 2128, 1320, 715, 1819, 264, 4190, 293, 1669, 257, 17630, 13, 51165], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13256387861948166, "compression_ratio": 1.7272727272727273, "no_speech_prob": 2.0206820158102934e-12}, {"id": 513, "seek": 185352, "start": 1870.08, "end": 1873.66, "text": " The backward pass backpropagation computes the derivatives to correct the errors.", "tokens": [51193, 440, 23897, 1320, 646, 79, 1513, 559, 399, 715, 1819, 264, 33733, 281, 3006, 264, 13603, 13, 51372], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13256387861948166, "compression_ratio": 1.7272727272727273, "no_speech_prob": 2.0206820158102934e-12}, {"id": 514, "seek": 185352, "start": 1874.16, "end": 1878.84, "text": " In SpherePOP, both of those passes are simply compositions over the exact same underlying history graph.", "tokens": [51397, 682, 318, 6605, 47, 12059, 11, 1293, 295, 729, 11335, 366, 2935, 43401, 670, 264, 1900, 912, 14217, 2503, 4295, 13, 51631], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13256387861948166, "compression_ratio": 1.7272727272727273, "no_speech_prob": 2.0206820158102934e-12}, {"id": 515, "seek": 185352, "start": 1879.06, "end": 1881.26, "text": " So you don't need a separate system for AI.", "tokens": [51642, 407, 291, 500, 380, 643, 257, 4994, 1185, 337, 7318, 13, 51752], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13256387861948166, "compression_ratio": 1.7272727272727273, "no_speech_prob": 2.0206820158102934e-12}, {"id": 516, "seek": 185352, "start": 1881.72, "end": 1882.06, "text": " No.", "tokens": [51775, 883, 13, 51792], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13256387861948166, "compression_ratio": 1.7272727272727273, "no_speech_prob": 2.0206820158102934e-12}, {"id": 517, "seek": 188206, "start": 1882.06, "end": 1887.72, "text": " The runtime environment doesn't need a massive, specialized machine learning engine bolted onto it.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 34474, 2823, 1177, 380, 643, 257, 5994, 11, 19813, 3479, 2539, 2848, 13436, 292, 3911, 309, 13, 50648], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11145907861215097, "compression_ratio": 1.663265306122449, "no_speech_prob": 1.6555023411163328e-12}, {"id": 518, "seek": 188206, "start": 1888.08, "end": 1892.6799999999998, "text": " It just needs a universal operator machine that knows how to read the graph and execute the verbs.", "tokens": [50666, 467, 445, 2203, 257, 11455, 12973, 3479, 300, 3255, 577, 281, 1401, 264, 4295, 293, 14483, 264, 30051, 13, 50896], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11145907861215097, "compression_ratio": 1.663265306122449, "no_speech_prob": 1.6555023411163328e-12}, {"id": 519, "seek": 188206, "start": 1892.8999999999999, "end": 1898.58, "text": " Okay, my mind is thoroughly blown by the universal operator machine, but Fliction refuses to stop there.", "tokens": [50907, 1033, 11, 452, 1575, 307, 17987, 16479, 538, 264, 11455, 12973, 3479, 11, 457, 3235, 4105, 33222, 281, 1590, 456, 13, 51191], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11145907861215097, "compression_ratio": 1.663265306122449, "no_speech_prob": 1.6555023411163328e-12}, {"id": 520, "seek": 188206, "start": 1899.1, "end": 1904.0, "text": " In the final section of the paper, he takes aim at the very code we type on our keyboards every day.", "tokens": [51217, 682, 264, 2572, 3541, 295, 264, 3035, 11, 415, 2516, 5939, 412, 264, 588, 3089, 321, 2010, 322, 527, 47808, 633, 786, 13, 51462], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11145907861215097, "compression_ratio": 1.663265306122449, "no_speech_prob": 1.6555023411163328e-12}, {"id": 521, "seek": 188206, "start": 1904.6599999999999, "end": 1909.82, "text": " If logic and types are just cartridges and human interpretations, what about syntax?", "tokens": [51495, 759, 9952, 293, 3467, 366, 445, 47036, 293, 1952, 37547, 11, 437, 466, 28431, 30, 51753], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11145907861215097, "compression_ratio": 1.663265306122449, "no_speech_prob": 1.6555023411163328e-12}, {"id": 522, "seek": 190982, "start": 1909.82, "end": 1915.86, "text": " What about the actual lines of code we write in Python, or C++A, or JavaScript?", "tokens": [50365, 708, 466, 264, 3539, 3876, 295, 3089, 321, 2464, 294, 15329, 11, 420, 383, 25472, 32, 11, 420, 15778, 30, 50667], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12731958690442538, "compression_ratio": 1.45662100456621, "no_speech_prob": 1.9887977983218397e-12}, {"id": 523, "seek": 190982, "start": 1916.3999999999999, "end": 1921.54, "text": " Fliction defines syntax, all the code we write, as a lossy human compression algorithm.", "tokens": [50694, 3235, 4105, 23122, 28431, 11, 439, 264, 3089, 321, 2464, 11, 382, 257, 4470, 88, 1952, 19355, 9284, 13, 50951], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12731958690442538, "compression_ratio": 1.45662100456621, "no_speech_prob": 1.9887977983218397e-12}, {"id": 524, "seek": 190982, "start": 1921.6599999999999, "end": 1922.0, "text": " Ouch.", "tokens": [50957, 27217, 13, 50974], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12731958690442538, "compression_ratio": 1.45662100456621, "no_speech_prob": 1.9887977983218397e-12}, {"id": 525, "seek": 190982, "start": 1922.6399999999999, "end": 1930.02, "text": " That feels like a direct attack on every programming language ever designed, and every developer who prides themselves on writing beautiful code.", "tokens": [51006, 663, 3417, 411, 257, 2047, 2690, 322, 633, 9410, 2856, 1562, 4761, 11, 293, 633, 10754, 567, 582, 1875, 2969, 322, 3579, 2238, 3089, 13, 51375], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12731958690442538, "compression_ratio": 1.45662100456621, "no_speech_prob": 1.9887977983218397e-12}, {"id": 526, "seek": 193002, "start": 1930.02, "end": 1933.9, "text": " It sounds harsh, but mathematically, it's undeniably true.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 3263, 14897, 11, 457, 44003, 11, 309, 311, 674, 15711, 1188, 2074, 13, 50559], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12872284533930758, "compression_ratio": 1.5826771653543308, "no_speech_prob": 1.399027920422069e-12}, {"id": 527, "seek": 193002, "start": 1934.4, "end": 1935.76, "text": " Think about how human beings communicate.", "tokens": [50584, 6557, 466, 577, 1952, 8958, 7890, 13, 50652], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12872284533930758, "compression_ratio": 1.5826771653543308, "no_speech_prob": 1.399027920422069e-12}, {"id": 528, "seek": 193002, "start": 1936.1, "end": 1938.58, "text": " We are biologically constrained to communicate linearly.", "tokens": [50669, 492, 366, 3228, 17157, 38901, 281, 7890, 43586, 13, 50793], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12872284533930758, "compression_ratio": 1.5826771653543308, "no_speech_prob": 1.399027920422069e-12}, {"id": 529, "seek": 193002, "start": 1938.86, "end": 1942.0, "text": " I am speaking to you right now in a sequence of words, one after another.", "tokens": [50807, 286, 669, 4124, 281, 291, 558, 586, 294, 257, 8310, 295, 2283, 11, 472, 934, 1071, 13, 50964], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12872284533930758, "compression_ratio": 1.5826771653543308, "no_speech_prob": 1.399027920422069e-12}, {"id": 530, "seek": 193002, "start": 1942.1399999999999, "end": 1945.58, "text": " When we write text, we write it in lines, top to bottom, left to right.", "tokens": [50971, 1133, 321, 2464, 2487, 11, 321, 2464, 309, 294, 3876, 11, 1192, 281, 2767, 11, 1411, 281, 558, 13, 51143], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12872284533930758, "compression_ratio": 1.5826771653543308, "no_speech_prob": 1.399027920422069e-12}, {"id": 531, "seek": 193002, "start": 1945.94, "end": 1948.22, "text": " But actual computation doesn't work like that.", "tokens": [51161, 583, 3539, 24903, 1177, 380, 589, 411, 300, 13, 51275], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12872284533930758, "compression_ratio": 1.5826771653543308, "no_speech_prob": 1.399027920422069e-12}, {"id": 532, "seek": 193002, "start": 1948.6, "end": 1951.28, "text": " Computation is a multidimensional dependency graph.", "tokens": [51294, 37804, 399, 307, 257, 2120, 327, 332, 11075, 33621, 4295, 13, 51428], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12872284533930758, "compression_ratio": 1.5826771653543308, "no_speech_prob": 1.399027920422069e-12}, {"id": 533, "seek": 195128, "start": 1951.28, "end": 1955.12, "text": " It is a vast web of nodes firing simultaneously.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 307, 257, 8369, 3670, 295, 13891, 16045, 16561, 13, 50557], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13627193852474814, "compression_ratio": 1.6127659574468085, "no_speech_prob": 1.5251264877738646e-12}, {"id": 534, "seek": 195128, "start": 1955.46, "end": 1956.46, "text": " So we're kind of squishing it.", "tokens": [50574, 407, 321, 434, 733, 295, 2339, 3807, 309, 13, 50624], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13627193852474814, "compression_ratio": 1.6127659574468085, "no_speech_prob": 1.5251264877738646e-12}, {"id": 535, "seek": 195128, "start": 1956.76, "end": 1957.1, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50639, 7587, 13, 50656], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13627193852474814, "compression_ratio": 1.6127659574468085, "no_speech_prob": 1.5251264877738646e-12}, {"id": 536, "seek": 195128, "start": 1957.68, "end": 1965.66, "text": " When we write code in a linear text file, we are forcing a massive multidimensional web into a flat one-dimensional string of characters.", "tokens": [50685, 1133, 321, 2464, 3089, 294, 257, 8213, 2487, 3991, 11, 321, 366, 19030, 257, 5994, 2120, 327, 332, 11075, 3670, 666, 257, 4962, 472, 12, 18759, 6798, 295, 4342, 13, 51084], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13627193852474814, "compression_ratio": 1.6127659574468085, "no_speech_prob": 1.5251264877738646e-12}, {"id": 537, "seek": 195128, "start": 1966.22, "end": 1969.36, "text": " In doing so, we lose an enormous amount of structural information.", "tokens": [51112, 682, 884, 370, 11, 321, 3624, 364, 11322, 2372, 295, 15067, 1589, 13, 51269], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13627193852474814, "compression_ratio": 1.6127659574468085, "no_speech_prob": 1.5251264877738646e-12}, {"id": 538, "seek": 195128, "start": 1969.86, "end": 1974.26, "text": " We compress the reality of the graph into a format our linear monkey brains can read.", "tokens": [51294, 492, 14778, 264, 4103, 295, 264, 4295, 666, 257, 7877, 527, 8213, 17847, 15442, 393, 1401, 13, 51514], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13627193852474814, "compression_ratio": 1.6127659574468085, "no_speech_prob": 1.5251264877738646e-12}, {"id": 539, "seek": 197426, "start": 1974.26, "end": 1981.8799999999999, "text": " I have to ask, then, if syntax is just a lossy projection, why do we even bother having programming languages like Rust or Python?", "tokens": [50365, 286, 362, 281, 1029, 11, 550, 11, 498, 28431, 307, 445, 257, 4470, 88, 22743, 11, 983, 360, 321, 754, 8677, 1419, 9410, 8650, 411, 34952, 420, 15329, 30, 50746], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12793302536010742, "compression_ratio": 1.5620689655172413, "no_speech_prob": 1.3303612768703066e-12}, {"id": 540, "seek": 197426, "start": 1982.44, "end": 1986.68, "text": " Why don't software engineers just sit down and build multidimensional graphs directly?", "tokens": [50774, 1545, 500, 380, 4722, 11955, 445, 1394, 760, 293, 1322, 2120, 327, 332, 11075, 24877, 3838, 30, 50986], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12793302536010742, "compression_ratio": 1.5620689655172413, "no_speech_prob": 1.3303612768703066e-12}, {"id": 541, "seek": 197426, "start": 1987.14, "end": 1989.46, "text": " Because of those exact human cognitive limits.", "tokens": [51009, 1436, 295, 729, 1900, 1952, 15605, 10406, 13, 51125], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12793302536010742, "compression_ratio": 1.5620689655172413, "no_speech_prob": 1.3303612768703066e-12}, {"id": 542, "seek": 197426, "start": 1990.14, "end": 1993.76, "text": " A human being cannot hold a million-node graph in their working memory.", "tokens": [51159, 316, 1952, 885, 2644, 1797, 257, 2459, 12, 77, 1429, 4295, 294, 641, 1364, 4675, 13, 51340], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12793302536010742, "compression_ratio": 1.5620689655172413, "no_speech_prob": 1.3303612768703066e-12}, {"id": 543, "seek": 197426, "start": 1994.3, "end": 1996.3799999999999, "text": " Programming languages are not the actual computation.", "tokens": [51367, 8338, 2810, 8650, 366, 406, 264, 3539, 24903, 13, 51471], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12793302536010742, "compression_ratio": 1.5620689655172413, "no_speech_prob": 1.3303612768703066e-12}, {"id": 544, "seek": 197426, "start": 1996.9, "end": 1998.06, "text": " They are descriptive tools.", "tokens": [51497, 814, 366, 42585, 3873, 13, 51555], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12793302536010742, "compression_ratio": 1.5620689655172413, "no_speech_prob": 1.3303612768703066e-12}, {"id": 545, "seek": 197426, "start": 1998.2, "end": 1999.92, "text": " Like blueprints, sort of.", "tokens": [51562, 1743, 888, 23547, 47523, 11, 1333, 295, 13, 51648], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12793302536010742, "compression_ratio": 1.5620689655172413, "no_speech_prob": 1.3303612768703066e-12}, {"id": 546, "seek": 197426, "start": 2000.08, "end": 2000.48, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [51656, 7587, 13, 51676], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12793302536010742, "compression_ratio": 1.5620689655172413, "no_speech_prob": 1.3303612768703066e-12}, {"id": 547, "seek": 200048, "start": 2000.48, "end": 2007.22, "text": " They are a user interface that helps us name, organize, and compress massive graphs so we can reason about them.", "tokens": [50365, 814, 366, 257, 4195, 9226, 300, 3665, 505, 1315, 11, 13859, 11, 293, 14778, 5994, 24877, 370, 321, 393, 1778, 466, 552, 13, 50702], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09761520347209891, "compression_ratio": 1.5962962962962963, "no_speech_prob": 1.6047124566653803e-12}, {"id": 548, "seek": 200048, "start": 2007.7, "end": 2013.1, "text": " We use concepts like functions, modules, and object-oriented classes to abstract the graph away.", "tokens": [50726, 492, 764, 10392, 411, 6828, 11, 16679, 11, 293, 2657, 12, 27414, 5359, 281, 12649, 264, 4295, 1314, 13, 50996], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09761520347209891, "compression_ratio": 1.5962962962962963, "no_speech_prob": 1.6047124566653803e-12}, {"id": 549, "seek": 200048, "start": 2013.66, "end": 2015.04, "text": " Abstraction is human compression.", "tokens": [51024, 46853, 26766, 307, 1952, 19355, 13, 51093], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09761520347209891, "compression_ratio": 1.5962962962962963, "no_speech_prob": 1.6047124566653803e-12}, {"id": 550, "seek": 200048, "start": 2015.56, "end": 2021.38, "text": " But when you click Run and the code actually executes, the compiler's job is to decompress it.", "tokens": [51119, 583, 562, 291, 2052, 8950, 293, 264, 3089, 767, 4454, 1819, 11, 264, 31958, 311, 1691, 307, 281, 22867, 735, 309, 13, 51410], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09761520347209891, "compression_ratio": 1.5962962962962963, "no_speech_prob": 1.6047124566653803e-12}, {"id": 551, "seek": 200048, "start": 2021.88, "end": 2026.38, "text": " It expands your linear text back out into the underlying multidimensional composition graph.", "tokens": [51435, 467, 33706, 428, 8213, 2487, 646, 484, 666, 264, 14217, 2120, 327, 332, 11075, 12686, 4295, 13, 51660], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09761520347209891, "compression_ratio": 1.5962962962962963, "no_speech_prob": 1.6047124566653803e-12}, {"id": 552, "seek": 202638, "start": 2026.38, "end": 2031.7600000000002, "text": " So a compiler isn't really a translator between different languages, like translating English to French.", "tokens": [50365, 407, 257, 31958, 1943, 380, 534, 257, 35223, 1296, 819, 8650, 11, 411, 35030, 3669, 281, 5522, 13, 50634], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13367868929493185, "compression_ratio": 1.5748987854251013, "no_speech_prob": 1.8111019411612417e-12}, {"id": 553, "seek": 202638, "start": 2031.88, "end": 2033.5, "text": " A compiler is a graph rewriter.", "tokens": [50640, 316, 31958, 307, 257, 4295, 319, 23681, 13, 50721], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13367868929493185, "compression_ratio": 1.5748987854251013, "no_speech_prob": 1.8111019411612417e-12}, {"id": 554, "seek": 202638, "start": 2033.7600000000002, "end": 2034.0800000000002, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50734, 7587, 13, 50750], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13367868929493185, "compression_ratio": 1.5748987854251013, "no_speech_prob": 1.8111019411612417e-12}, {"id": 555, "seek": 202638, "start": 2034.3600000000001, "end": 2036.46, "text": " And this reframes what optimization is.", "tokens": [50764, 400, 341, 13334, 1632, 437, 19618, 307, 13, 50869], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13367868929493185, "compression_ratio": 1.5748987854251013, "no_speech_prob": 1.8111019411612417e-12}, {"id": 556, "seek": 202638, "start": 2036.98, "end": 2041.5200000000002, "text": " When a compiler optimizes your code to make it run faster, it isn't making the code better.", "tokens": [50895, 1133, 257, 31958, 5028, 5660, 428, 3089, 281, 652, 309, 1190, 4663, 11, 309, 1943, 380, 1455, 264, 3089, 1101, 13, 51122], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13367868929493185, "compression_ratio": 1.5748987854251013, "no_speech_prob": 1.8111019411612417e-12}, {"id": 557, "seek": 202638, "start": 2041.8600000000001, "end": 2045.96, "text": " It is navigating what Fliction calls an observational equivalence class.", "tokens": [51139, 467, 307, 32054, 437, 3235, 4105, 5498, 364, 9951, 1478, 9052, 655, 1508, 13, 51344], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13367868929493185, "compression_ratio": 1.5748987854251013, "no_speech_prob": 1.8111019411612417e-12}, {"id": 558, "seek": 202638, "start": 2046.0400000000002, "end": 2046.24, "text": " Okay.", "tokens": [51348, 1033, 13, 51358], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13367868929493185, "compression_ratio": 1.5748987854251013, "no_speech_prob": 1.8111019411612417e-12}, {"id": 559, "seek": 202638, "start": 2046.3600000000001, "end": 2047.4, "text": " What does that mean in practice?", "tokens": [51364, 708, 775, 300, 914, 294, 3124, 30, 51416], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13367868929493185, "compression_ratio": 1.5748987854251013, "no_speech_prob": 1.8111019411612417e-12}, {"id": 560, "seek": 204740, "start": 2047.4, "end": 2057.1600000000003, "text": " The compiler is looking at the massive graph you generated, and it is searching for a mathematically cheaper graph geometry that is guaranteed to produce the exact same observable history.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 31958, 307, 1237, 412, 264, 5994, 4295, 291, 10833, 11, 293, 309, 307, 10808, 337, 257, 44003, 12284, 4295, 18426, 300, 307, 18031, 281, 5258, 264, 1900, 912, 9951, 712, 2503, 13, 50853], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12561636135495943, "compression_ratio": 1.6870748299319729, "no_speech_prob": 1.831788843872917e-12}, {"id": 561, "seek": 204740, "start": 2057.4, "end": 2059.2200000000003, "text": " I want a concrete example of that.", "tokens": [50865, 286, 528, 257, 9859, 1365, 295, 300, 13, 50956], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12561636135495943, "compression_ratio": 1.6870748299319729, "no_speech_prob": 1.831788843872917e-12}, {"id": 562, "seek": 204740, "start": 2059.54, "end": 2062.5, "text": " What does a cheaper graph geometry actually look like?", "tokens": [50972, 708, 775, 257, 12284, 4295, 18426, 767, 574, 411, 30, 51120], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12561636135495943, "compression_ratio": 1.6870748299319729, "no_speech_prob": 1.831788843872917e-12}, {"id": 563, "seek": 204740, "start": 2062.76, "end": 2065.04, "text": " Let's look at a technique called operator fusion.", "tokens": [51133, 961, 311, 574, 412, 257, 6532, 1219, 12973, 23100, 13, 51247], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12561636135495943, "compression_ratio": 1.6870748299319729, "no_speech_prob": 1.831788843872917e-12}, {"id": 564, "seek": 204740, "start": 2065.84, "end": 2069.8, "text": " Imagine your graph has a node that takes a number and multiplies it by two.", "tokens": [51287, 11739, 428, 4295, 575, 257, 9984, 300, 2516, 257, 1230, 293, 12788, 530, 309, 538, 732, 13, 51485], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12561636135495943, "compression_ratio": 1.6870748299319729, "no_speech_prob": 1.831788843872917e-12}, {"id": 565, "seek": 204740, "start": 2070.38, "end": 2073.78, "text": " The very next node in the graph takes that result and adds three.", "tokens": [51514, 440, 588, 958, 9984, 294, 264, 4295, 2516, 300, 1874, 293, 10860, 1045, 13, 51684], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12561636135495943, "compression_ratio": 1.6870748299319729, "no_speech_prob": 1.831788843872917e-12}, {"id": 566, "seek": 204740, "start": 2073.96, "end": 2074.28, "text": " Okay.", "tokens": [51693, 1033, 13, 51709], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12561636135495943, "compression_ratio": 1.6870748299319729, "no_speech_prob": 1.831788843872917e-12}, {"id": 567, "seek": 204740, "start": 2074.5, "end": 2075.2400000000002, "text": " Pretty simple math.", "tokens": [51720, 10693, 2199, 5221, 13, 51757], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12561636135495943, "compression_ratio": 1.6870748299319729, "no_speech_prob": 1.831788843872917e-12}, {"id": 568, "seek": 207524, "start": 2075.24, "end": 2080.4799999999996, "text": " The compiler looks at that topology and says, executing two separate nodes takes extra time.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 31958, 1542, 412, 300, 1192, 1793, 293, 1619, 11, 32368, 732, 4994, 13891, 2516, 2857, 565, 13, 50627], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14571060180664064, "compression_ratio": 1.6687898089171975, "no_speech_prob": 1.755388044123729e-12}, {"id": 569, "seek": 207524, "start": 2080.9199999999996, "end": 2086.9399999999996, "text": " It might replace those two nodes with a single fused node that computes 2x plus 3 in one step.", "tokens": [50649, 467, 1062, 7406, 729, 732, 13891, 365, 257, 2167, 283, 4717, 9984, 300, 715, 1819, 568, 87, 1804, 805, 294, 472, 1823, 13, 50950], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14571060180664064, "compression_ratio": 1.6687898089171975, "no_speech_prob": 1.755388044123729e-12}, {"id": 570, "seek": 207524, "start": 2087.06, "end": 2087.54, "text": " Oh, I see.", "tokens": [50956, 876, 11, 286, 536, 13, 50980], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14571060180664064, "compression_ratio": 1.6687898089171975, "no_speech_prob": 1.755388044123729e-12}, {"id": 571, "seek": 207524, "start": 2087.8599999999997, "end": 2089.2799999999997, "text": " The topology of the graph changes.", "tokens": [50996, 440, 1192, 1793, 295, 264, 4295, 2962, 13, 51067], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14571060180664064, "compression_ratio": 1.6687898089171975, "no_speech_prob": 1.755388044123729e-12}, {"id": 572, "seek": 207524, "start": 2089.6, "end": 2091.3399999999997, "text": " The number of nodes physically shrinks.", "tokens": [51083, 440, 1230, 295, 13891, 9762, 9884, 16431, 13, 51170], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14571060180664064, "compression_ratio": 1.6687898089171975, "no_speech_prob": 1.755388044123729e-12}, {"id": 573, "seek": 207524, "start": 2091.68, "end": 2096.8799999999997, "text": " But the observable history it produces is identical, or considered dead graph elimination.", "tokens": [51187, 583, 264, 9951, 712, 2503, 309, 14725, 307, 14800, 11, 420, 4888, 3116, 4295, 29224, 13, 51447], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14571060180664064, "compression_ratio": 1.6687898089171975, "no_speech_prob": 1.755388044123729e-12}, {"id": 574, "seek": 207524, "start": 2097.52, "end": 2102.9799999999996, "text": " The compiler will locate entire branches of the graph whose outputs never actually connect to the final result,", "tokens": [51479, 440, 31958, 486, 22370, 2302, 14770, 295, 264, 4295, 6104, 23930, 1128, 767, 1745, 281, 264, 2572, 1874, 11, 51752], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14571060180664064, "compression_ratio": 1.6687898089171975, "no_speech_prob": 1.755388044123729e-12}, {"id": 575, "seek": 207524, "start": 2102.9799999999996, "end": 2105.2, "text": " and it will simply prune them out of existence.", "tokens": [51752, 293, 309, 486, 2935, 582, 2613, 552, 484, 295, 9123, 13, 51863], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14571060180664064, "compression_ratio": 1.6687898089171975, "no_speech_prob": 1.755388044123729e-12}, {"id": 576, "seek": 210524, "start": 2105.24, "end": 2107.04, "text": " And what about control flow?", "tokens": [50365, 400, 437, 466, 1969, 3095, 30, 50455], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.229458474493646, "compression_ratio": 1.4764397905759161, "no_speech_prob": 1.5922259170852993e-12}, {"id": 577, "seek": 210524, "start": 2107.3199999999997, "end": 2112.12, "text": " If statements, while loops, for loops, these are the absolute bread and butter of coding.", "tokens": [50469, 759, 12363, 11, 1339, 16121, 11, 337, 16121, 11, 613, 366, 264, 8236, 5961, 293, 5517, 295, 17720, 13, 50709], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.229458474493646, "compression_ratio": 1.4764397905759161, "no_speech_prob": 1.5922259170852993e-12}, {"id": 578, "seek": 210524, "start": 2112.2599999999998, "end": 2115.08, "text": " Every programmer learns if this, then that on day one.", "tokens": [50716, 2048, 32116, 27152, 498, 341, 11, 550, 300, 322, 786, 472, 13, 50857], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.229458474493646, "compression_ratio": 1.4764397905759161, "no_speech_prob": 1.5922259170852993e-12}, {"id": 579, "seek": 210524, "start": 2115.2, "end": 2119.58, "text": " In SpherePop, control flow as a primitive foundational concept is an illusion.", "tokens": [50863, 682, 318, 6605, 38677, 11, 1969, 3095, 382, 257, 28540, 32195, 3410, 307, 364, 18854, 13, 51082], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.229458474493646, "compression_ratio": 1.4764397905759161, "no_speech_prob": 1.5922259170852993e-12}, {"id": 580, "seek": 210524, "start": 2119.8599999999997, "end": 2120.3999999999996, "text": " An illusion?", "tokens": [51096, 1107, 18854, 30, 51123], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.229458474493646, "compression_ratio": 1.4764397905759161, "no_speech_prob": 1.5922259170852993e-12}, {"id": 581, "seek": 210524, "start": 2120.7599999999998, "end": 2121.24, "text": " Come on.", "tokens": [51141, 2492, 322, 13, 51165], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.229458474493646, "compression_ratio": 1.4764397905759161, "no_speech_prob": 1.5922259170852993e-12}, {"id": 582, "seek": 210524, "start": 2121.3799999999997, "end": 2121.7599999999998, "text": " Really?", "tokens": [51172, 4083, 30, 51191], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.229458474493646, "compression_ratio": 1.4764397905759161, "no_speech_prob": 1.5922259170852993e-12}, {"id": 583, "seek": 212176, "start": 2121.76, "end": 2129.1400000000003, "text": " And a fill statement in your code feels like a magical fork in the road of time, where the universe splits into two possibilities.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 257, 2836, 5629, 294, 428, 3089, 3417, 411, 257, 12066, 17716, 294, 264, 3060, 295, 565, 11, 689, 264, 6445, 37741, 666, 732, 12178, 13, 50734], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1588201904296875, "compression_ratio": 1.580188679245283, "no_speech_prob": 1.775825363495298e-12}, {"id": 584, "seek": 212176, "start": 2129.6400000000003, "end": 2135.42, "text": " But on the graph, it is simply a node with two incoming continuations and a select operator.", "tokens": [50759, 583, 322, 264, 4295, 11, 309, 307, 2935, 257, 9984, 365, 732, 22341, 2993, 763, 293, 257, 3048, 12973, 13, 51048], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1588201904296875, "compression_ratio": 1.580188679245283, "no_speech_prob": 1.775825363495298e-12}, {"id": 585, "seek": 212176, "start": 2135.92, "end": 2141.76, "text": " The select operator looks at the condition, true or false, and outputs the value from the corresponding branch.", "tokens": [51073, 440, 3048, 12973, 1542, 412, 264, 4188, 11, 2074, 420, 7908, 11, 293, 23930, 264, 2158, 490, 264, 11760, 9819, 13, 51365], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1588201904296875, "compression_ratio": 1.580188679245283, "no_speech_prob": 1.775825363495298e-12}, {"id": 586, "seek": 214176, "start": 2141.76, "end": 2143.6200000000003, "text": " Wait, so the graph doesn't actually fork.", "tokens": [50365, 3802, 11, 370, 264, 4295, 1177, 380, 767, 17716, 13, 50458], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.23171611059279668, "compression_ratio": 1.481012658227848, "no_speech_prob": 1.4158149479193138e-12}, {"id": 587, "seek": 214176, "start": 2143.88, "end": 2145.96, "text": " Both paths just exist on the motherboard.", "tokens": [50471, 6767, 14518, 445, 2514, 322, 264, 32916, 13, 50575], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.23171611059279668, "compression_ratio": 1.481012658227848, "no_speech_prob": 1.4158149479193138e-12}, {"id": 588, "seek": 214176, "start": 2146.46, "end": 2147.76, "text": " Both paths exist structurally.", "tokens": [50600, 6767, 14518, 2514, 6594, 6512, 13, 50665], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.23171611059279668, "compression_ratio": 1.481012658227848, "no_speech_prob": 1.4158149479193138e-12}, {"id": 589, "seek": 214176, "start": 2148.36, "end": 2151.26, "text": " The select operator just decides which history to pass forward.", "tokens": [50695, 440, 3048, 12973, 445, 14898, 597, 2503, 281, 1320, 2128, 13, 50840], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.23171611059279668, "compression_ratio": 1.481012658227848, "no_speech_prob": 1.4158149479193138e-12}, {"id": 590, "seek": 214176, "start": 2151.88, "end": 2153.0800000000004, "text": " And remember our cartridges.", "tokens": [50871, 400, 1604, 527, 47036, 13, 50931], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.23171611059279668, "compression_ratio": 1.481012658227848, "no_speech_prob": 1.4158149479193138e-12}, {"id": 591, "seek": 214176, "start": 2153.42, "end": 2153.86, "text": " Oh, right.", "tokens": [50948, 876, 11, 558, 13, 50970], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.23171611059279668, "compression_ratio": 1.481012658227848, "no_speech_prob": 1.4158149479193138e-12}, {"id": 592, "seek": 214176, "start": 2153.96, "end": 2154.34, "text": " The cartridges.", "tokens": [50975, 440, 47036, 13, 50994], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.23171611059279668, "compression_ratio": 1.481012658227848, "no_speech_prob": 1.4158149479193138e-12}, {"id": 593, "seek": 215434, "start": 2154.34, "end": 2160.6000000000004, "text": " If you swap the Boolean cartridge for a fuzzy logic cartridge, the select operator doesn't have to choose just one path.", "tokens": [50365, 759, 291, 18135, 264, 23351, 28499, 27753, 337, 257, 34710, 9952, 27753, 11, 264, 3048, 12973, 1177, 380, 362, 281, 2826, 445, 472, 3100, 13, 50678], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09014725892440133, "compression_ratio": 1.6094276094276094, "no_speech_prob": 1.8610291259435474e-12}, {"id": 594, "seek": 215434, "start": 2160.76, "end": 2165.8, "text": " It might evaluate both branches and blend their histories together based on a 40-60 probability.", "tokens": [50686, 467, 1062, 13059, 1293, 14770, 293, 10628, 641, 30631, 1214, 2361, 322, 257, 3356, 12, 4550, 8482, 13, 50938], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09014725892440133, "compression_ratio": 1.6094276094276094, "no_speech_prob": 1.8610291259435474e-12}, {"id": 595, "seek": 215434, "start": 2166.46, "end": 2169.2200000000003, "text": " Control flow is just an operator cartridge interacting with the graph.", "tokens": [50971, 12912, 3095, 307, 445, 364, 12973, 27753, 18017, 365, 264, 4295, 13, 51109], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09014725892440133, "compression_ratio": 1.6094276094276094, "no_speech_prob": 1.8610291259435474e-12}, {"id": 596, "seek": 215434, "start": 2169.38, "end": 2170.6600000000003, "text": " That is wild.", "tokens": [51117, 663, 307, 4868, 13, 51181], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09014725892440133, "compression_ratio": 1.6094276094276094, "no_speech_prob": 1.8610291259435474e-12}, {"id": 597, "seek": 215434, "start": 2170.86, "end": 2174.4, "text": " But this brings up a massive question about time and recursion.", "tokens": [51191, 583, 341, 5607, 493, 257, 5994, 1168, 466, 565, 293, 20560, 313, 13, 51368], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09014725892440133, "compression_ratio": 1.6094276094276094, "no_speech_prob": 1.8610291259435474e-12}, {"id": 598, "seek": 215434, "start": 2174.76, "end": 2179.1000000000004, "text": " If the graph is just a static web of nodes on a motherboard, how do things ever repeat?", "tokens": [51386, 759, 264, 4295, 307, 445, 257, 13437, 3670, 295, 13891, 322, 257, 32916, 11, 577, 360, 721, 1562, 7149, 30, 51603], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09014725892440133, "compression_ratio": 1.6094276094276094, "no_speech_prob": 1.8610291259435474e-12}, {"id": 599, "seek": 215434, "start": 2179.46, "end": 2180.36, "text": " How do you have a loop?", "tokens": [51621, 1012, 360, 291, 362, 257, 6367, 30, 51666], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09014725892440133, "compression_ratio": 1.6094276094276094, "no_speech_prob": 1.8610291259435474e-12}, {"id": 600, "seek": 218036, "start": 2180.36, "end": 2184.2400000000002, "text": " This requires us to look at directed encyclographs, or DAGs.", "tokens": [50365, 639, 7029, 505, 281, 574, 412, 12898, 465, 34080, 3108, 82, 11, 420, 9578, 33715, 13, 50559], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1312677443973602, "compression_ratio": 1.6145833333333333, "no_speech_prob": 1.443960619476603e-12}, {"id": 601, "seek": 218036, "start": 2185.02, "end": 2188.7000000000003, "text": " A DAG represents pure, unadulterated compositional flow.", "tokens": [50598, 316, 9578, 38, 8855, 6075, 11, 517, 345, 425, 391, 770, 10199, 2628, 3095, 13, 50782], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1312677443973602, "compression_ratio": 1.6145833333333333, "no_speech_prob": 1.443960619476603e-12}, {"id": 602, "seek": 218036, "start": 2189.36, "end": 2193.32, "text": " The data moves in one direction, from input to output, never looking back.", "tokens": [50815, 440, 1412, 6067, 294, 472, 3513, 11, 490, 4846, 281, 5598, 11, 1128, 1237, 646, 13, 51013], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1312677443973602, "compression_ratio": 1.6145833333333333, "no_speech_prob": 1.443960619476603e-12}, {"id": 603, "seek": 218036, "start": 2193.86, "end": 2196.7200000000003, "text": " But what happens when you introduce a cycle into that graph?", "tokens": [51040, 583, 437, 2314, 562, 291, 5366, 257, 6586, 666, 300, 4295, 30, 51183], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1312677443973602, "compression_ratio": 1.6145833333333333, "no_speech_prob": 1.443960619476603e-12}, {"id": 604, "seek": 218036, "start": 2197.2400000000002, "end": 2202.58, "text": " What happens when node C has a copper trace that points backward, connecting it to node A, which came before it?", "tokens": [51209, 708, 2314, 562, 9984, 383, 575, 257, 15007, 13508, 300, 2793, 23897, 11, 11015, 309, 281, 9984, 316, 11, 597, 1361, 949, 309, 30, 51476], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1312677443973602, "compression_ratio": 1.6145833333333333, "no_speech_prob": 1.443960619476603e-12}, {"id": 605, "seek": 218036, "start": 2202.7000000000003, "end": 2203.56, "text": " Right, that's a loop.", "tokens": [51482, 1779, 11, 300, 311, 257, 6367, 13, 51525], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1312677443973602, "compression_ratio": 1.6145833333333333, "no_speech_prob": 1.443960619476603e-12}, {"id": 606, "seek": 218036, "start": 2203.76, "end": 2208.92, "text": " But doesn't a cycle in the graph break the axiom of historical monotonicity?", "tokens": [51535, 583, 1177, 380, 257, 6586, 294, 264, 4295, 1821, 264, 6360, 72, 298, 295, 8584, 1108, 310, 11630, 507, 30, 51793], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1312677443973602, "compression_ratio": 1.6145833333333333, "no_speech_prob": 1.443960619476603e-12}, {"id": 607, "seek": 220892, "start": 2208.92, "end": 2213.34, "text": " Because if you loop back to the beginning, aren't you erasing the whiteboard and overriding the past?", "tokens": [50365, 1436, 498, 291, 6367, 646, 281, 264, 2863, 11, 3212, 380, 291, 1189, 3349, 264, 2418, 3787, 293, 670, 81, 2819, 264, 1791, 30, 50586], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14886348430926982, "compression_ratio": 1.7263157894736842, "no_speech_prob": 1.460984545148536e-12}, {"id": 608, "seek": 220892, "start": 2213.54, "end": 2215.26, "text": " You would be, in a traditional system.", "tokens": [50596, 509, 576, 312, 11, 294, 257, 5164, 1185, 13, 50682], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14886348430926982, "compression_ratio": 1.7263157894736842, "no_speech_prob": 1.460984545148536e-12}, {"id": 609, "seek": 220892, "start": 2215.7200000000003, "end": 2219.86, "text": " But this is the genius of spherepop, separating the graph topology from the history.", "tokens": [50705, 583, 341, 307, 264, 14017, 295, 16687, 13872, 11, 29279, 264, 4295, 1192, 1793, 490, 264, 2503, 13, 50912], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14886348430926982, "compression_ratio": 1.7263157894736842, "no_speech_prob": 1.460984545148536e-12}, {"id": 610, "seek": 220892, "start": 2220.38, "end": 2222.58, "text": " A cycle in the graph represents feedback.", "tokens": [50938, 316, 6586, 294, 264, 4295, 8855, 5824, 13, 51048], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14886348430926982, "compression_ratio": 1.7263157894736842, "no_speech_prob": 1.460984545148536e-12}, {"id": 611, "seek": 220892, "start": 2223.26, "end": 2225.42, "text": " But it doesn't feed back into the same history.", "tokens": [51082, 583, 309, 1177, 380, 3154, 646, 666, 264, 912, 2503, 13, 51190], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14886348430926982, "compression_ratio": 1.7263157894736842, "no_speech_prob": 1.460984545148536e-12}, {"id": 612, "seek": 220892, "start": 2225.6800000000003, "end": 2227.42, "text": " It feeds back into the next history.", "tokens": [51203, 467, 23712, 646, 666, 264, 958, 2503, 13, 51290], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14886348430926982, "compression_ratio": 1.7263157894736842, "no_speech_prob": 1.460984545148536e-12}, {"id": 613, "seek": 220892, "start": 2227.58, "end": 2227.92, "text": " Oh.", "tokens": [51298, 876, 13, 51315], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14886348430926982, "compression_ratio": 1.7263157894736842, "no_speech_prob": 1.460984545148536e-12}, {"id": 614, "seek": 220892, "start": 2228.42, "end": 2230.4, "text": " It's like turning to a fresh page in the journal.", "tokens": [51340, 467, 311, 411, 6246, 281, 257, 4451, 3028, 294, 264, 6708, 13, 51439], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14886348430926982, "compression_ratio": 1.7263157894736842, "no_speech_prob": 1.460984545148536e-12}, {"id": 615, "seek": 220892, "start": 2230.66, "end": 2234.38, "text": " The loop just tells you to start writing on page 2 using the conclusions from page 1.", "tokens": [51452, 440, 6367, 445, 5112, 291, 281, 722, 3579, 322, 3028, 568, 1228, 264, 22865, 490, 3028, 502, 13, 51638], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14886348430926982, "compression_ratio": 1.7263157894736842, "no_speech_prob": 1.460984545148536e-12}, {"id": 616, "seek": 223438, "start": 2234.38, "end": 2235.08, "text": " Precisely.", "tokens": [50365, 48746, 736, 13, 50400], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16472629264548974, "compression_ratio": 1.6395759717314489, "no_speech_prob": 1.6108364642164474e-12}, {"id": 617, "seek": 223438, "start": 2235.6600000000003, "end": 2239.12, "text": " History at time 2 becomes history time 2 plus 1.", "tokens": [50429, 12486, 412, 565, 568, 3643, 2503, 565, 568, 1804, 502, 13, 50602], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16472629264548974, "compression_ratio": 1.6395759717314489, "no_speech_prob": 1.6108364642164474e-12}, {"id": 618, "seek": 223438, "start": 2239.86, "end": 2242.92, "text": " The physical graph on the motherboard is cyclic and loops back on itself.", "tokens": [50639, 440, 4001, 4295, 322, 264, 32916, 307, 38154, 1050, 293, 16121, 646, 322, 2564, 13, 50792], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16472629264548974, "compression_ratio": 1.6395759717314489, "no_speech_prob": 1.6108364642164474e-12}, {"id": 619, "seek": 223438, "start": 2243.2200000000003, "end": 2248.1, "text": " But the histories generated by repeatedly executing that cycle are linearly ordered and permanent.", "tokens": [50807, 583, 264, 30631, 10833, 538, 18227, 32368, 300, 6586, 366, 43586, 8866, 293, 10996, 13, 51051], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16472629264548974, "compression_ratio": 1.6395759717314489, "no_speech_prob": 1.6108364642164474e-12}, {"id": 620, "seek": 223438, "start": 2248.28, "end": 2249.08, "text": " That is so elegant.", "tokens": [51060, 663, 307, 370, 21117, 13, 51100], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16472629264548974, "compression_ratio": 1.6395759717314489, "no_speech_prob": 1.6108364642164474e-12}, {"id": 621, "seek": 223438, "start": 2249.32, "end": 2252.2400000000002, "text": " Time itself emerges explicitly as a sequence of histories.", "tokens": [51112, 6161, 2564, 38965, 20803, 382, 257, 8310, 295, 30631, 13, 51258], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16472629264548974, "compression_ratio": 1.6395759717314489, "no_speech_prob": 1.6108364642164474e-12}, {"id": 622, "seek": 223438, "start": 2252.88, "end": 2255.98, "text": " Recursion isn't some special magical feature of a programming language.", "tokens": [51290, 9647, 2156, 313, 1943, 380, 512, 2121, 12066, 4111, 295, 257, 9410, 2856, 13, 51445], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16472629264548974, "compression_ratio": 1.6395759717314489, "no_speech_prob": 1.6108364642164474e-12}, {"id": 623, "seek": 223438, "start": 2256.42, "end": 2261.08, "text": " It is simply repeated self-composition across successive, uneraseable histories.", "tokens": [51467, 467, 307, 2935, 10477, 2698, 12, 21541, 5830, 2108, 48043, 11, 517, 260, 651, 712, 30631, 13, 51700], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16472629264548974, "compression_ratio": 1.6395759717314489, "no_speech_prob": 1.6108364642164474e-12}, {"id": 624, "seek": 226108, "start": 2261.08, "end": 2266.7799999999997, "text": " And persistent state, what we normally call a computer's memory or hard drive,", "tokens": [50365, 400, 24315, 1785, 11, 437, 321, 5646, 818, 257, 3820, 311, 4675, 420, 1152, 3332, 11, 50650], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12602677345275878, "compression_ratio": 1.612794612794613, "no_speech_prob": 1.8326336542057176e-12}, {"id": 625, "seek": 226108, "start": 2266.94, "end": 2271.94, "text": " is just committed history that remains available as an input for the next iteration of the cycle.", "tokens": [50658, 307, 445, 7784, 2503, 300, 7023, 2435, 382, 364, 4846, 337, 264, 958, 24784, 295, 264, 6586, 13, 50908], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12602677345275878, "compression_ratio": 1.612794612794613, "no_speech_prob": 1.8326336542057176e-12}, {"id": 626, "seek": 226108, "start": 2272.36, "end": 2277.84, "text": " I want to challenge you, the listener, to look at any process in your life right now through this lens.", "tokens": [50929, 286, 528, 281, 3430, 291, 11, 264, 31569, 11, 281, 574, 412, 604, 1399, 294, 428, 993, 558, 586, 807, 341, 6765, 13, 51203], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12602677345275878, "compression_ratio": 1.612794612794613, "no_speech_prob": 1.8326336542057176e-12}, {"id": 627, "seek": 226108, "start": 2278.38, "end": 2280.44, "text": " Think about a recipe you use to cook dinner.", "tokens": [51230, 6557, 466, 257, 6782, 291, 764, 281, 2543, 6148, 13, 51333], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12602677345275878, "compression_ratio": 1.612794612794613, "no_speech_prob": 1.8326336542057176e-12}, {"id": 628, "seek": 226108, "start": 2280.7599999999998, "end": 2284.18, "text": " Or a workflow you use at your job to onboard a new client.", "tokens": [51349, 1610, 257, 20993, 291, 764, 412, 428, 1691, 281, 24033, 257, 777, 6423, 13, 51520], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12602677345275878, "compression_ratio": 1.612794612794613, "no_speech_prob": 1.8326336542057176e-12}, {"id": 629, "seek": 226108, "start": 2284.5, "end": 2288.2999999999997, "text": " We almost always write these processes down as a linear list of steps.", "tokens": [51536, 492, 1920, 1009, 2464, 613, 7555, 760, 382, 257, 8213, 1329, 295, 4439, 13, 51726], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12602677345275878, "compression_ratio": 1.612794612794613, "no_speech_prob": 1.8326336542057176e-12}, {"id": 630, "seek": 226108, "start": 2288.44, "end": 2290.0, "text": " Step 1, step 2, step 3.", "tokens": [51733, 5470, 502, 11, 1823, 568, 11, 1823, 805, 13, 51811], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12602677345275878, "compression_ratio": 1.612794612794613, "no_speech_prob": 1.8326336542057176e-12}, {"id": 631, "seek": 229000, "start": 2290.0, "end": 2293.14, "text": " Exactly. But in reality, it's a web of dependencies.", "tokens": [50365, 7587, 13, 583, 294, 4103, 11, 309, 311, 257, 3670, 295, 36606, 13, 50522], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11956910465074622, "compression_ratio": 1.635135135135135, "no_speech_prob": 2.4658005672029137e-12}, {"id": 632, "seek": 229000, "start": 2293.48, "end": 2296.86, "text": " If you are making pasta, you can boil the water while you chop the onions.", "tokens": [50539, 759, 291, 366, 1455, 13296, 11, 291, 393, 13329, 264, 1281, 1339, 291, 7931, 264, 13146, 13, 50708], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11956910465074622, "compression_ratio": 1.635135135135135, "no_speech_prob": 2.4658005672029137e-12}, {"id": 633, "seek": 229000, "start": 2297.14, "end": 2299.62, "text": " The onions do not historically depend on the water.", "tokens": [50722, 440, 13146, 360, 406, 16180, 5672, 322, 264, 1281, 13, 50846], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11956910465074622, "compression_ratio": 1.635135135135135, "no_speech_prob": 2.4658005672029137e-12}, {"id": 634, "seek": 229000, "start": 2299.76, "end": 2301.42, "text": " They can be executed concurrently.", "tokens": [50853, 814, 393, 312, 17577, 37702, 356, 13, 50936], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11956910465074622, "compression_ratio": 1.635135135135135, "no_speech_prob": 2.4658005672029137e-12}, {"id": 635, "seek": 229000, "start": 2301.9, "end": 2305.12, "text": " The linear list you wrote on the recipe card is a lossy human compression.", "tokens": [50960, 440, 8213, 1329, 291, 4114, 322, 264, 6782, 2920, 307, 257, 4470, 88, 1952, 19355, 13, 51121], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11956910465074622, "compression_ratio": 1.635135135135135, "no_speech_prob": 2.4658005672029137e-12}, {"id": 636, "seek": 229000, "start": 2305.7, "end": 2309.68, "text": " The reality of cooking that meal is a multidimensional composition graph.", "tokens": [51150, 440, 4103, 295, 6361, 300, 6791, 307, 257, 2120, 327, 332, 11075, 12686, 4295, 13, 51349], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11956910465074622, "compression_ratio": 1.635135135135135, "no_speech_prob": 2.4658005672029137e-12}, {"id": 637, "seek": 230968, "start": 2309.68, "end": 2315.3999999999996, "text": " And that composition graph is what the SpherePop runtime natively executes.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 300, 12686, 4295, 307, 437, 264, 318, 6605, 38677, 34474, 8470, 356, 4454, 1819, 13, 50651], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1653555052621024, "compression_ratio": 1.5080213903743316, "no_speech_prob": 1.5549715378163076e-12}, {"id": 638, "seek": 230968, "start": 2315.94, "end": 2318.58, "text": " It doesn't read your recipe card line by line.", "tokens": [50678, 467, 1177, 380, 1401, 428, 6782, 2920, 1622, 538, 1622, 13, 50810], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1653555052621024, "compression_ratio": 1.5080213903743316, "no_speech_prob": 1.5549715378163076e-12}, {"id": 639, "seek": 230968, "start": 2318.8199999999997, "end": 2323.44, "text": " It reverses the graph, firing operators the exact moment their dependencies are met,", "tokens": [50822, 467, 14582, 279, 264, 4295, 11, 16045, 19077, 264, 1900, 1623, 641, 36606, 366, 1131, 11, 51053], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1653555052621024, "compression_ratio": 1.5080213903743316, "no_speech_prob": 1.5549715378163076e-12}, {"id": 640, "seek": 230968, "start": 2323.8199999999997, "end": 2325.8999999999996, "text": " and appending the results to the permanent journal.", "tokens": [51072, 293, 724, 2029, 264, 3542, 281, 264, 10996, 6708, 13, 51176], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1653555052621024, "compression_ratio": 1.5080213903743316, "no_speech_prob": 1.5549715378163076e-12}, {"id": 641, "seek": 230968, "start": 2326.12, "end": 2327.16, "text": " It's totally inverted.", "tokens": [51187, 467, 311, 3879, 38969, 13, 51239], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1653555052621024, "compression_ratio": 1.5080213903743316, "no_speech_prob": 1.5549715378163076e-12}, {"id": 642, "seek": 232716, "start": 2327.16, "end": 2331.7799999999997, "text": " It is a fundamental inversion of how we build systems.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 307, 257, 8088, 43576, 295, 577, 321, 1322, 3652, 13, 50596], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12549292852008154, "compression_ratio": 1.4378698224852071, "no_speech_prob": 1.39932932862602e-12}, {"id": 643, "seek": 232716, "start": 2331.94, "end": 2337.42, "text": " For 70 years, we have started with syntax, and we added static types, then we ran the code,", "tokens": [50604, 1171, 5285, 924, 11, 321, 362, 1409, 365, 28431, 11, 293, 321, 3869, 13437, 3467, 11, 550, 321, 5872, 264, 3089, 11, 50878], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12549292852008154, "compression_ratio": 1.4378698224852071, "no_speech_prob": 1.39932932862602e-12}, {"id": 644, "seek": 232716, "start": 2337.62, "end": 2342.72, "text": " and if it broke, we tried to extract a log file at the very end to piece together what happened.", "tokens": [50888, 293, 498, 309, 6902, 11, 321, 3031, 281, 8947, 257, 3565, 3991, 412, 264, 588, 917, 281, 2522, 1214, 437, 2011, 13, 51143], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12549292852008154, "compression_ratio": 1.4378698224852071, "no_speech_prob": 1.39932932862602e-12}, {"id": 645, "seek": 234272, "start": 2342.72, "end": 2347.02, "text": " And SpherePop says no. Start with the history. Make the history the math.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 318, 6605, 38677, 1619, 572, 13, 6481, 365, 264, 2503, 13, 4387, 264, 2503, 264, 5221, 13, 50580], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13826176298766577, "compression_ratio": 1.6501650165016502, "no_speech_prob": 1.5432390608471902e-12}, {"id": 646, "seek": 234272, "start": 2347.22, "end": 2352.66, "text": " Everything else, the types, the logic, the syntax, is just a descriptive human layer", "tokens": [50590, 5471, 1646, 11, 264, 3467, 11, 264, 9952, 11, 264, 28431, 11, 307, 445, 257, 42585, 1952, 4583, 50862], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13826176298766577, "compression_ratio": 1.6501650165016502, "no_speech_prob": 1.5432390608471902e-12}, {"id": 647, "seek": 234272, "start": 2352.66, "end": 2355.24, "text": " wrapped around that unreasonable provenance.", "tokens": [50862, 14226, 926, 300, 41730, 12785, 719, 13, 50991], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13826176298766577, "compression_ratio": 1.6501650165016502, "no_speech_prob": 1.5432390608471902e-12}, {"id": 648, "seek": 234272, "start": 2355.3599999999997, "end": 2358.2799999999997, "text": " Okay, let's take a deep breath and recap this incredible journey,", "tokens": [50997, 1033, 11, 718, 311, 747, 257, 2452, 6045, 293, 20928, 341, 4651, 4671, 11, 51143], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13826176298766577, "compression_ratio": 1.6501650165016502, "no_speech_prob": 1.5432390608471902e-12}, {"id": 649, "seek": 234272, "start": 2358.3999999999996, "end": 2360.16, "text": " because we have covered a lot of ground today.", "tokens": [51149, 570, 321, 362, 5343, 257, 688, 295, 2727, 965, 13, 51237], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13826176298766577, "compression_ratio": 1.6501650165016502, "no_speech_prob": 1.5432390608471902e-12}, {"id": 650, "seek": 234272, "start": 2360.4399999999996, "end": 2364.2999999999997, "text": " We started with the realization that overwriting state-erasing the whiteboard", "tokens": [51251, 492, 1409, 365, 264, 25138, 300, 670, 19868, 1785, 12, 260, 3349, 264, 2418, 3787, 51444], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13826176298766577, "compression_ratio": 1.6501650165016502, "no_speech_prob": 1.5432390608471902e-12}, {"id": 651, "seek": 234272, "start": 2364.2999999999997, "end": 2368.3799999999997, "text": " destroys the very provenance that makes mathematics and computation reliable.", "tokens": [51444, 36714, 264, 588, 12785, 719, 300, 1669, 18666, 293, 24903, 12924, 13, 51648], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13826176298766577, "compression_ratio": 1.6501650165016502, "no_speech_prob": 1.5432390608471902e-12}, {"id": 652, "seek": 234272, "start": 2368.48, "end": 2369.6, "text": " Right, the loss of context.", "tokens": [51653, 1779, 11, 264, 4470, 295, 4319, 13, 51709], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13826176298766577, "compression_ratio": 1.6501650165016502, "no_speech_prob": 1.5432390608471902e-12}, {"id": 653, "seek": 236960, "start": 2369.6, "end": 2375.52, "text": " So, SpherePop moves us from erasing states to presuming histories in a monotonic journal.", "tokens": [50365, 407, 11, 318, 6605, 38677, 6067, 505, 490, 1189, 3349, 4368, 281, 18028, 278, 30631, 294, 257, 1108, 310, 11630, 6708, 13, 50661], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17956179664248512, "compression_ratio": 1.5612648221343874, "no_speech_prob": 2.2894058610695156e-12}, {"id": 654, "seek": 236960, "start": 2376.2599999999998, "end": 2378.46, "text": " We built a universe out of just five verbs.", "tokens": [50698, 492, 3094, 257, 6445, 484, 295, 445, 1732, 30051, 13, 50808], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17956179664248512, "compression_ratio": 1.5612648221343874, "no_speech_prob": 2.2894058610695156e-12}, {"id": 655, "seek": 236960, "start": 2379.1, "end": 2380.74, "text": " Pop, to choose a path.", "tokens": [50840, 10215, 11, 281, 2826, 257, 3100, 13, 50922], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17956179664248512, "compression_ratio": 1.5612648221343874, "no_speech_prob": 2.2894058610695156e-12}, {"id": 656, "seek": 236960, "start": 2381.46, "end": 2383.7, "text": " Refuse, to constructively reject one.", "tokens": [50958, 16957, 438, 11, 281, 7690, 3413, 8248, 472, 13, 51070], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17956179664248512, "compression_ratio": 1.5612648221343874, "no_speech_prob": 2.2894058610695156e-12}, {"id": 657, "seek": 236960, "start": 2384.46, "end": 2386.16, "text": " Bind, to establish dependency.", "tokens": [51108, 363, 471, 11, 281, 8327, 33621, 13, 51193], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17956179664248512, "compression_ratio": 1.5612648221343874, "no_speech_prob": 2.2894058610695156e-12}, {"id": 658, "seek": 236960, "start": 2386.96, "end": 2391.7, "text": " Collapse, to declare two distinct histories equivalent without destroying either receipt.", "tokens": [51233, 4586, 11145, 11, 281, 19710, 732, 10644, 30631, 10344, 1553, 19926, 2139, 33882, 13, 51470], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17956179664248512, "compression_ratio": 1.5612648221343874, "no_speech_prob": 2.2894058610695156e-12}, {"id": 659, "seek": 236960, "start": 2392.22, "end": 2395.12, "text": " And meld, to merge concurrent paths.", "tokens": [51496, 400, 4795, 67, 11, 281, 22183, 37702, 14518, 13, 51641], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17956179664248512, "compression_ratio": 1.5612648221343874, "no_speech_prob": 2.2894058610695156e-12}, {"id": 660, "seek": 236960, "start": 2395.56, "end": 2398.56, "text": " From there, we completely reimagine types.", "tokens": [51663, 3358, 456, 11, 321, 2584, 33433, 10260, 3467, 13, 51813], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17956179664248512, "compression_ratio": 1.5612648221343874, "no_speech_prob": 2.2894058610695156e-12}, {"id": 661, "seek": 239856, "start": 2398.56, "end": 2402.42, "text": " They are no longer static buckets of data, but disciplined refusal structures,", "tokens": [50365, 814, 366, 572, 2854, 13437, 32191, 295, 1412, 11, 457, 40061, 48948, 9227, 11, 50558], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12124783305798546, "compression_ratio": 1.6634304207119741, "no_speech_prob": 1.875915438612208e-12}, {"id": 662, "seek": 239856, "start": 2402.72, "end": 2406.66, "text": " the active bouncers at the door of history, checking the provenance of every event before", "tokens": [50573, 264, 4967, 15521, 8530, 412, 264, 2853, 295, 2503, 11, 8568, 264, 12785, 719, 295, 633, 2280, 949, 50770], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12124783305798546, "compression_ratio": 1.6634304207119741, "no_speech_prob": 1.875915438612208e-12}, {"id": 663, "seek": 239856, "start": 2406.66, "end": 2407.18, "text": " admitting it.", "tokens": [50770, 44056, 309, 13, 50796], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12124783305798546, "compression_ratio": 1.6634304207119741, "no_speech_prob": 1.875915438612208e-12}, {"id": 664, "seek": 239856, "start": 2407.48, "end": 2412.18, "text": " We saw how a type error isn't a crash, but an early refusal preventing a bad history.", "tokens": [50811, 492, 1866, 577, 257, 2010, 6713, 1943, 380, 257, 8252, 11, 457, 364, 2440, 48948, 19965, 257, 1578, 2503, 13, 51046], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12124783305798546, "compression_ratio": 1.6634304207119741, "no_speech_prob": 1.875915438612208e-12}, {"id": 665, "seek": 239856, "start": 2412.56, "end": 2416.56, "text": " We brought in the Curry-Howard correspondence, realizing that proving a mathematical theorem", "tokens": [51065, 492, 3038, 294, 264, 34789, 12, 6462, 515, 38135, 11, 16734, 300, 27221, 257, 18894, 20904, 51265], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12124783305798546, "compression_ratio": 1.6634304207119741, "no_speech_prob": 1.875915438612208e-12}, {"id": 666, "seek": 239856, "start": 2416.56, "end": 2418.66, "text": " means building an unrefusable history.", "tokens": [51265, 1355, 2390, 364, 20584, 69, 301, 712, 2503, 13, 51370], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12124783305798546, "compression_ratio": 1.6634304207119741, "no_speech_prob": 1.875915438612208e-12}, {"id": 667, "seek": 239856, "start": 2419.16, "end": 2422.44, "text": " And then we pulled back the curtain to reveal the universal operator machine.", "tokens": [51395, 400, 550, 321, 7373, 646, 264, 26789, 281, 10658, 264, 11455, 12973, 3479, 13, 51559], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12124783305798546, "compression_ratio": 1.6634304207119741, "no_speech_prob": 1.875915438612208e-12}, {"id": 668, "seek": 239856, "start": 2422.58, "end": 2423.62, "text": " The motherboard and the cartridges?", "tokens": [51566, 440, 32916, 293, 264, 47036, 30, 51618], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12124783305798546, "compression_ratio": 1.6634304207119741, "no_speech_prob": 1.875915438612208e-12}, {"id": 669, "seek": 242362, "start": 2423.62, "end": 2424.06, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [50365, 1079, 13, 50387], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12480154804799748, "compression_ratio": 1.518987341772152, "no_speech_prob": 2.7400440857222597e-12}, {"id": 670, "seek": 242362, "start": 2424.46, "end": 2428.7599999999998, "text": " We saw that Boolean logic, fuzzy logic, and neural networks aren't entirely different", "tokens": [50407, 492, 1866, 300, 23351, 28499, 9952, 11, 34710, 9952, 11, 293, 18161, 9590, 3212, 380, 7696, 819, 50622], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12480154804799748, "compression_ratio": 1.518987341772152, "no_speech_prob": 2.7400440857222597e-12}, {"id": 671, "seek": 242362, "start": 2428.7599999999998, "end": 2429.6, "text": " fields of science.", "tokens": [50622, 7909, 295, 3497, 13, 50664], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12480154804799748, "compression_ratio": 1.518987341772152, "no_speech_prob": 2.7400440857222597e-12}, {"id": 672, "seek": 242362, "start": 2429.8199999999997, "end": 2434.02, "text": " They are all just swappable cartridges running on the exact same composition graphs.", "tokens": [50675, 814, 366, 439, 445, 1693, 1746, 712, 47036, 2614, 322, 264, 1900, 912, 12686, 24877, 13, 50885], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12480154804799748, "compression_ratio": 1.518987341772152, "no_speech_prob": 2.7400440857222597e-12}, {"id": 673, "seek": 242362, "start": 2434.46, "end": 2439.2, "text": " And finally, we dismantled the illusion of syntax and time, revealing that the code we", "tokens": [50907, 400, 2721, 11, 321, 30506, 1493, 264, 18854, 295, 28431, 293, 565, 11, 23983, 300, 264, 3089, 321, 51144], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12480154804799748, "compression_ratio": 1.518987341772152, "no_speech_prob": 2.7400440857222597e-12}, {"id": 674, "seek": 242362, "start": 2439.2, "end": 2443.72, "text": " write is just a lossy projection of these magnificent multidimensional graphs.", "tokens": [51144, 2464, 307, 445, 257, 4470, 88, 22743, 295, 613, 23690, 2120, 327, 332, 11075, 24877, 13, 51370], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12480154804799748, "compression_ratio": 1.518987341772152, "no_speech_prob": 2.7400440857222597e-12}, {"id": 675, "seek": 244372, "start": 2443.72, "end": 2449.8599999999997, "text": " We saw that loops and computer memory are just cycles in the graph, generating linear sequences", "tokens": [50365, 492, 1866, 300, 16121, 293, 3820, 4675, 366, 445, 17796, 294, 264, 4295, 11, 17746, 8213, 22978, 50672], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17358266512552897, "compression_ratio": 1.2358490566037736, "no_speech_prob": 2.0320147474384154e-12}, {"id": 676, "seek": 244372, "start": 2449.8599999999997, "end": 2451.58, "text": " of terminant, constructive history.", "tokens": [50672, 295, 10761, 394, 11, 30223, 2503, 13, 50758], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17358266512552897, "compression_ratio": 1.2358490566037736, "no_speech_prob": 2.0320147474384154e-12}, {"id": 677, "seek": 245158, "start": 2451.58, "end": 2455.34, "text": " It is a stunning unified theory of computation.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 307, 257, 18550, 26787, 5261, 295, 24903, 13, 50553], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1314826400912538, "compression_ratio": 1.5490196078431373, "no_speech_prob": 1.8182097537636221e-12}, {"id": 678, "seek": 245158, "start": 2455.72, "end": 2460.44, "text": " But before we go, I know you have one final thought on this, and it looks beyond just computers", "tokens": [50572, 583, 949, 321, 352, 11, 286, 458, 291, 362, 472, 2572, 1194, 322, 341, 11, 293, 309, 1542, 4399, 445, 10807, 50808], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1314826400912538, "compression_ratio": 1.5490196078431373, "no_speech_prob": 1.8182097537636221e-12}, {"id": 679, "seek": 245158, "start": 2460.44, "end": 2461.34, "text": " and math.", "tokens": [50808, 293, 5221, 13, 50853], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1314826400912538, "compression_ratio": 1.5490196078431373, "no_speech_prob": 1.8182097537636221e-12}, {"id": 680, "seek": 245158, "start": 2461.6, "end": 2461.9, "text": " I do.", "tokens": [50866, 286, 360, 13, 50881], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1314826400912538, "compression_ratio": 1.5490196078431373, "no_speech_prob": 1.8182097537636221e-12}, {"id": 681, "seek": 245158, "start": 2462.54, "end": 2465.52, "text": " The implications of this go far beyond writing better code.", "tokens": [50913, 440, 16602, 295, 341, 352, 1400, 4399, 3579, 1101, 3089, 13, 51062], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1314826400912538, "compression_ratio": 1.5490196078431373, "no_speech_prob": 1.8182097537636221e-12}, {"id": 682, "seek": 245158, "start": 2466.1, "end": 2470.94, "text": " If we take Flixian's premise seriously, that every computational paradigm, whether it", "tokens": [51091, 759, 321, 747, 3235, 970, 952, 311, 22045, 6638, 11, 300, 633, 28270, 24709, 11, 1968, 309, 51333], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1314826400912538, "compression_ratio": 1.5490196078431373, "no_speech_prob": 1.8182097537636221e-12}, {"id": 683, "seek": 245158, "start": 2470.94, "end": 2476.56, "text": " is rigid binary logic or fluid probability or complex neural network, is just a swappable", "tokens": [51333, 307, 22195, 17434, 9952, 420, 9113, 8482, 420, 3997, 18161, 3209, 11, 307, 445, 257, 1693, 1746, 712, 51614], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1314826400912538, "compression_ratio": 1.5490196078431373, "no_speech_prob": 1.8182097537636221e-12}, {"id": 684, "seek": 247656, "start": 2476.56, "end": 2479.7999999999997, "text": " operator library running on an irreversible historical graph.", "tokens": [50365, 12973, 6405, 2614, 322, 364, 16014, 840, 964, 8584, 4295, 13, 50527], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1605636241824128, "compression_ratio": 1.655844155844156, "no_speech_prob": 2.1423457625957543e-12}, {"id": 685, "seek": 247656, "start": 2480.22, "end": 2482.2799999999997, "text": " It forces us to ask a profound question.", "tokens": [50548, 467, 5874, 505, 281, 1029, 257, 14382, 1168, 13, 50651], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1605636241824128, "compression_ratio": 1.655844155844156, "no_speech_prob": 2.1423457625957543e-12}, {"id": 686, "seek": 247656, "start": 2482.32, "end": 2482.98, "text": " Okay, I'm ready.", "tokens": [50653, 1033, 11, 286, 478, 1919, 13, 50686], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1605636241824128, "compression_ratio": 1.655844155844156, "no_speech_prob": 2.1423457625957543e-12}, {"id": 687, "seek": 247656, "start": 2483.2799999999997, "end": 2486.1, "text": " Does human memory and consciousness work the exact same way?", "tokens": [50701, 4402, 1952, 4675, 293, 10081, 589, 264, 1900, 912, 636, 30, 50842], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1605636241824128, "compression_ratio": 1.655844155844156, "no_speech_prob": 2.1423457625957543e-12}, {"id": 688, "seek": 247656, "start": 2486.42, "end": 2487.34, "text": " Think about your own mind.", "tokens": [50858, 6557, 466, 428, 1065, 1575, 13, 50904], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1605636241824128, "compression_ratio": 1.655844155844156, "no_speech_prob": 2.1423457625957543e-12}, {"id": 689, "seek": 247656, "start": 2487.7, "end": 2489.02, "text": " We do not overwrite our past.", "tokens": [50922, 492, 360, 406, 670, 21561, 527, 1791, 13, 50988], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1605636241824128, "compression_ratio": 1.655844155844156, "no_speech_prob": 2.1423457625957543e-12}, {"id": 690, "seek": 247656, "start": 2489.2599999999998, "end": 2491.34, "text": " We cannot erase the whiteboard of our experiences.", "tokens": [51000, 492, 2644, 23525, 264, 2418, 3787, 295, 527, 5235, 13, 51104], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1605636241824128, "compression_ratio": 1.655844155844156, "no_speech_prob": 2.1423457625957543e-12}, {"id": 691, "seek": 247656, "start": 2491.64, "end": 2493.92, "text": " We accumulate irreversible, constructive events.", "tokens": [51119, 492, 33384, 16014, 840, 964, 11, 30223, 3931, 13, 51233], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1605636241824128, "compression_ratio": 1.655844155844156, "no_speech_prob": 2.1423457625957543e-12}, {"id": 692, "seek": 247656, "start": 2494.0, "end": 2494.7999999999997, "text": " We are our history.", "tokens": [51237, 492, 366, 527, 2503, 13, 51277], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1605636241824128, "compression_ratio": 1.655844155844156, "no_speech_prob": 2.1423457625957543e-12}, {"id": 693, "seek": 247656, "start": 2494.7999999999997, "end": 2499.02, "text": " We carry our providence with us every second of every day.", "tokens": [51277, 492, 3985, 527, 1439, 2778, 365, 505, 633, 1150, 295, 633, 786, 13, 51488], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1605636241824128, "compression_ratio": 1.655844155844156, "no_speech_prob": 2.1423457625957543e-12}, {"id": 694, "seek": 247656, "start": 2499.88, "end": 2505.24, "text": " It's what we call our personality or our cognition, simply the specific operator library that", "tokens": [51531, 467, 311, 437, 321, 818, 527, 9033, 420, 527, 46905, 11, 2935, 264, 2685, 12973, 6405, 300, 51799], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1605636241824128, "compression_ratio": 1.655844155844156, "no_speech_prob": 2.1423457625957543e-12}, {"id": 695, "seek": 250524, "start": 2505.24, "end": 2511.06, "text": " our brain currently uses to navigate and evaluate that massive, unerasable graph of our life's", "tokens": [50365, 527, 3567, 4362, 4960, 281, 12350, 293, 13059, 300, 5994, 11, 517, 260, 296, 712, 4295, 295, 527, 993, 311, 50656], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12141937842735877, "compression_ratio": 1.745928338762215, "no_speech_prob": 1.4217490032497615e-12}, {"id": 696, "seek": 250524, "start": 2511.06, "end": 2511.3199999999997, "text": " history.", "tokens": [50656, 2503, 13, 50669], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12141937842735877, "compression_ratio": 1.745928338762215, "no_speech_prob": 1.4217490032497615e-12}, {"id": 697, "seek": 250524, "start": 2511.8999999999996, "end": 2517.08, "text": " And if our operators change as we grow older and gain wisdom, the graph of our past remains", "tokens": [50698, 400, 498, 527, 19077, 1319, 382, 321, 1852, 4906, 293, 6052, 10712, 11, 264, 4295, 295, 527, 1791, 7023, 50957], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12141937842735877, "compression_ratio": 1.745928338762215, "no_speech_prob": 1.4217490032497615e-12}, {"id": 698, "seek": 250524, "start": 2517.08, "end": 2521.52, "text": " identical, but our interpretation of that history transforms completely.", "tokens": [50957, 14800, 11, 457, 527, 14174, 295, 300, 2503, 35592, 2584, 13, 51179], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12141937842735877, "compression_ratio": 1.745928338762215, "no_speech_prob": 1.4217490032497615e-12}, {"id": 699, "seek": 250524, "start": 2521.7, "end": 2522.14, "text": " Wow.", "tokens": [51188, 3153, 13, 51210], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12141937842735877, "compression_ratio": 1.745928338762215, "no_speech_prob": 1.4217490032497615e-12}, {"id": 700, "seek": 250524, "start": 2522.8199999999997, "end": 2525.7999999999997, "text": " Are we just accumulating irreversible, constructive events?", "tokens": [51244, 2014, 321, 445, 12989, 12162, 16014, 840, 964, 11, 30223, 3931, 30, 51393], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12141937842735877, "compression_ratio": 1.745928338762215, "no_speech_prob": 1.421749